155#define YYLLOC_DEFAULT(Current, Rhs, N) \

165 (Current).end_pos = YYRHSLOC(Rhs, 0).end_pos; \
166 } \
167 while (0)

184enum lex_state_bits {
185 EXPR_BEG_bit, /* ignore newline, +/- is a sign. */
186 EXPR_END_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
187 EXPR_ENDARG_bit, /* ditto, and unbound braces. */
188 EXPR_ENDFN_bit, /* ditto, and unbound braces. */
189 EXPR_ARG_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
190 EXPR_CMDARG_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
191 EXPR_MID_bit, /* newline significant, +/- is an operator. */
192 EXPR_FNAME_bit, /* ignore newline, no reserved words. */
193 EXPR_DOT_bit, /* right after `.' or `::', no reserved words. */
194 EXPR_CLASS_bit, /* immediate after `class', no here document. */
195 EXPR_LABEL_bit, /* flag bit, label is allowed. */
196 EXPR_LABELED_bit, /* flag bit, just after a label. */
197 EXPR_FITEM_bit, /* symbol literal as FNAME. */
198 EXPR_MAX_STATE
199};
200/* examine combinations */
201enum lex_state_e {
202#define DEF_EXPR(n) EXPR_##n = (1 << EXPR_##n##_bit)
203 DEF_EXPR(BEG),
204 DEF_EXPR(END),
205 DEF_EXPR(ENDARG),
206 DEF_EXPR(ENDFN),
207 DEF_EXPR(ARG),
208 DEF_EXPR(CMDARG),
209 DEF_EXPR(MID),
210 DEF_EXPR(FNAME),
211 DEF_EXPR(DOT),
212 DEF_EXPR(CLASS),
213 DEF_EXPR(LABEL),
214 DEF_EXPR(LABELED),
215 DEF_EXPR(FITEM),
216 EXPR_VALUE = EXPR_BEG,
217 EXPR_BEG_ANY = (EXPR_BEG | EXPR_MID | EXPR_CLASS),
218 EXPR_ARG_ANY = (EXPR_ARG | EXPR_CMDARG),
219 EXPR_END_ANY = (EXPR_END | EXPR_ENDARG | EXPR_ENDFN),
220 EXPR_NONE = 0
221};
222#define IS_lex_state_for(x, ls) ((x) & (ls))
223#define IS_lex_state_all_for(x, ls) (((x) & (ls)) == (ls))
224#define IS_lex_state(ls) IS_lex_state_for(p->lex.state, (ls))
225#define IS_lex_state_all(ls) IS_lex_state_all_for(p->lex.state, (ls))
226
227# define SET_LEX_STATE(ls) \
228 parser_set_lex_state(p, ls, __LINE__)
229static inline enum lex_state_e parser_set_lex_state(struct parser_params *p, enum lex_state_e ls, int line);

233static const rb_code_location_t NULL_LOC = { {0, -1}, {0, -1} };

235# define SHOW_BITSTACK(stack, name) (p->debug ? rb_parser_show_bitstack(p, stack, name, __LINE__) : (void)0)
236# define BITSTACK_PUSH(stack, n) (((p->stack) = ((p->stack)<<1)|((n)&1)), SHOW_BITSTACK(p->stack, #stack"(push)"))
237# define BITSTACK_POP(stack) (((p->stack) = (p->stack) >> 1), SHOW_BITSTACK(p->stack, #stack"(pop)"))
238# define BITSTACK_SET_P(stack) (SHOW_BITSTACK(p->stack, #stack), (p->stack)&1)
239# define BITSTACK_SET(stack, n) ((p->stack)=(n), SHOW_BITSTACK(p->stack, #stack"(set)"))
240
241/* A flag to identify keyword_do_cond, "do" keyword after condition expression.
242 Examples: `while ... do`, `until ... do`, and `for ... in ... do` */
243#define COND_PUSH(n) BITSTACK_PUSH(cond_stack, (n))
244#define COND_POP() BITSTACK_POP(cond_stack)
245#define COND_P() BITSTACK_SET_P(cond_stack)
246#define COND_SET(n) BITSTACK_SET(cond_stack, (n))
247
248/* A flag to identify keyword_do_block; "do" keyword after command_call.
249 Example: `foo 1, 2 do`. */
250#define CMDARG_PUSH(n) BITSTACK_PUSH(cmdarg_stack, (n))
251#define CMDARG_POP() BITSTACK_POP(cmdarg_stack)
252#define CMDARG_P() BITSTACK_SET_P(cmdarg_stack)
253#define CMDARG_SET(n) BITSTACK_SET(cmdarg_stack, (n))

277enum {
278 ORDINAL_PARAM = -1,
279 NO_PARAM = 0,
280 NUMPARAM_MAX = 9,
281};
282
283#define NUMPARAM_ID_P(id) numparam_id_p(id)
284#define NUMPARAM_ID_TO_IDX(id) (unsigned int)(((id) >> ID_SCOPE_SHIFT) - tNUMPARAM_1 + 1)
285#define NUMPARAM_IDX_TO_ID(idx) TOKEN2LOCALID((tNUMPARAM_1 + (idx) - 1))
286static int
287numparam_id_p(ID id)
288{
289 if (!is_local_id(id)) return 0;
290 unsigned int idx = NUMPARAM_ID_TO_IDX(id);
291 return idx > 0 && idx <= NUMPARAM_MAX;
292}

309/*
310 Structure of Lexer Buffer:
311
312 lex.pbeg lex.ptok lex.pcur lex.pend
313 | | | |
314 |------------+------------+------------|
315 |<---------->|
316 token
317*/

339 /* track the nest level of any parens "()[]{}" */
340 int paren_nest;

342 int lpar_beg;
343 /* track the nest level of only braces "{}" */
344 int brace_nest;
345 } lex;
346 stack_type cond_stack;
347 stack_type cmdarg_stack;
348 int tokidx;

429static st_table *
430push_pvtbl(struct parser_params *p)
431{
432 st_table *tbl = p->pvtbl;
433 p->pvtbl = st_init_numtable();
434 return tbl;
435}
436
437static void
438pop_pvtbl(struct parser_params *p, st_table *tbl)
439{
440 st_free_table(p->pvtbl);
441 p->pvtbl = tbl;
442}
443
444static st_table *
445push_pktbl(struct parser_params *p)
446{
447 st_table *tbl = p->pktbl;
448 p->pktbl = 0;
449 return tbl;
450}
451
452static void
453pop_pktbl(struct parser_params *p, st_table *tbl)
454{
455 if (p->pktbl) st_free_table(p->pktbl);
456 p->pktbl = tbl;
457}

531static inline void
532set_line_body(NODE *body, int line)
533{
534 if (!body) return;
535 switch (nd_type(body)) {
536 case NODE_RESCUE:
537 case NODE_ENSURE:
538 nd_set_line(body, line);
539 }

779/* structs for managing terminator of string literal and heredocment */
780typedef struct rb_strterm_literal_struct {
781 union {
782 VALUE dummy;
783 long nest;
784 } u0;
785 union {
786 VALUE dummy;
787 long func; /* STR_FUNC_* (e.g., STR_FUNC_ESCAPE and STR_FUNC_EXPAND) */
788 } u1;
789 union {
790 VALUE dummy;
791 long paren; /* '(' of `%q(...)` */
792 } u2;
793 union {
794 VALUE dummy;
795 long term; /* ')' of `%q(...)` */
796 } u3;
797} rb_strterm_literal_t;
798
799#define HERETERM_LENGTH_BITS ((SIZEOF_VALUE - 1) * CHAR_BIT - 1)
800
801struct rb_strterm_heredoc_struct {
802 VALUE lastline; /* the string of line that contains `<<"END"` */
803 long offset; /* the column of END in `<<"END"` */
804 int sourceline; /* lineno of the line that contains `<<"END"` */
805 unsigned length /* the length of END in `<<"END"` */
806#if HERETERM_LENGTH_BITS < SIZEOF_INT * CHAR_BIT
807 : HERETERM_LENGTH_BITS
808# define HERETERM_LENGTH_MAX ((1U << HERETERM_LENGTH_BITS) - 1)
809#else
810# define HERETERM_LENGTH_MAX UINT_MAX
811#endif
812 ;
813#if HERETERM_LENGTH_BITS < SIZEOF_INT * CHAR_BIT
814 unsigned quote: 1;
815 unsigned func: 8;
816#else
817 uint8_t quote;
818 uint8_t func;
819#endif
820};
821STATIC_ASSERT(rb_strterm_heredoc_t, sizeof(rb_strterm_heredoc_t) <= 4 * SIZEOF_VALUE);
822
823#define STRTERM_HEREDOC IMEMO_FL_USER0
824
825struct rb_strterm_struct {
826 VALUE flags;
827 union {
828 rb_strterm_literal_t literal;
829 rb_strterm_heredoc_t heredoc;
830 } u;
831};
832
833#ifndef RIPPER
834void
835rb_strterm_mark(VALUE obj)
836{
837 rb_strterm_t *strterm = (rb_strterm_t*)obj;
838 if (RBASIC(obj)->flags & STRTERM_HEREDOC) {
839 rb_strterm_heredoc_t *heredoc = &strterm->u.heredoc;
840 rb_gc_mark(heredoc->lastline);
841 }
842}
843#endif

848#define TOKEN2ID(tok) ( \
849 tTOKEN_LOCAL_BEGIN<(tok)&&(tok)<tTOKEN_LOCAL_END ? TOKEN2LOCALID(tok) : \
850 tTOKEN_INSTANCE_BEGIN<(tok)&&(tok)<tTOKEN_INSTANCE_END ? TOKEN2INSTANCEID(tok) : \
851 tTOKEN_GLOBAL_BEGIN<(tok)&&(tok)<tTOKEN_GLOBAL_END ? TOKEN2GLOBALID(tok) : \
852 tTOKEN_CONST_BEGIN<(tok)&&(tok)<tTOKEN_CONST_END ? TOKEN2CONSTID(tok) : \
853 tTOKEN_CLASS_BEGIN<(tok)&&(tok)<tTOKEN_CLASS_END ? TOKEN2CLASSID(tok) : \
854 tTOKEN_ATTRSET_BEGIN<(tok)&&(tok)<tTOKEN_ATTRSET_END ? TOKEN2ATTRSETID(tok) : \
855 ((tok) / ((tok)<tPRESERVED_ID_END && ((tok)>=128 || rb_ispunct(tok)))))

867static VALUE ripper_dispatch0(struct parser_params*,ID);
868static VALUE ripper_dispatch1(struct parser_params*,ID,VALUE);
869static VALUE ripper_dispatch2(struct parser_params*,ID,VALUE,VALUE);
870static VALUE ripper_dispatch3(struct parser_params*,ID,VALUE,VALUE,VALUE);

876#define dispatch0(n) ripper_dispatch0(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n))
877#define dispatch1(n,a) ripper_dispatch1(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n), (a))
878#define dispatch2(n,a,b) ripper_dispatch2(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n), (a), (b))
879#define dispatch3(n,a,b,c) ripper_dispatch3(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n), (a), (b), (c))
880#define dispatch4(n,a,b,c,d) ripper_dispatch4(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n), (a), (b), (c), (d))
881#define dispatch5(n,a,b,c,d,e) ripper_dispatch5(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n), (a), (b), (c), (d), (e))
882#define dispatch7(n,a,b,c,d,e,f,g) ripper_dispatch7(p, TOKEN_PASTE(ripper_id_, n), (a), (b), (c), (d), (e), (f), (g))

895static inline VALUE
896new_args(struct parser_params *p, VALUE pre_args, VALUE opt_args, VALUE rest_arg, VALUE post_args, VALUE tail, YYLTYPE *loc)
897{
898 NODE *t = (NODE *)tail;
899 VALUE kw_args = t->u1.value, kw_rest_arg = t->u2.value, block = t->u3.value;
900 return params_new(pre_args, opt_args, rest_arg, post_args, kw_args, kw_rest_arg, escape_Qundef(block));
901}
902
903static inline VALUE
904new_args_tail(struct parser_params *p, VALUE kw_args, VALUE kw_rest_arg, VALUE block, YYLTYPE *loc)
905{
906 NODE *t = rb_node_newnode(NODE_ARGS_AUX, kw_args, kw_rest_arg, block, &NULL_LOC);
907 add_mark_object(p, kw_args);
908 add_mark_object(p, kw_rest_arg);
909 add_mark_object(p, block);
910 return (VALUE)t;
911}

918
919static VALUE
920new_array_pattern(struct parser_params *p, VALUE constant, VALUE pre_arg, VALUE aryptn, const YYLTYPE *loc)
921{
922 NODE *t = (NODE *)aryptn;
923 VALUE pre_args = t->u1.value, rest_arg = t->u2.value, post_args = t->u3.value;
924
925 if (!NIL_P(pre_arg)) {
926 if (!NIL_P(pre_args)) {
927 rb_ary_unshift(pre_args, pre_arg);
928 }
929 else {
930 pre_args = rb_ary_new_from_args(1, pre_arg);
931 }
932 }
933 return dispatch4(aryptn, constant, pre_args, rest_arg, post_args);
934}
935
936static VALUE
937new_array_pattern_tail(struct parser_params *p, VALUE pre_args, VALUE has_rest, VALUE rest_arg, VALUE post_args, const YYLTYPE *loc)
938{
939 NODE *t;
940
941 if (has_rest) {
942 rest_arg = dispatch1(var_field, rest_arg ? rest_arg : Qnil);
943 }
944 else {
945 rest_arg = Qnil;
946 }
947
948 t = rb_node_newnode(NODE_ARYPTN, pre_args, rest_arg, post_args, &NULL_LOC);
949 add_mark_object(p, pre_args);
950 add_mark_object(p, rest_arg);
951 add_mark_object(p, post_args);
952 return (VALUE)t;
953}
954
955static VALUE
956new_find_pattern(struct parser_params *p, VALUE constant, VALUE fndptn, const YYLTYPE *loc)
957{
958 NODE *t = (NODE *)fndptn;
959 VALUE pre_rest_arg = t->u1.value, args = t->u2.value, post_rest_arg = t->u3.value;
960
961 return dispatch4(fndptn, constant, pre_rest_arg, args, post_rest_arg);
962}
963
964static VALUE
965new_find_pattern_tail(struct parser_params *p, VALUE pre_rest_arg, VALUE args, VALUE post_rest_arg, const YYLTYPE *loc)
966{
967 NODE *t;
968
969 pre_rest_arg = dispatch1(var_field, pre_rest_arg ? pre_rest_arg : Qnil);
970 post_rest_arg = dispatch1(var_field, post_rest_arg ? post_rest_arg : Qnil);
971
972 t = rb_node_newnode(NODE_FNDPTN, pre_rest_arg, args, post_rest_arg, &NULL_LOC);
973 add_mark_object(p, pre_rest_arg);
974 add_mark_object(p, args);
975 add_mark_object(p, post_rest_arg);
976 return (VALUE)t;
977}

987static VALUE
988new_hash_pattern(struct parser_params *p, VALUE constant, VALUE hshptn, const YYLTYPE *loc)
989{
990 NODE *t = (NODE *)hshptn;
991 VALUE kw_args = t->u1.value, kw_rest_arg = t->u2.value;

993}

995static VALUE
996new_hash_pattern_tail(struct parser_params *p, VALUE kw_args, VALUE kw_rest_arg, const YYLTYPE *loc)
997{
998 NODE *t;
999 if (kw_rest_arg) {
1000 kw_rest_arg = dispatch1(var_field, kw_rest_arg);
1001 }
1002 else {
1003 kw_rest_arg = Qnil;
1004 }
1005 t = rb_node_newnode(NODE_HSHPTN, kw_args, kw_rest_arg, 0, &NULL_LOC);
1006
1007 add_mark_object(p, kw_args);
1008 add_mark_object(p, kw_rest_arg);
1009 return (VALUE)t;
1010}

1021static NODE *
1022set_defun_body(struct parser_params *p, NODE *n, NODE *args, NODE *body, const YYLTYPE *loc)
1023{
1024 body = remove_begin(body);
1025 reduce_nodes(p, &body);
1026 n->nd_defn = NEW_SCOPE(args, body, loc);
1027 n->nd_loc = *loc;
1028 nd_set_line(n->nd_defn, loc->end_pos.lineno);
1029 set_line_body(body, loc->beg_pos.lineno);
1030 return n;
1031}

1033static NODE *
1034rescued_expr(struct parser_params *p, NODE *arg, NODE *rescue,
1035 const YYLTYPE *arg_loc, const YYLTYPE *mod_loc, const YYLTYPE *res_loc)
1036{
1037 YYLTYPE loc = code_loc_gen(mod_loc, res_loc);
1038 rescue = NEW_RESBODY(0, remove_begin(rescue), 0, &loc);
1039 loc.beg_pos = arg_loc->beg_pos;
1040 return NEW_RESCUE(arg, rescue, 0, &loc);
1041}

1045static void
1046restore_defun(struct parser_params *p, NODE *name)
1047{
1048 YYSTYPE c = {.val = name->nd_cval};
1049 p->cur_arg = name->nd_vid;
1050 p->ctxt.in_def = c.ctxt.in_def;
1051 p->ctxt.shareable_constant_value = c.ctxt.shareable_constant_value;
1052}

1054static void
1055endless_method_name(struct parser_params *p, NODE *defn, const YYLTYPE *loc)
1056{
1057#ifdef RIPPER
1058 defn = defn->nd_defn;
1059#endif
1060 ID mid = defn->nd_mid;
1061 if (is_attrset_id(mid)) {
1062 yyerror1(loc, "setter method cannot be defined in an endless method definition");
1063 }
1064 token_info_drop(p, "def", loc->beg_pos);
1065}

1077# define rb_warn0(fmt) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS(fmt, 1))
1078# define rb_warn1(fmt,a) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS(fmt, 2), (a))
1079# define rb_warn2(fmt,a,b) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS(fmt, 3), (a), (b))
1080# define rb_warn3(fmt,a,b,c) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS(fmt, 4), (a), (b), (c))
1081# define rb_warn4(fmt,a,b,c,d) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS(fmt, 5), (a), (b), (c), (d))
1082# define rb_warning0(fmt) WARNING_CALL(WARNING_ARGS(fmt, 1))
1083# define rb_warning1(fmt,a) WARNING_CALL(WARNING_ARGS(fmt, 2), (a))
1084# define rb_warning2(fmt,a,b) WARNING_CALL(WARNING_ARGS(fmt, 3), (a), (b))
1085# define rb_warning3(fmt,a,b,c) WARNING_CALL(WARNING_ARGS(fmt, 4), (a), (b), (c))
1086# define rb_warning4(fmt,a,b,c,d) WARNING_CALL(WARNING_ARGS(fmt, 5), (a), (b), (c), (d))
1087# define rb_warn0L(l,fmt) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS_L(l, fmt, 1))
1088# define rb_warn1L(l,fmt,a) WARN_CALL(WARN_ARGS_L(l, fmt, 2), (a))

1798/* On compilers that do not define __PTRDIFF_MAX__ etc., make sure
1799 <limits.h> and (if available) <stdint.h> are included
1800 so that the code can choose integer types of a good width. */
1801
1802#ifndef __PTRDIFF_MAX__
1803# include <limits.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1804# if defined __STDC_VERSION__ && 199901 <= __STDC_VERSION__
1805# include <stdint.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1806# define YY_STDINT_H
1807# endif
1808#endif
1809
1810/* Narrow types that promote to a signed type and that can represent a
1811 signed or unsigned integer of at least N bits. In tables they can
1812 save space and decrease cache pressure. Promoting to a signed type
1813 helps avoid bugs in integer arithmetic. */
1814
1815#ifdef __INT_LEAST8_MAX__
1816typedef __INT_LEAST8_TYPE__ yytype_int8;
1817#elif defined YY_STDINT_H
1818typedef int_least8_t yytype_int8;
1819#else
1820typedef signed char yytype_int8;
1821#endif
1822
1823#ifdef __INT_LEAST16_MAX__
1824typedef __INT_LEAST16_TYPE__ yytype_int16;
1825#elif defined YY_STDINT_H
1826typedef int_least16_t yytype_int16;
1827#else
1828typedef short yytype_int16;
1829#endif
1830
1831/* Work around bug in HP-UX 11.23, which defines these macros
1832 incorrectly for preprocessor constants. This workaround can likely
1833 be removed in 2023, as HPE has promised support for HP-UX 11.23
1834 (aka HP-UX 11i v2) only through the end of 2022; see Table 2 of
1835 <https://h20195.www2.hpe.com/V2/getpdf.aspx/4AA4-7673ENW.pdf>. */
1836#ifdef __hpux
1837# undef UINT_LEAST8_MAX
1838# undef UINT_LEAST16_MAX
1839# define UINT_LEAST8_MAX 255
1840# define UINT_LEAST16_MAX 65535
1841#endif
1842
1843#if defined __UINT_LEAST8_MAX__ && __UINT_LEAST8_MAX__ <= __INT_MAX__
1844typedef __UINT_LEAST8_TYPE__ yytype_uint8;
1845#elif (!defined __UINT_LEAST8_MAX__ && defined YY_STDINT_H \
1846 && UINT_LEAST8_MAX <= INT_MAX)
1847typedef uint_least8_t yytype_uint8;
1848#elif !defined __UINT_LEAST8_MAX__ && UCHAR_MAX <= INT_MAX
1849typedef unsigned char yytype_uint8;
1850#else
1851typedef short yytype_uint8;
1852#endif
1853
1854#if defined __UINT_LEAST16_MAX__ && __UINT_LEAST16_MAX__ <= __INT_MAX__
1855typedef __UINT_LEAST16_TYPE__ yytype_uint16;
1856#elif (!defined __UINT_LEAST16_MAX__ && defined YY_STDINT_H \
1857 && UINT_LEAST16_MAX <= INT_MAX)
1858typedef uint_least16_t yytype_uint16;
1859#elif !defined __UINT_LEAST16_MAX__ && USHRT_MAX <= INT_MAX
1860typedef unsigned short yytype_uint16;
1861#else
1862typedef int yytype_uint16;
1863#endif
1864
1865#ifndef YYPTRDIFF_T
1866# if defined __PTRDIFF_TYPE__ && defined __PTRDIFF_MAX__
1867# define YYPTRDIFF_T __PTRDIFF_TYPE__
1868# define YYPTRDIFF_MAXIMUM __PTRDIFF_MAX__
1869# elif defined PTRDIFF_MAX
1870# ifndef ptrdiff_t
1871# include <stddef.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1872# endif
1873# define YYPTRDIFF_T ptrdiff_t
1874# define YYPTRDIFF_MAXIMUM PTRDIFF_MAX
1875# else
1876# define YYPTRDIFF_T long
1877# define YYPTRDIFF_MAXIMUM LONG_MAX
1878# endif
1879#endif

1881#ifndef YYSIZE_T

1884# elif defined size_t

1886# elif defined __STDC_VERSION__ && 199901 <= __STDC_VERSION__

1888# define YYSIZE_T size_t
1889# else
1890# define YYSIZE_T unsigned
1891# endif
1892#endif
1893
1894#define YYSIZE_MAXIMUM \
1895 YY_CAST (YYPTRDIFF_T, \
1896 (YYPTRDIFF_MAXIMUM < YY_CAST (YYSIZE_T, -1) \
1897 ? YYPTRDIFF_MAXIMUM \
1898 : YY_CAST (YYSIZE_T, -1)))
1899
1900#define YYSIZEOF(X) YY_CAST (YYPTRDIFF_T, sizeof (X))

1945/* Suppress an incorrect diagnostic about yylval being uninitialized. */
1946#if defined __GNUC__ && ! defined __ICC && 406 <= __GNUC__ * 100 + __GNUC_MINOR__
1947# if __GNUC__ * 100 + __GNUC_MINOR__ < 407
1948# define YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_BEGIN \
1949 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic push") \
1950 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wuninitialized\"")
1951# else
1952# define YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_BEGIN \
1953 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic push") \
1954 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wuninitialized\"") \
1955 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wmaybe-uninitialized\"")
1956# endif
1957# define YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_END \
1958 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic pop")
1959#else
1960# define YY_INITIAL_VALUE(Value) Value
1961#endif
1962#ifndef YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_BEGIN
1963# define YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_BEGIN
1964# define YY_IGNORE_MAYBE_UNINITIALIZED_END
1965#endif
1966#ifndef YY_INITIAL_VALUE
1967# define YY_INITIAL_VALUE(Value) /* Nothing. */
1968#endif

1973 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wuseless-cast\"")
1974# define YY_IGNORE_USELESS_CAST_END \
1975 _Pragma ("GCC diagnostic pop")
1976#endif

1986
1987/* The parser invokes alloca or malloc; define the necessary symbols. */
1988
1989# ifdef YYSTACK_USE_ALLOCA
1990# if YYSTACK_USE_ALLOCA
1991# ifdef __GNUC__
1992# define YYSTACK_ALLOC __builtin_alloca
1993# elif defined __BUILTIN_VA_ARG_INCR
1994# include <alloca.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1995# elif defined _AIX
1996# define YYSTACK_ALLOC __alloca
1997# elif defined _MSC_VER
1998# include <malloc.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
1999# define alloca _alloca
2000# else
2001# define YYSTACK_ALLOC alloca
2002# if ! defined _ALLOCA_H && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS
2003# include <stdlib.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
2004 /* Use EXIT_SUCCESS as a witness for stdlib.h. */
2005# ifndef EXIT_SUCCESS
2006# define EXIT_SUCCESS 0
2007# endif
2008# endif
2009# endif
2010# endif
2011# endif
2012
2013# ifdef YYSTACK_ALLOC
2014 /* Pacify GCC's 'empty if-body' warning. */
2015# define YYSTACK_FREE(Ptr) do { /* empty */; } while (0)
2016# ifndef YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM
2017 /* The OS might guarantee only one guard page at the bottom of the stack,
2018 and a page size can be as small as 4096 bytes. So we cannot safely
2019 invoke alloca (N) if N exceeds 4096. Use a slightly smaller number
2020 to allow for a few compiler-allocated temporary stack slots. */
2021# define YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM 4032 /* reasonable circa 2006 */
2022# endif
2023# else
2024# define YYSTACK_ALLOC YYMALLOC
2025# define YYSTACK_FREE YYFREE
2026# ifndef YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM
2027# define YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM YYSIZE_MAXIMUM
2028# endif
2029# if (defined __cplusplus && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS \
2030 && ! ((defined YYMALLOC || defined malloc) \
2031 && (defined YYFREE || defined free)))
2032# include <stdlib.h> /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
2033# ifndef EXIT_SUCCESS
2034# define EXIT_SUCCESS 0
2035# endif
2036# endif
2037# ifndef YYMALLOC
2038# define YYMALLOC malloc
2039# if ! defined malloc && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS
2040void *malloc (YYSIZE_T); /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
2041# endif
2042# endif
2043# ifndef YYFREE
2044# define YYFREE free
2045# if ! defined free && ! defined EXIT_SUCCESS
2046void free (void *); /* INFRINGES ON USER NAME SPACE */
2047# endif
2048# endif
2049# endif
2050#endif /* 1 */
2051
2052#if (! defined yyoverflow \
2053 && (! defined __cplusplus \
2054 || (defined YYLTYPE_IS_TRIVIAL && YYLTYPE_IS_TRIVIAL \
2055 && defined YYSTYPE_IS_TRIVIAL && YYSTYPE_IS_TRIVIAL)))
2056
2057/* A type that is properly aligned for any stack member. */
2058union yyalloc
2059{
2060 yy_state_t yyss_alloc;
2061 YYSTYPE yyvs_alloc;
2062 YYLTYPE yyls_alloc;
2063};
2064
2065/* The size of the maximum gap between one aligned stack and the next. */
2066# define YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM (YYSIZEOF (union yyalloc) - 1)
2067
2068/* The size of an array large to enough to hold all stacks, each with
2069 N elements. */
2070# define YYSTACK_BYTES(N) \
2071 ((N) * (YYSIZEOF (yy_state_t) + YYSIZEOF (YYSTYPE) \
2072 + YYSIZEOF (YYLTYPE)) \
2073 + 2 * YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM)
2074
2075# define YYCOPY_NEEDED 1
2076
2077/* Relocate STACK from its old location to the new one. The
2078 local variables YYSIZE and YYSTACKSIZE give the old and new number of
2079 elements in the stack, and YYPTR gives the new location of the
2080 stack. Advance YYPTR to a properly aligned location for the next
2081 stack. */
2082# define YYSTACK_RELOCATE(Stack_alloc, Stack) \
2083 do \
2084 { \
2085 YYPTRDIFF_T yynewbytes; \
2086 YYCOPY (&yyptr->Stack_alloc, Stack, yysize); \
2087 Stack = &yyptr->Stack_alloc; \
2088 yynewbytes = yystacksize * YYSIZEOF (*Stack) + YYSTACK_GAP_MAXIMUM; \
2089 yyptr += yynewbytes / YYSIZEOF (*yyptr); \
2090 } \
2091 while (0)
2092
2093#endif
2094
2095#if defined YYCOPY_NEEDED && YYCOPY_NEEDED
2096/* Copy COUNT objects from SRC to DST. The source and destination do
2097 not overlap. */
2098# ifndef YYCOPY
2099# if defined __GNUC__ && 1 < __GNUC__
2100# define YYCOPY(Dst, Src, Count) \
2101 __builtin_memcpy (Dst, Src, YY_CAST (YYSIZE_T, (Count)) * sizeof (*(Src)))
2102# else
2103# define YYCOPY(Dst, Src, Count) \
2104 do \
2105 { \
2106 YYPTRDIFF_T yyi; \
2107 for (yyi = 0; yyi < (Count); yyi++) \
2108 (Dst)[yyi] = (Src)[yyi]; \
2109 } \
2110 while (0)
2111# endif
2112# endif
2113#endif /* !YYCOPY_NEEDED */
2114

6063 } \

6106/* Print *YYLOCP on YYO. Private, do not rely on its existence. */
6107
6108YY_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED
6109static int
6110yy_location_print_ (FILE *yyo, YYLTYPE const * const yylocp)
6111{
6112 int res = 0;
6113 int end_col = 0 != yylocp->last_column ? yylocp->last_column - 1 : 0;
6114 if (0 <= yylocp->first_line)
6115 {
6116 res += YYFPRINTF (p, "%d", yylocp->first_line);
6117 if (0 <= yylocp->first_column)
6118 res += YYFPRINTF (p, ".%d", yylocp->first_column);
6119 }
6120 if (0 <= yylocp->last_line)
6121 {
6122 if (yylocp->first_line < yylocp->last_line)
6123 {
6124 res += YYFPRINTF (p, "-%d", yylocp->last_line);
6125 if (0 <= end_col)
6126 res += YYFPRINTF (p, ".%d", end_col);
6127 }
6128 else if (0 <= end_col && yylocp->first_column < end_col)
6129 res += YYFPRINTF (p, "-%d", end_col);
6130 }
6131 return res;
6132}

6140# else
6141
6142# define YYLOCATION_PRINT(File, Loc) ((void) 0)

6425static void
6426yy_reduce_print (yy_state_t *yyssp, YYSTYPE *yyvsp, YYLTYPE *yylsp,

6428{

6433 yyrule - 1, yylno);

6440 &yyvsp[(yyi + 1) - (yynrhs)],
6441 &(yylsp[(yyi + 1) - (yynrhs)]), p);
6442 YYFPRINTF (p, "\n");
6443 }
6444}

6490/* Put in YYARG at most YYARGN of the expected tokens given the
6491 current YYCTX, and return the number of tokens stored in YYARG. If
6492 YYARG is null, return the number of expected tokens (guaranteed to
6493 be less than YYNTOKENS). Return YYENOMEM on memory exhaustion.
6494 Return 0 if there are more than YYARGN expected tokens, yet fill
6495 YYARG up to YYARGN. */
6496static int
6497yypcontext_expected_tokens (const yypcontext_t *yyctx,
6498 yysymbol_kind_t yyarg[], int yyargn)
6499{

6569#ifndef yytnamerr
6570/* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary
6571 quotes and backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror. The
6572 heuristic is that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string
6573 contains an apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than
6574 backslash-backslash). YYSTR is taken from yytname. If YYRES is
6575 null, do not copy; instead, return the length of what the result
6576 would have been. */
6577static YYPTRDIFF_T
6578yytnamerr (char *yyres, const char *yystr)
6579{
6580 if (*yystr == '"')
6581 {
6582 YYPTRDIFF_T yyn = 0;
6583 char const *yyp = yystr;
6584 for (;;)
6585 switch (*++yyp)
6586 {
6587 case '\'':
6588 case ',':
6589 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
6590
6591 case '\\':
6592 if (*++yyp != '\\')
6593 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
6594 else
6595 goto append;
6596
6597 append:
6598 default:
6599 if (yyres)
6600 yyres[yyn] = *yyp;
6601 yyn++;
6602 break;
6603
6604 case '"':
6605 if (yyres)
6606 yyres[yyn] = '\0';
6607 return yyn;
6608 }
6609 do_not_strip_quotes: ;
6610 }
6611
6612 if (yyres)
6613 return yystpcpy (yyres, yystr) - yyres;
6614 else
6615 return yystrlen (yystr);
6616}
6617#endif

6620static int
6621yy_syntax_error_arguments (const yypcontext_t *yyctx,
6622 yysymbol_kind_t yyarg[], int yyargn)
6623{
6624 /* Actual size of YYARG. */
6625 int yycount = 0;
6626 /* There are many possibilities here to consider:
6627 - If this state is a consistent state with a default action, then
6628 the only way this function was invoked is if the default action
6629 is an error action. In that case, don't check for expected
6630 tokens because there are none.
6631 - The only way there can be no lookahead present (in yychar) is if
6632 this state is a consistent state with a default action. Thus,
6633 detecting the absence of a lookahead is sufficient to determine
6634 that there is no unexpected or expected token to report. In that
6635 case, just report a simple "syntax error".
6636 - Don't assume there isn't a lookahead just because this state is a
6637 consistent state with a default action. There might have been a
6638 previous inconsistent state, consistent state with a non-default
6639 action, or user semantic action that manipulated yychar.
6640 - Of course, the expected token list depends on states to have
6641 correct lookahead information, and it depends on the parser not
6642 to perform extra reductions after fetching a lookahead from the
6643 scanner and before detecting a syntax error. Thus, state merging
6644 (from LALR or IELR) and default reductions corrupt the expected
6645 token list. However, the list is correct for canonical LR with
6646 one exception: it will still contain any token that will not be
6647 accepted due to an error action in a later state.
6648 */
6649 if (yyctx->yytoken != YYSYMBOL_YYEMPTY)
6650 {
6651 int yyn;
6652 if (yyarg)
6653 yyarg[yycount] = yyctx->yytoken;
6654 ++yycount;
6655 yyn = yypcontext_expected_tokens (yyctx,
6656 yyarg ? yyarg + 1 : yyarg, yyargn - 1);
6657 if (yyn == YYENOMEM)
6658 return YYENOMEM;
6659 else
6660 yycount += yyn;
6661 }
6662 return yycount;
6663}
6664
6665/* Copy into *YYMSG, which is of size *YYMSG_ALLOC, an error message
6666 about the unexpected token YYTOKEN for the state stack whose top is
6667 YYSSP.
6668
6669 Return 0 if *YYMSG was successfully written. Return -1 if *YYMSG is
6670 not large enough to hold the message. In that case, also set
6671 *YYMSG_ALLOC to the required number of bytes. Return YYENOMEM if the
6672 required number of bytes is too large to store. */
6673static int
6674yysyntax_error (struct parser_params *p, YYPTRDIFF_T *yymsg_alloc, char **yymsg,
6675 const yypcontext_t *yyctx)
6676{
6677 enum { YYARGS_MAX = 5 };
6678 /* Internationalized format string. */
6679 const char *yyformat = YY_NULLPTR;
6680 /* Arguments of yyformat: reported tokens (one for the "unexpected",
6681 one per "expected"). */
6682 yysymbol_kind_t yyarg[YYARGS_MAX];
6683 /* Cumulated lengths of YYARG. */
6684 YYPTRDIFF_T yysize = 0;
6685
6686 /* Actual size of YYARG. */
6687 int yycount = yy_syntax_error_arguments (yyctx, yyarg, YYARGS_MAX);
6688 if (yycount == YYENOMEM)
6689 return YYENOMEM;
6690
6691 switch (yycount)
6692 {
6693#define YYCASE_(N, S) \
6694 case N: \
6695 yyformat = S; \
6696 break
6697 default: /* Avoid compiler warnings. */
6698 YYCASE_(0, YY_("syntax error"));
6699 YYCASE_(1, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s"));
6700 YYCASE_(2, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s"));
6701 YYCASE_(3, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s"));
6702 YYCASE_(4, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s or %s"));
6703 YYCASE_(5, YY_("syntax error, unexpected %s, expecting %s or %s or %s or %s"));
6704#undef YYCASE_
6705 }
6706
6707 /* Compute error message size. Don't count the "%s"s, but reserve
6708 room for the terminator. */
6709 yysize = yystrlen (yyformat) - 2 * yycount + 1;
6710 {
6711 int yyi;
6712 for (yyi = 0; yyi < yycount; ++yyi)
6713 {
6714 YYPTRDIFF_T yysize1
6715 = yysize + yytnamerr (YY_NULLPTR, yytname[yyarg[yyi]]);
6716 if (yysize <= yysize1 && yysize1 <= YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM)
6717 yysize = yysize1;
6718 else
6719 return YYENOMEM;
6720 }
6721 }
6722
6723 if (*yymsg_alloc < yysize)
6724 {
6725 *yymsg_alloc = 2 * yysize;
6726 if (! (yysize <= *yymsg_alloc
6727 && *yymsg_alloc <= YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM))
6728 *yymsg_alloc = YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM;
6729 return -1;
6730 }
6731
6732 /* Avoid sprintf, as that infringes on the user's name space.
6733 Don't have undefined behavior even if the translation
6734 produced a string with the wrong number of "%s"s. */
6735 {
6736 char *yyp = *yymsg;
6737 int yyi = 0;
6738 while ((*yyp = *yyformat) != '\0')
6739 if (*yyp == '%' && yyformat[1] == 's' && yyi < yycount)
6740 {
6741 yyp += yytnamerr (yyp, yytname[yyarg[yyi++]]);
6742 yyformat += 2;
6743 }
6744 else
6745 {
6746 ++yyp;
6747 ++yyformat;
6748 }
6749 }
6750 return 0;
6751}

13336 approach of translating immediately before every use of yytoken.
13337 One alternative is translating here after every semantic action,
13338 but that translation would be missed if the semantic action invokes

13651static void
13652ripper_dispatch_delayed_token(struct parser_params *p, enum yytokentype t)
13653{

13655 const char *saved_tokp = p->lex.ptok;
13656

13661 p->delayed.token = Qnil;
13662 p->ruby_sourceline = saved_line;
13663 p->lex.ptok = saved_tokp;
13664}

13687static void
13688token_info_setup(token_info *ptinfo, const char *ptr, const rb_code_location_t *loc)
13689{
13690 int column = 1, nonspc = 0, i;
13691 for (i = 0; i < loc->beg_pos.column; i++, ptr++) {
13692 if (*ptr == '\t') {
13693 column = (((column - 1) / TAB_WIDTH) + 1) * TAB_WIDTH;
13694 }
13695 column++;
13696 if (*ptr != ' ' && *ptr != '\t') {
13697 nonspc = 1;
13698 }
13699 }
13700
13701 ptinfo->beg = loc->beg_pos;
13702 ptinfo->indent = column;
13703 ptinfo->nonspc = nonspc;
13704}
13705
13706static void
13707token_info_push(struct parser_params *p, const char *token, const rb_code_location_t *loc)
13708{
13709 token_info *ptinfo;
13710
13711 if (!p->token_info_enabled) return;
13712 ptinfo = ALLOC(token_info);
13713 ptinfo->token = token;
13714 ptinfo->next = p->token_info;
13715 token_info_setup(ptinfo, p->lex.pbeg, loc);
13716
13717 p->token_info = ptinfo;
13718}
13719
13720static void
13721token_info_pop(struct parser_params *p, const char *token, const rb_code_location_t *loc)
13722{
13723 token_info *ptinfo_beg = p->token_info;
13724
13725 if (!ptinfo_beg) return;
13726 p->token_info = ptinfo_beg->next;
13727
13728 /* indentation check of matched keywords (begin..end, if..end, etc.) */
13729 token_info_warn(p, token, ptinfo_beg, 1, loc);
13730 ruby_sized_xfree(ptinfo_beg, sizeof(*ptinfo_beg));
13731}
13732
13733static void
13734token_info_drop(struct parser_params *p, const char *token, rb_code_position_t beg_pos)
13735{
13736 token_info *ptinfo_beg = p->token_info;
13737
13738 if (!ptinfo_beg) return;
13739 p->token_info = ptinfo_beg->next;
13740
13741 if (ptinfo_beg->beg.lineno != beg_pos.lineno ||
13742 ptinfo_beg->beg.column != beg_pos.column ||
13743 strcmp(ptinfo_beg->token, token)) {
13744 compile_error(p, "token position mismatch: %d:%d:%s expected but %d:%d:%s",
13745 beg_pos.lineno, beg_pos.column, token,
13746 ptinfo_beg->beg.lineno, ptinfo_beg->beg.column,
13747 ptinfo_beg->token);
13748 }
13749
13750 ruby_sized_xfree(ptinfo_beg, sizeof(*ptinfo_beg));
13751}
13752
13753static void
13754token_info_warn(struct parser_params *p, const char *token, token_info *ptinfo_beg, int same, const rb_code_location_t *loc)
13755{
13756 token_info ptinfo_end_body, *ptinfo_end = &ptinfo_end_body;
13757 if (!p->token_info_enabled) return;
13758 if (!ptinfo_beg) return;
13759 token_info_setup(ptinfo_end, p->lex.pbeg, loc);
13760 if (ptinfo_beg->beg.lineno == ptinfo_end->beg.lineno) return; /* ignore one-line block */
13761 if (ptinfo_beg->nonspc || ptinfo_end->nonspc) return; /* ignore keyword in the middle of a line */
13762 if (ptinfo_beg->indent == ptinfo_end->indent) return; /* the indents are matched */
13763 if (!same && ptinfo_beg->indent < ptinfo_end->indent) return;
13764 rb_warn3L(ptinfo_end->beg.lineno,
13765 "mismatched indentations at '%s' with '%s' at %d",
13766 WARN_S(token), WARN_S(ptinfo_beg->token), WARN_I(ptinfo_beg->beg.lineno));
13767}
13768
13769static int
13770parser_precise_mbclen(struct parser_params *p, const char *ptr)
13771{
13772 int len = rb_enc_precise_mbclen(ptr, p->lex.pend, p->enc);
13773 if (!MBCLEN_CHARFOUND_P(len)) {
13774 compile_error(p, "invalid multibyte char (%s)", rb_enc_name(p->enc));
13775 return -1;
13776 }
13777 return len;
13778}

13793 }
13794 else {
13795 return;

13798}

13825
13826static void
13827ruby_show_error_line(VALUE errbuf, const YYLTYPE *yylloc, int lineno, VALUE str)
13828{
13829 VALUE mesg;
13830 const int max_line_margin = 30;
13831 const char *ptr, *ptr_end, *pt, *pb;
13832 const char *pre = "", *post = "", *pend;
13833 const char *code = "", *caret = "";
13834 const char *lim;
13835 const char *const pbeg = RSTRING_PTR(str);
13836 char *buf;
13837 long len;
13838 int i;
13839
13840 if (!yylloc) return;
13841 pend = RSTRING_END(str);
13842 if (pend > pbeg && pend[-1] == '\n') {
13843 if (--pend > pbeg && pend[-1] == '\r') --pend;
13844 }
13845
13846 pt = pend;
13847 if (lineno == yylloc->end_pos.lineno &&
13848 (pend - pbeg) > yylloc->end_pos.column) {
13849 pt = pbeg + yylloc->end_pos.column;
13850 }
13851
13852 ptr = ptr_end = pt;
13853 lim = ptr - pbeg > max_line_margin ? ptr - max_line_margin : pbeg;
13854 while ((lim < ptr) && (*(ptr-1) != '\n')) ptr--;
13855
13856 lim = pend - ptr_end > max_line_margin ? ptr_end + max_line_margin : pend;
13857 while ((ptr_end < lim) && (*ptr_end != '\n') && (*ptr_end != '\r')) ptr_end++;
13858
13859 len = ptr_end - ptr;
13860 if (len > 4) {
13861 if (ptr > pbeg) {
13862 ptr = rb_enc_prev_char(pbeg, ptr, pt, rb_enc_get(str));
13863 if (ptr > pbeg) pre = "...";
13864 }
13865 if (ptr_end < pend) {
13866 ptr_end = rb_enc_prev_char(pt, ptr_end, pend, rb_enc_get(str));
13867 if (ptr_end < pend) post = "...";
13868 }
13869 }
13870 pb = pbeg;
13871 if (lineno == yylloc->beg_pos.lineno) {
13872 pb += yylloc->beg_pos.column;
13873 if (pb > pt) pb = pt;
13874 }
13875 if (pb < ptr) pb = ptr;
13876 if (len <= 4 && yylloc->beg_pos.lineno == yylloc->end_pos.lineno) {
13877 return;
13878 }
13879 if (RTEST(errbuf)) {
13880 mesg = rb_attr_get(errbuf, idMesg);
13881 if (RSTRING_LEN(mesg) > 0 && *(RSTRING_END(mesg)-1) != '\n')
13882 rb_str_cat_cstr(mesg, "\n");
13883 }
13884 else {
13885 mesg = rb_enc_str_new(0, 0, rb_enc_get(str));
13886 }
13887 if (!errbuf && rb_stderr_tty_p()) {
13888#define CSI_BEGIN "\033["
13889#define CSI_SGR "m"
13890 rb_str_catf(mesg,
13891 CSI_BEGIN""CSI_SGR"%s" /* pre */
13892 CSI_BEGIN"1"CSI_SGR"%.*s"
13893 CSI_BEGIN"1;4"CSI_SGR"%.*s"
13894 CSI_BEGIN";1"CSI_SGR"%.*s"
13895 CSI_BEGIN""CSI_SGR"%s" /* post */
13896 "\n",
13897 pre,
13898 (int)(pb - ptr), ptr,
13899 (int)(pt - pb), pb,
13900 (int)(ptr_end - pt), pt,
13901 post);
13902 }
13903 else {
13904 char *p2;
13905
13906 len = ptr_end - ptr;
13907 lim = pt < pend ? pt : pend;
13908 i = (int)(lim - ptr);
13909 buf = ALLOCA_N(char, i+2);
13910 code = ptr;
13911 caret = p2 = buf;
13912 if (ptr <= pb) {
13913 while (ptr < pb) {
13914 *p2++ = *ptr++ == '\t' ? '\t' : ' ';
13915 }
13916 *p2++ = '^';
13917 ptr++;
13918 }
13919 if (lim > ptr) {
13920 memset(p2, '~', (lim - ptr));
13921 p2 += (lim - ptr);
13922 }
13923 *p2 = '\0';
13924 rb_str_catf(mesg, "%s%.*s%s\n""%s%s\n",
13925 pre, (int)len, code, post,
13926 pre, caret);
13927 }
13928 if (!errbuf) rb_write_error_str(mesg);
13929}
13930#else
13931static int
13932parser_yyerror(struct parser_params *p, const YYLTYPE *yylloc, const char *msg)
13933{
13934 const char *pcur = 0, *ptok = 0;
13935 if (p->ruby_sourceline == yylloc->beg_pos.lineno &&
13936 p->ruby_sourceline == yylloc->end_pos.lineno) {
13937 pcur = p->lex.pcur;
13938 ptok = p->lex.ptok;
13939 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pbeg + yylloc->beg_pos.column;
13940 p->lex.pcur = p->lex.pbeg + yylloc->end_pos.column;
13941 }
13942 parser_yyerror0(p, msg);
13943 if (pcur) {
13944 p->lex.ptok = ptok;
13945 p->lex.pcur = pcur;
13946 }
13947 return 0;
13948}

13961}

13965static int
13966vtable_size(const struct vtable *tbl)
13967{
13968 if (!DVARS_TERMINAL_P(tbl)) {
13969 return tbl->pos;
13970 }
13971 else {
13972 return 0;
13973 }
13974}

13976
13977static struct vtable *
13978vtable_alloc_gen(struct parser_params *p, int line, struct vtable *prev)
13979{
13980 struct vtable *tbl = ALLOC(struct vtable);
13981 tbl->pos = 0;
13982 tbl->capa = 8;
13983 tbl->tbl = ALLOC_N(ID, tbl->capa);
13984 tbl->prev = prev;
13985#ifndef RIPPER
13986 if (p->debug) {
13987 rb_parser_printf(p, "vtable_alloc:%d: %p\n", line, (void *)tbl);
13988 }
13989#endif
13990 return tbl;
13991}
13992#define vtable_alloc(prev) vtable_alloc_gen(p, __LINE__, prev)
13993
13994static void
13995vtable_free_gen(struct parser_params *p, int line, const char *name,
13996 struct vtable *tbl)
13997{
13998#ifndef RIPPER
13999 if (p->debug) {
14000 rb_parser_printf(p, "vtable_free:%d: %s(%p)\n", line, name, (void *)tbl);
14001 }
14002#endif
14003 if (!DVARS_TERMINAL_P(tbl)) {
14004 if (tbl->tbl) {
14005 ruby_sized_xfree(tbl->tbl, tbl->capa * sizeof(ID));
14006 }
14007 ruby_sized_xfree(tbl, sizeof(*tbl));
14008 }
14009}
14010#define vtable_free(tbl) vtable_free_gen(p, __LINE__, #tbl, tbl)
14011
14012static void
14013vtable_add_gen(struct parser_params *p, int line, const char *name,
14014 struct vtable *tbl, ID id)
14015{
14016#ifndef RIPPER
14017 if (p->debug) {
14018 rb_parser_printf(p, "vtable_add:%d: %s(%p), %s\n",
14019 line, name, (void *)tbl, rb_id2name(id));
14020 }
14021#endif
14022 if (DVARS_TERMINAL_P(tbl)) {
14023 rb_parser_fatal(p, "vtable_add: vtable is not allocated (%p)", (void *)tbl);
14024 return;
14025 }
14026 if (tbl->pos == tbl->capa) {
14027 tbl->capa = tbl->capa * 2;
14028 SIZED_REALLOC_N(tbl->tbl, ID, tbl->capa, tbl->pos);
14029 }
14030 tbl->tbl[tbl->pos++] = id;
14031}
14032#define vtable_add(tbl, id) vtable_add_gen(p, __LINE__, #tbl, tbl, id)
14033
14034#ifndef RIPPER
14035static void
14036vtable_pop_gen(struct parser_params *p, int line, const char *name,
14037 struct vtable *tbl, int n)
14038{
14039 if (p->debug) {
14040 rb_parser_printf(p, "vtable_pop:%d: %s(%p), %d\n",
14041 line, name, (void *)tbl, n);
14042 }
14043 if (tbl->pos < n) {
14044 rb_parser_fatal(p, "vtable_pop: unreachable (%d < %d)", tbl->pos, n);
14045 return;
14046 }
14047 tbl->pos -= n;
14048}
14049#define vtable_pop(tbl, n) vtable_pop_gen(p, __LINE__, #tbl, tbl, n)
14050#endif
14051
14052static int
14053vtable_included(const struct vtable * tbl, ID id)
14054{
14055 int i;
14056
14057 if (!DVARS_TERMINAL_P(tbl)) {
14058 for (i = 0; i < tbl->pos; i++) {
14059 if (tbl->tbl[i] == id) {
14060 return i+1;
14061 }
14062 }
14063 }
14064 return 0;
14065}

14071
14072static VALUE
14073debug_lines(VALUE fname)
14074{
14075 ID script_lines;
14076 CONST_ID(script_lines, "SCRIPT_LINES__");
14077 if (rb_const_defined_at(rb_cObject, script_lines)) {
14078 VALUE hash = rb_const_get_at(rb_cObject, script_lines);
14079 if (RB_TYPE_P(hash, T_HASH)) {
14080 VALUE lines = rb_ary_new();
14081 rb_hash_aset(hash, fname, lines);
14082 return lines;
14083 }
14084 }
14085 return 0;
14086}

14088static int
14089e_option_supplied(struct parser_params *p)
14090{
14091 return strcmp(p->ruby_sourcefile, "-e") == 0;
14092}
14093
14094static VALUE
14095yycompile0(VALUE arg)
14096{
14097 int n;
14098 NODE *tree;
14099 struct parser_params *p = (struct parser_params *)arg;
14100 VALUE cov = Qfalse;
14101
14102 if (!compile_for_eval && !NIL_P(p->ruby_sourcefile_string)) {
14103 p->debug_lines = debug_lines(p->ruby_sourcefile_string);
14104 if (p->debug_lines && p->ruby_sourceline > 0) {
14105 VALUE str = rb_default_rs;
14106 n = p->ruby_sourceline;
14107 do {
14108 rb_ary_push(p->debug_lines, str);
14109 } while (--n);
14110 }
14111
14112 if (!e_option_supplied(p)) {
14113 cov = Qtrue;
14114 }
14115 }
14116
14117 if (p->keep_script_lines || ruby_vm_keep_script_lines) {
14118 if (!p->debug_lines) {
14119 p->debug_lines = rb_ary_new();
14120 }
14121
14122 RB_OBJ_WRITE(p->ast, &p->ast->body.script_lines, p->debug_lines);
14123 }
14124
14125 parser_prepare(p);
14126#define RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_HOOK(name) \
14127 if (RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_##name##_ENABLED()) { \
14128 RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_##name(p->ruby_sourcefile, p->ruby_sourceline); \
14129 }
14130 RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_HOOK(BEGIN);
14131 n = yyparse(p);
14132 RUBY_DTRACE_PARSE_HOOK(END);
14133 p->debug_lines = 0;
14134
14135 p->lex.strterm = 0;
14136 p->lex.pcur = p->lex.pbeg = p->lex.pend = 0;
14137 p->lex.prevline = p->lex.lastline = p->lex.nextline = 0;
14138 if (n || p->error_p) {
14139 VALUE mesg = p->error_buffer;
14140 if (!mesg) {
14141 mesg = rb_class_new_instance(0, 0, rb_eSyntaxError);
14142 }
14143 rb_set_errinfo(mesg);
14144 return FALSE;
14145 }
14146 tree = p->eval_tree;
14147 if (!tree) {
14148 tree = NEW_NIL(&NULL_LOC);
14149 }
14150 else {
14151 VALUE opt = p->compile_option;
14152 NODE *prelude;
14153 NODE *body = parser_append_options(p, tree->nd_body);
14154 if (!opt) opt = rb_obj_hide(rb_ident_hash_new());
14155 rb_hash_aset(opt, rb_sym_intern_ascii_cstr("coverage_enabled"), cov);
14156 prelude = block_append(p, p->eval_tree_begin, body);
14157 tree->nd_body = prelude;
14158 RB_OBJ_WRITE(p->ast, &p->ast->body.compile_option, opt);
14159 }
14160 p->ast->body.root = tree;
14161 if (!p->ast->body.script_lines) p->ast->body.script_lines = INT2FIX(p->line_count);
14162 return TRUE;
14163}
14164
14165static rb_ast_t *
14166yycompile(VALUE vparser, struct parser_params *p, VALUE fname, int line)
14167{
14168 rb_ast_t *ast;
14169 if (NIL_P(fname)) {
14170 p->ruby_sourcefile_string = Qnil;
14171 p->ruby_sourcefile = "(none)";
14172 }
14173 else {
14174 p->ruby_sourcefile_string = rb_fstring(fname);
14175 p->ruby_sourcefile = StringValueCStr(fname);
14176 }
14177 p->ruby_sourceline = line - 1;
14178
14179 p->lvtbl = NULL;
14180
14181 p->ast = ast = rb_ast_new();
14182 rb_suppress_tracing(yycompile0, (VALUE)p);
14183 p->ast = 0;
14184 RB_GC_GUARD(vparser); /* prohibit tail call optimization */
14185
14186 while (p->lvtbl) {
14187 local_pop(p);
14188 }
14189
14190 return ast;
14191}
14192#endif /* !RIPPER */

14194static rb_encoding *
14195must_be_ascii_compatible(VALUE s)
14196{
14197 rb_encoding *enc = rb_enc_get(s);
14198 if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
14199 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "invalid source encoding");
14200 }
14201 return enc;
14202}
14203
14204static VALUE
14205lex_get_str(struct parser_params *p, VALUE s)
14206{
14207 char *beg, *end, *start;
14208 long len;
14209
14210 beg = RSTRING_PTR(s);
14211 len = RSTRING_LEN(s);
14212 start = beg;
14213 if (p->lex.gets_.ptr) {
14214 if (len == p->lex.gets_.ptr) return Qnil;
14215 beg += p->lex.gets_.ptr;
14216 len -= p->lex.gets_.ptr;
14217 }
14218 end = memchr(beg, '\n', len);
14219 if (end) len = ++end - beg;
14220 p->lex.gets_.ptr += len;
14221 return rb_str_subseq(s, beg - start, len);
14222}
14223
14224static VALUE
14225lex_getline(struct parser_params *p)
14226{
14227 VALUE line = (*p->lex.gets)(p, p->lex.input);
14228 if (NIL_P(line)) return line;
14229 must_be_ascii_compatible(line);
14230 if (RB_OBJ_FROZEN(line)) line = rb_str_dup(line); // needed for RubyVM::AST.of because script_lines in iseq is deep-frozen
14231#ifndef RIPPER
14232 if (p->debug_lines) {
14233 rb_enc_associate(line, p->enc);
14234 rb_ary_push(p->debug_lines, line);
14235 }
14236#endif
14237 p->line_count++;
14238 return line;
14239}

14245parser_compile_string(VALUE vparser, VALUE fname, VALUE s, int line)
14246{
14247 struct parser_params *p;

14250

14252 p->lex.gets_.ptr = 0;
14253 p->lex.input = rb_str_new_frozen(s);
14254 p->lex.pbeg = p->lex.pcur = p->lex.pend = 0;
14255
14256 return yycompile(vparser, p, fname, line);
14257}

14315
14316#define STR_FUNC_ESCAPE 0x01
14317#define STR_FUNC_EXPAND 0x02
14318#define STR_FUNC_REGEXP 0x04
14319#define STR_FUNC_QWORDS 0x08
14320#define STR_FUNC_SYMBOL 0x10
14321#define STR_FUNC_INDENT 0x20
14322#define STR_FUNC_LABEL 0x40
14323#define STR_FUNC_LIST 0x4000
14324#define STR_FUNC_TERM 0x8000
14325
14326enum string_type {
14327 str_label = STR_FUNC_LABEL,
14328 str_squote = (0),
14329 str_dquote = (STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
14330 str_xquote = (STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
14331 str_regexp = (STR_FUNC_REGEXP|STR_FUNC_ESCAPE|STR_FUNC_EXPAND),
14332 str_sword = (STR_FUNC_QWORDS|STR_FUNC_LIST),
14333 str_dword = (STR_FUNC_QWORDS|STR_FUNC_EXPAND|STR_FUNC_LIST),
14334 str_ssym = (STR_FUNC_SYMBOL),
14335 str_dsym = (STR_FUNC_SYMBOL|STR_FUNC_EXPAND)
14336};
14337
14338static VALUE
14339parser_str_new(const char *ptr, long len, rb_encoding *enc, int func, rb_encoding *enc0)
14340{
14341 VALUE str;
14342
14343 str = rb_enc_str_new(ptr, len, enc);
14344 if (!(func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) && rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
14345 if (rb_enc_str_coderange(str) == ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) {
14346 }
14347 else if (enc0 == rb_usascii_encoding() && enc != rb_utf8_encoding()) {
14348 rb_enc_associate(str, rb_ascii8bit_encoding());
14349 }
14350 }
14351
14352 return str;
14353}
14354
14355#define lex_goto_eol(p) ((p)->lex.pcur = (p)->lex.pend)
14356#define lex_eol_p(p) ((p)->lex.pcur >= (p)->lex.pend)
14357#define lex_eol_n_p(p,n) ((p)->lex.pcur+(n) >= (p)->lex.pend)
14358#define peek(p,c) peek_n(p, (c), 0)
14359#define peek_n(p,c,n) (!lex_eol_n_p(p, n) && (c) == (unsigned char)(p)->lex.pcur[n])
14360#define peekc(p) peekc_n(p, 0)
14361#define peekc_n(p,n) (lex_eol_n_p(p, n) ? -1 : (unsigned char)(p)->lex.pcur[n])
14362
14363#ifdef RIPPER
14364static void
14365add_delayed_token(struct parser_params *p, const char *tok, const char *end)
14366{
14367 if (tok < end) {
14368 if (!has_delayed_token(p)) {
14369 p->delayed.token = rb_str_buf_new(end - tok);
14370 rb_enc_associate(p->delayed.token, p->enc);
14371 p->delayed.line = p->ruby_sourceline;
14372 p->delayed.col = rb_long2int(tok - p->lex.pbeg);
14373 }
14374 rb_str_buf_cat(p->delayed.token, tok, end - tok);
14375 p->lex.ptok = end;
14376 }
14377}
14378#else
14379#define add_delayed_token(p, tok, end) ((void)(tok), (void)(end))
14380#endif
14381
14382static int
14383nextline(struct parser_params *p)
14384{
14385 VALUE v = p->lex.nextline;
14386 p->lex.nextline = 0;
14387 if (!v) {
14388 if (p->eofp)
14389 return -1;
14390
14391 if (p->lex.pend > p->lex.pbeg && *(p->lex.pend-1) != '\n') {
14392 goto end_of_input;
14393 }
14394
14395 if (!p->lex.input || NIL_P(v = lex_getline(p))) {
14396 end_of_input:
14397 p->eofp = 1;
14398 lex_goto_eol(p);
14399 return -1;
14400 }
14401 p->cr_seen = FALSE;
14402 }
14403 else if (NIL_P(v)) {
14404 /* after here-document without terminator */
14405 goto end_of_input;
14406 }
14407 add_delayed_token(p, p->lex.ptok, p->lex.pend);
14408 if (p->heredoc_end > 0) {
14409 p->ruby_sourceline = p->heredoc_end;
14410 p->heredoc_end = 0;
14411 }
14412 p->ruby_sourceline++;
14413 p->lex.pbeg = p->lex.pcur = RSTRING_PTR(v);
14414 p->lex.pend = p->lex.pcur + RSTRING_LEN(v);
14415 token_flush(p);
14416 p->lex.prevline = p->lex.lastline;
14417 p->lex.lastline = v;
14418 return 0;
14419}
14420
14421static int
14422parser_cr(struct parser_params *p, int c)
14423{
14424 if (peek(p, '\n')) {
14425 p->lex.pcur++;
14426 c = '\n';
14427 }
14428 return c;
14429}
14430
14431static inline int
14432nextc(struct parser_params *p)
14433{
14434 int c;
14435
14436 if (UNLIKELY((p->lex.pcur == p->lex.pend) || p->eofp || RTEST(p->lex.nextline))) {
14437 if (nextline(p)) return -1;
14438 }
14439 c = (unsigned char)*p->lex.pcur++;
14440 if (UNLIKELY(c == '\r')) {
14441 c = parser_cr(p, c);
14442 }
14443
14444 return c;
14445}
14446
14447static void
14448pushback(struct parser_params *p, int c)
14449{
14450 if (c == -1) return;
14451 p->lex.pcur--;
14452 if (p->lex.pcur > p->lex.pbeg && p->lex.pcur[0] == '\n' && p->lex.pcur[-1] == '\r') {
14453 p->lex.pcur--;
14454 }
14455}
14456
14457#define was_bol(p) ((p)->lex.pcur == (p)->lex.pbeg + 1)
14458
14459#define tokfix(p) ((p)->tokenbuf[(p)->tokidx]='\0')
14460#define tok(p) (p)->tokenbuf
14461#define toklen(p) (p)->tokidx
14462
14463static int
14464looking_at_eol_p(struct parser_params *p)
14465{
14466 const char *ptr = p->lex.pcur;
14467 while (ptr < p->lex.pend) {
14468 int c = (unsigned char)*ptr++;
14469 int eol = (c == '\n' || c == '#');
14470 if (eol || !ISSPACE(c)) {
14471 return eol;
14472 }
14473 }
14474 return TRUE;
14475}
14476
14477static char*
14478newtok(struct parser_params *p)
14479{
14480 p->tokidx = 0;
14481 p->tokline = p->ruby_sourceline;
14482 if (!p->tokenbuf) {
14483 p->toksiz = 60;
14484 p->tokenbuf = ALLOC_N(char, 60);
14485 }
14486 if (p->toksiz > 4096) {
14487 p->toksiz = 60;
14488 REALLOC_N(p->tokenbuf, char, 60);
14489 }
14490 return p->tokenbuf;
14491}
14492
14493static char *
14494tokspace(struct parser_params *p, int n)
14495{
14496 p->tokidx += n;
14497
14498 if (p->tokidx >= p->toksiz) {
14499 do {p->toksiz *= 2;} while (p->toksiz < p->tokidx);
14500 REALLOC_N(p->tokenbuf, char, p->toksiz);
14501 }
14502 return &p->tokenbuf[p->tokidx-n];
14503}
14504
14505static void
14506tokadd(struct parser_params *p, int c)
14507{
14508 p->tokenbuf[p->tokidx++] = (char)c;
14509 if (p->tokidx >= p->toksiz) {
14510 p->toksiz *= 2;
14511 REALLOC_N(p->tokenbuf, char, p->toksiz);
14512 }
14513}
14514
14515static int
14516tok_hex(struct parser_params *p, size_t *numlen)
14517{
14518 int c;
14519
14520 c = scan_hex(p->lex.pcur, 2, numlen);
14521 if (!*numlen) {
14522 yyerror0("invalid hex escape");
14523 token_flush(p);
14524 return 0;
14525 }
14526 p->lex.pcur += *numlen;
14527 return c;
14528}
14529
14530#define tokcopy(p, n) memcpy(tokspace(p, n), (p)->lex.pcur - (n), (n))
14531
14532static int
14533escaped_control_code(int c)
14534{
14535 int c2 = 0;
14536 switch (c) {
14537 case ' ':
14538 c2 = 's';
14539 break;
14540 case '\n':
14541 c2 = 'n';
14542 break;
14543 case '\t':
14544 c2 = 't';
14545 break;
14546 case '\v':
14547 c2 = 'v';
14548 break;
14549 case '\r':
14550 c2 = 'r';
14551 break;
14552 case '\f':
14553 c2 = 'f';
14554 break;
14555 }
14556 return c2;
14557}
14558
14559#define WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c, prefix) \
14560 rb_warn1("invalid character syntax; use "prefix"\\%c", WARN_I(c2))
14561
14562static int
14563tokadd_codepoint(struct parser_params *p, rb_encoding **encp,
14564 int regexp_literal, int wide)
14565{
14566 size_t numlen;
14567 int codepoint = scan_hex(p->lex.pcur, wide ? p->lex.pend - p->lex.pcur : 4, &numlen);
14568 literal_flush(p, p->lex.pcur);
14569 p->lex.pcur += numlen;
14570 if (p->lex.strterm == NULL ||
14571 (p->lex.strterm->flags & STRTERM_HEREDOC) ||
14572 (p->lex.strterm->u.literal.u1.func != str_regexp)) {
14573 if (wide ? (numlen == 0 || numlen > 6) : (numlen < 4)) {
14574 yyerror0("invalid Unicode escape");
14575 return wide && numlen > 0;
14576 }
14577 if (codepoint > 0x10ffff) {
14578 yyerror0("invalid Unicode codepoint (too large)");
14579 return wide;
14580 }
14581 if ((codepoint & 0xfffff800) == 0xd800) {
14582 yyerror0("invalid Unicode codepoint");
14583 return wide;
14584 }
14585 }
14586 if (regexp_literal) {
14587 tokcopy(p, (int)numlen);
14588 }
14589 else if (codepoint >= 0x80) {
14590 rb_encoding *utf8 = rb_utf8_encoding();
14591 if (*encp && utf8 != *encp) {
14592 YYLTYPE loc = RUBY_INIT_YYLLOC();
14593 compile_error(p, "UTF-8 mixed within %s source", rb_enc_name(*encp));
14594 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
14595 return wide;
14596 }
14597 *encp = utf8;
14598 tokaddmbc(p, codepoint, *encp);
14599 }
14600 else {
14601 tokadd(p, codepoint);
14602 }
14603 return TRUE;
14604}
14605
14606/* return value is for ?\u3042 */
14607static void
14608tokadd_utf8(struct parser_params *p, rb_encoding **encp,
14609 int term, int symbol_literal, int regexp_literal)
14610{
14611 /*
14612 * If `term` is not -1, then we allow multiple codepoints in \u{}
14613 * upto `term` byte, otherwise we're parsing a character literal.
14614 * And then add the codepoints to the current token.
14615 */
14616 static const char multiple_codepoints[] = "Multiple codepoints at single character literal";
14617
14618 const int open_brace = '{', close_brace = '}';
14619
14620 if (regexp_literal) { tokadd(p, '\\'); tokadd(p, 'u'); }
14621
14622 if (peek(p, open_brace)) { /* handle \u{...} form */
14623 const char *second = NULL;
14624 int c, last = nextc(p);
14625 if (p->lex.pcur >= p->lex.pend) goto unterminated;
14626 while (ISSPACE(c = *p->lex.pcur) && ++p->lex.pcur < p->lex.pend);
14627 while (c != close_brace) {
14628 if (c == term) goto unterminated;
14629 if (second == multiple_codepoints)
14630 second = p->lex.pcur;
14631 if (regexp_literal) tokadd(p, last);
14632 if (!tokadd_codepoint(p, encp, regexp_literal, TRUE)) {
14633 break;
14634 }
14635 while (ISSPACE(c = *p->lex.pcur)) {
14636 if (++p->lex.pcur >= p->lex.pend) goto unterminated;
14637 last = c;
14638 }
14639 if (term == -1 && !second)
14640 second = multiple_codepoints;
14641 }
14642
14643 if (c != close_brace) {
14644 unterminated:
14645 token_flush(p);
14646 yyerror0("unterminated Unicode escape");
14647 return;
14648 }
14649 if (second && second != multiple_codepoints) {
14650 const char *pcur = p->lex.pcur;
14651 p->lex.pcur = second;
14652 dispatch_scan_event(p, tSTRING_CONTENT);
14653 token_flush(p);
14654 p->lex.pcur = pcur;
14655 yyerror0(multiple_codepoints);
14656 token_flush(p);
14657 }
14658
14659 if (regexp_literal) tokadd(p, close_brace);
14660 nextc(p);
14661 }
14662 else { /* handle \uxxxx form */
14663 if (!tokadd_codepoint(p, encp, regexp_literal, FALSE)) {
14664 token_flush(p);
14665 return;
14666 }
14667 }
14668}
14669
14670#define ESCAPE_CONTROL 1
14671#define ESCAPE_META 2
14672
14673static int
14674read_escape(struct parser_params *p, int flags, rb_encoding **encp)
14675{
14676 int c;
14677 size_t numlen;
14678
14679 switch (c = nextc(p)) {
14680 case '\\': /* Backslash */
14681 return c;
14682
14683 case 'n': /* newline */
14684 return '\n';
14685
14686 case 't': /* horizontal tab */
14687 return '\t';
14688
14689 case 'r': /* carriage-return */
14690 return '\r';
14691
14692 case 'f': /* form-feed */
14693 return '\f';
14694
14695 case 'v': /* vertical tab */
14696 return '\13';
14697
14698 case 'a': /* alarm(bell) */
14699 return '\007';
14700
14701 case 'e': /* escape */
14702 return 033;
14703
14704 case '0': case '1': case '2': case '3': /* octal constant */
14705 case '4': case '5': case '6': case '7':
14706 pushback(p, c);
14707 c = scan_oct(p->lex.pcur, 3, &numlen);
14708 p->lex.pcur += numlen;
14709 return c;
14710
14711 case 'x': /* hex constant */
14712 c = tok_hex(p, &numlen);
14713 if (numlen == 0) return 0;
14714 return c;
14715
14716 case 'b': /* backspace */
14717 return '\010';
14718
14719 case 's': /* space */
14720 return ' ';
14721
14722 case 'M':
14723 if (flags & ESCAPE_META) goto eof;
14724 if ((c = nextc(p)) != '-') {
14725 goto eof;
14726 }
14727 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '\\') {
14728 switch (peekc(p)) {
14729 case 'u': case 'U':
14730 nextc(p);
14731 goto eof;
14732 }
14733 return read_escape(p, flags|ESCAPE_META, encp) | 0x80;
14734 }
14735 else if (c == -1 || !ISASCII(c)) goto eof;
14736 else {
14737 int c2 = escaped_control_code(c);
14738 if (c2) {
14739 if (ISCNTRL(c) || !(flags & ESCAPE_CONTROL)) {
14740 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "\\M-");
14741 }
14742 else {
14743 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "\\C-\\M-");
14744 }
14745 }
14746 else if (ISCNTRL(c)) goto eof;
14747 return ((c & 0xff) | 0x80);
14748 }
14749
14750 case 'C':
14751 if ((c = nextc(p)) != '-') {
14752 goto eof;
14753 }
14754 case 'c':
14755 if (flags & ESCAPE_CONTROL) goto eof;
14756 if ((c = nextc(p))== '\\') {
14757 switch (peekc(p)) {
14758 case 'u': case 'U':
14759 nextc(p);
14760 goto eof;
14761 }
14762 c = read_escape(p, flags|ESCAPE_CONTROL, encp);
14763 }
14764 else if (c == '?')
14765 return 0177;
14766 else if (c == -1 || !ISASCII(c)) goto eof;
14767 else {
14768 int c2 = escaped_control_code(c);
14769 if (c2) {
14770 if (ISCNTRL(c)) {
14771 if (flags & ESCAPE_META) {
14772 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "\\M-");
14773 }
14774 else {
14775 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "");
14776 }
14777 }
14778 else {
14779 if (flags & ESCAPE_META) {
14780 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "\\M-\\C-");
14781 }
14782 else {
14783 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "\\C-");
14784 }
14785 }
14786 }
14787 else if (ISCNTRL(c)) goto eof;
14788 }
14789 return c & 0x9f;
14790
14791 eof:
14792 case -1:
14793 yyerror0("Invalid escape character syntax");
14794 token_flush(p);
14795 return '\0';
14796
14797 default:
14798 return c;
14799 }
14800}
14801
14802static void
14803tokaddmbc(struct parser_params *p, int c, rb_encoding *enc)
14804{
14805 int len = rb_enc_codelen(c, enc);
14806 rb_enc_mbcput(c, tokspace(p, len), enc);
14807}
14808
14809static int
14810tokadd_escape(struct parser_params *p, rb_encoding **encp)
14811{
14812 int c;
14813 size_t numlen;
14814
14815 switch (c = nextc(p)) {
14816 case '\n':
14817 return 0; /* just ignore */
14818
14819 case '0': case '1': case '2': case '3': /* octal constant */
14820 case '4': case '5': case '6': case '7':
14821 {
14822 ruby_scan_oct(--p->lex.pcur, 3, &numlen);
14823 if (numlen == 0) goto eof;
14824 p->lex.pcur += numlen;
14825 tokcopy(p, (int)numlen + 1);
14826 }
14827 return 0;
14828
14829 case 'x': /* hex constant */
14830 {
14831 tok_hex(p, &numlen);
14832 if (numlen == 0) return -1;
14833 tokcopy(p, (int)numlen + 2);
14834 }
14835 return 0;
14836
14837 eof:
14838 case -1:
14839 yyerror0("Invalid escape character syntax");
14840 token_flush(p);
14841 return -1;
14842
14843 default:
14844 tokadd(p, '\\');
14845 tokadd(p, c);
14846 }
14847 return 0;
14848}
14849
14850static int
14851regx_options(struct parser_params *p)
14852{
14853 int kcode = 0;
14854 int kopt = 0;
14855 int options = 0;
14856 int c, opt, kc;
14857
14858 newtok(p);
14859 while (c = nextc(p), ISALPHA(c)) {
14860 if (c == 'o') {
14861 options |= RE_OPTION_ONCE;
14862 }
14863 else if (rb_char_to_option_kcode(c, &opt, &kc)) {
14864 if (kc >= 0) {
14865 if (kc != rb_ascii8bit_encindex()) kcode = c;
14866 kopt = opt;
14867 }
14868 else {
14869 options |= opt;
14870 }
14871 }
14872 else {
14873 tokadd(p, c);
14874 }
14875 }
14876 options |= kopt;
14877 pushback(p, c);
14878 if (toklen(p)) {
14879 YYLTYPE loc = RUBY_INIT_YYLLOC();
14880 tokfix(p);
14881 compile_error(p, "unknown regexp option%s - %*s",
14882 toklen(p) > 1 ? "s" : "", toklen(p), tok(p));
14883 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
14884 }
14885 return options | RE_OPTION_ENCODING(kcode);
14886}
14887
14888static int
14889tokadd_mbchar(struct parser_params *p, int c)
14890{
14891 int len = parser_precise_mbclen(p, p->lex.pcur-1);
14892 if (len < 0) return -1;
14893 tokadd(p, c);
14894 p->lex.pcur += --len;
14895 if (len > 0) tokcopy(p, len);
14896 return c;
14897}
14898
14899static inline int
14900simple_re_meta(int c)
14901{
14902 switch (c) {
14903 case '$': case '*': case '+': case '.':
14904 case '?': case '^': case '|':
14905 case ')': case ']': case '}': case '>':
14906 return TRUE;
14907 default:
14908 return FALSE;
14909 }
14910}
14911
14912static int
14913parser_update_heredoc_indent(struct parser_params *p, int c)
14914{
14915 if (p->heredoc_line_indent == -1) {
14916 if (c == '\n') p->heredoc_line_indent = 0;
14917 }
14918 else {
14919 if (c == ' ') {
14920 p->heredoc_line_indent++;
14921 return TRUE;
14922 }
14923 else if (c == '\t') {
14924 int w = (p->heredoc_line_indent / TAB_WIDTH) + 1;
14925 p->heredoc_line_indent = w * TAB_WIDTH;
14926 return TRUE;
14927 }
14928 else if (c != '\n') {
14929 if (p->heredoc_indent > p->heredoc_line_indent) {
14930 p->heredoc_indent = p->heredoc_line_indent;
14931 }
14932 p->heredoc_line_indent = -1;
14933 }
14934 }
14935 return FALSE;
14936}
14937
14938static void
14939parser_mixed_error(struct parser_params *p, rb_encoding *enc1, rb_encoding *enc2)
14940{
14941 YYLTYPE loc = RUBY_INIT_YYLLOC();
14942 const char *n1 = rb_enc_name(enc1), *n2 = rb_enc_name(enc2);
14943 compile_error(p, "%s mixed within %s source", n1, n2);
14944 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
14945}
14946
14947static void
14948parser_mixed_escape(struct parser_params *p, const char *beg, rb_encoding *enc1, rb_encoding *enc2)
14949{
14950 const char *pos = p->lex.pcur;
14951 p->lex.pcur = beg;
14952 parser_mixed_error(p, enc1, enc2);
14953 p->lex.pcur = pos;
14954}
14955
14956static int
14957tokadd_string(struct parser_params *p,
14958 int func, int term, int paren, long *nest,
14959 rb_encoding **encp, rb_encoding **enc)
14960{
14961 int c;
14962 bool erred = false;
14963
14964#define mixed_error(enc1, enc2) \
14965 (void)(erred || (parser_mixed_error(p, enc1, enc2), erred = true))
14966#define mixed_escape(beg, enc1, enc2) \
14967 (void)(erred || (parser_mixed_escape(p, beg, enc1, enc2), erred = true))
14968
14969 while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1) {
14970 if (p->heredoc_indent > 0) {
14971 parser_update_heredoc_indent(p, c);
14972 }
14973
14974 if (paren && c == paren) {
14975 ++*nest;
14976 }
14977 else if (c == term) {
14978 if (!nest || !*nest) {
14979 pushback(p, c);
14980 break;
14981 }
14982 --*nest;
14983 }
14984 else if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) && c == '#' && p->lex.pcur < p->lex.pend) {
14985 int c2 = *p->lex.pcur;
14986 if (c2 == '$' || c2 == '@' || c2 == '{') {
14987 pushback(p, c);
14988 break;
14989 }
14990 }
14991 else if (c == '\\') {
14992 literal_flush(p, p->lex.pcur - 1);
14993 c = nextc(p);
14994 switch (c) {
14995 case '\n':
14996 if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) break;
14997 if (func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) {
14998 if (!(func & STR_FUNC_INDENT) || (p->heredoc_indent < 0))
14999 continue;
15000 if (c == term) {
15001 c = '\\';
15002 goto terminate;
15003 }
15004 }
15005 tokadd(p, '\\');
15006 break;
15007
15008 case '\\':
15009 if (func & STR_FUNC_ESCAPE) tokadd(p, c);
15010 break;
15011
15012 case 'u':
15013 if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) == 0) {
15014 tokadd(p, '\\');
15015 break;
15016 }
15017 tokadd_utf8(p, enc, term,
15018 func & STR_FUNC_SYMBOL,
15019 func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP);
15020 continue;
15021
15022 default:
15023 if (c == -1) return -1;
15024 if (!ISASCII(c)) {
15025 if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) == 0) tokadd(p, '\\');
15026 goto non_ascii;
15027 }
15028 if (func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) {
15029 switch (c) {
15030 case 'c':
15031 case 'C':
15032 case 'M': {
15033 pushback(p, c);
15034 c = read_escape(p, 0, enc);
15035
15036 int i;
15037 char escbuf[5];
15038 snprintf(escbuf, sizeof(escbuf), "\\x%02X", c);
15039 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
15040 tokadd(p, escbuf[i]);
15041 }
15042 continue;
15043 }
15044 }
15045
15046 if (c == term && !simple_re_meta(c)) {
15047 tokadd(p, c);
15048 continue;
15049 }
15050 pushback(p, c);
15051 if ((c = tokadd_escape(p, enc)) < 0)
15052 return -1;
15053 if (*enc && *enc != *encp) {
15054 mixed_escape(p->lex.ptok+2, *enc, *encp);
15055 }
15056 continue;
15057 }
15058 else if (func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) {
15059 pushback(p, c);
15060 if (func & STR_FUNC_ESCAPE) tokadd(p, '\\');
15061 c = read_escape(p, 0, enc);
15062 }
15063 else if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
15064 /* ignore backslashed spaces in %w */
15065 }
15066 else if (c != term && !(paren && c == paren)) {
15067 tokadd(p, '\\');
15068 pushback(p, c);
15069 continue;
15070 }
15071 }
15072 }
15073 else if (!parser_isascii(p)) {
15074 non_ascii:
15075 if (!*enc) {
15076 *enc = *encp;
15077 }
15078 else if (*enc != *encp) {
15079 mixed_error(*enc, *encp);
15080 continue;
15081 }
15082 if (tokadd_mbchar(p, c) == -1) return -1;
15083 continue;
15084 }
15085 else if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
15086 pushback(p, c);
15087 break;
15088 }
15089 if (c & 0x80) {
15090 if (!*enc) {
15091 *enc = *encp;
15092 }
15093 else if (*enc != *encp) {
15094 mixed_error(*enc, *encp);
15095 continue;
15096 }
15097 }
15098 tokadd(p, c);
15099 }
15100 terminate:
15101 if (*enc) *encp = *enc;
15102 return c;
15103}
15104
15105static inline rb_strterm_t *
15106new_strterm(VALUE v1, VALUE v2, VALUE v3, VALUE v0)
15107{
15108 return (rb_strterm_t*)rb_imemo_new(imemo_parser_strterm, v1, v2, v3, v0);
15109}

15112#define NEW_STRTERM(func, term, paren) \
15113 new_strterm((VALUE)(func), (VALUE)(paren), (VALUE)(term), 0)

15115#ifdef RIPPER
15116static void
15117flush_string_content(struct parser_params *p, rb_encoding *enc)
15118{
15119 VALUE content = yylval.val;
15120 if (!ripper_is_node_yylval(content))
15121 content = ripper_new_yylval(p, 0, 0, content);
15122 if (has_delayed_token(p)) {
15123 ptrdiff_t len = p->lex.pcur - p->lex.ptok;
15124 if (len > 0) {
15125 rb_enc_str_buf_cat(p->delayed.token, p->lex.ptok, len, enc);
15126 }
15127 dispatch_delayed_token(p, tSTRING_CONTENT);
15128 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pcur;
15129 RNODE(content)->nd_rval = yylval.val;
15130 }
15131 dispatch_scan_event(p, tSTRING_CONTENT);
15132 if (yylval.val != content)
15133 RNODE(content)->nd_rval = yylval.val;
15134 yylval.val = content;
15135}
15136#else
15137#define flush_string_content(p, enc) ((void)(enc))
15138#endif
15139
15140RUBY_FUNC_EXPORTED const unsigned int ruby_global_name_punct_bits[(0x7e - 0x20 + 31) / 32];
15141/* this can be shared with ripper, since it's independent from struct
15142 * parser_params. */
15143#ifndef RIPPER
15144#define BIT(c, idx) (((c) / 32 - 1 == idx) ? (1U << ((c) % 32)) : 0)
15145#define SPECIAL_PUNCT(idx) ( \
15146 BIT('~', idx) | BIT('*', idx) | BIT('$', idx) | BIT('?', idx) | \
15147 BIT('!', idx) | BIT('@', idx) | BIT('/', idx) | BIT('\\', idx) | \
15148 BIT(';', idx) | BIT(',', idx) | BIT('.', idx) | BIT('=', idx) | \
15149 BIT(':', idx) | BIT('<', idx) | BIT('>', idx) | BIT('\"', idx) | \
15150 BIT('&', idx) | BIT('`', idx) | BIT('\'', idx) | BIT('+', idx) | \
15151 BIT('0', idx))
15152const unsigned int ruby_global_name_punct_bits[] = {
15153 SPECIAL_PUNCT(0),
15154 SPECIAL_PUNCT(1),
15155 SPECIAL_PUNCT(2),
15156};
15157#undef BIT
15158#undef SPECIAL_PUNCT
15159#endif
15160
15161static enum yytokentype
15162parser_peek_variable_name(struct parser_params *p)
15163{
15164 int c;
15165 const char *ptr = p->lex.pcur;
15166
15167 if (ptr + 1 >= p->lex.pend) return 0;
15168 c = *ptr++;
15169 switch (c) {
15170 case '$':
15171 if ((c = *ptr) == '-') {
15172 if (++ptr >= p->lex.pend) return 0;
15173 c = *ptr;
15174 }
15175 else if (is_global_name_punct(c) || ISDIGIT(c)) {
15176 return tSTRING_DVAR;
15177 }
15178 break;
15179 case '@':
15180 if ((c = *ptr) == '@') {
15181 if (++ptr >= p->lex.pend) return 0;
15182 c = *ptr;
15183 }
15184 break;
15185 case '{':
15186 p->lex.pcur = ptr;
15187 p->command_start = TRUE;
15188 return tSTRING_DBEG;
15189 default:
15190 return 0;
15191 }
15192 if (!ISASCII(c) || c == '_' || ISALPHA(c))
15193 return tSTRING_DVAR;
15194 return 0;
15195}
15196
15197#define IS_ARG() IS_lex_state(EXPR_ARG_ANY)
15198#define IS_END() IS_lex_state(EXPR_END_ANY)
15199#define IS_BEG() (IS_lex_state(EXPR_BEG_ANY) || IS_lex_state_all(EXPR_ARG|EXPR_LABELED))
15200#define IS_SPCARG(c) (IS_ARG() && space_seen && !ISSPACE(c))
15201#define IS_LABEL_POSSIBLE() (\
15202 (IS_lex_state(EXPR_LABEL|EXPR_ENDFN) && !cmd_state) || \
15203 IS_ARG())
15204#define IS_LABEL_SUFFIX(n) (peek_n(p, ':',(n)) && !peek_n(p, ':', (n)+1))
15205#define IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() IS_lex_state(EXPR_FNAME | EXPR_DOT)
15206
15207static inline enum yytokentype
15208parser_string_term(struct parser_params *p, int func)
15209{
15210 p->lex.strterm = 0;
15211 if (func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) {
15212 set_yylval_num(regx_options(p));
15213 dispatch_scan_event(p, tREGEXP_END);
15214 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
15215 return tREGEXP_END;
15216 }
15217 if ((func & STR_FUNC_LABEL) && IS_LABEL_SUFFIX(0)) {
15218 nextc(p);
15219 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG|EXPR_LABEL);
15220 return tLABEL_END;
15221 }
15222 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
15223 return tSTRING_END;
15224}
15225
15226static enum yytokentype
15227parse_string(struct parser_params *p, rb_strterm_literal_t *quote)
15228{
15229 int func = (int)quote->u1.func;
15230 int term = (int)quote->u3.term;
15231 int paren = (int)quote->u2.paren;
15232 int c, space = 0;
15233 rb_encoding *enc = p->enc;
15234 rb_encoding *base_enc = 0;
15235 VALUE lit;
15236
15237 if (func & STR_FUNC_TERM) {
15238 if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) nextc(p); /* delayed term */
15239 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
15240 p->lex.strterm = 0;
15241 return func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP ? tREGEXP_END : tSTRING_END;
15242 }
15243 c = nextc(p);
15244 if ((func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) && ISSPACE(c)) {
15245 do {c = nextc(p);} while (ISSPACE(c));
15246 space = 1;
15247 }
15248 if (func & STR_FUNC_LIST) {
15249 quote->u1.func &= ~STR_FUNC_LIST;
15250 space = 1;
15251 }
15252 if (c == term && !quote->u0.nest) {
15253 if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) {
15254 quote->u1.func |= STR_FUNC_TERM;
15255 pushback(p, c); /* dispatch the term at tSTRING_END */
15256 add_delayed_token(p, p->lex.ptok, p->lex.pcur);
15257 return ' ';
15258 }
15259 return parser_string_term(p, func);
15260 }
15261 if (space) {
15262 pushback(p, c);
15263 add_delayed_token(p, p->lex.ptok, p->lex.pcur);
15264 return ' ';
15265 }
15266 newtok(p);
15267 if ((func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND) && c == '#') {
15268 int t = parser_peek_variable_name(p);
15269 if (t) return t;
15270 tokadd(p, '#');
15271 c = nextc(p);
15272 }
15273 pushback(p, c);
15274 if (tokadd_string(p, func, term, paren, &quote->u0.nest,
15275 &enc, &base_enc) == -1) {
15276 if (p->eofp) {
15277#ifndef RIPPER
15278# define unterminated_literal(mesg) yyerror0(mesg)
15279#else
15280# define unterminated_literal(mesg) compile_error(p, mesg)
15281#endif
15282 literal_flush(p, p->lex.pcur);
15283 if (func & STR_FUNC_QWORDS) {
15284 /* no content to add, bailing out here */
15285 unterminated_literal("unterminated list meets end of file");
15286 p->lex.strterm = 0;
15287 return tSTRING_END;
15288 }
15289 if (func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) {
15290 unterminated_literal("unterminated regexp meets end of file");
15291 }
15292 else {
15293 unterminated_literal("unterminated string meets end of file");
15294 }
15295 quote->u1.func |= STR_FUNC_TERM;
15296 }
15297 }
15298
15299 tokfix(p);
15300 lit = STR_NEW3(tok(p), toklen(p), enc, func);
15301 set_yylval_str(lit);
15302 flush_string_content(p, enc);
15303
15304 return tSTRING_CONTENT;
15305}
15306
15307static enum yytokentype
15308heredoc_identifier(struct parser_params *p)
15309{
15310 /*
15311 * term_len is length of `<<"END"` except `END`,
15312 * in this case term_len is 4 (<, <, " and ").
15313 */
15314 long len, offset = p->lex.pcur - p->lex.pbeg;
15315 int c = nextc(p), term, func = 0, quote = 0;
15316 enum yytokentype token = tSTRING_BEG;
15317 int indent = 0;
15318
15319 if (c == '-') {
15320 c = nextc(p);
15321 func = STR_FUNC_INDENT;
15322 offset++;
15323 }
15324 else if (c == '~') {
15325 c = nextc(p);
15326 func = STR_FUNC_INDENT;
15327 offset++;
15328 indent = INT_MAX;
15329 }
15330 switch (c) {
15331 case '\'':
15332 func |= str_squote; goto quoted;
15333 case '"':
15334 func |= str_dquote; goto quoted;
15335 case '`':
15336 token = tXSTRING_BEG;
15337 func |= str_xquote; goto quoted;
15338
15339 quoted:
15340 quote++;
15341 offset++;
15342 term = c;
15343 len = 0;
15344 while ((c = nextc(p)) != term) {
15345 if (c == -1 || c == '\r' || c == '\n') {
15346 yyerror0("unterminated here document identifier");
15347 return -1;
15348 }
15349 }
15350 break;
15351
15352 default:
15353 if (!parser_is_identchar(p)) {
15354 pushback(p, c);
15355 if (func & STR_FUNC_INDENT) {
15356 pushback(p, indent > 0 ? '~' : '-');
15357 }
15358 return 0;
15359 }
15360 func |= str_dquote;
15361 do {
15362 int n = parser_precise_mbclen(p, p->lex.pcur-1);
15363 if (n < 0) return 0;
15364 p->lex.pcur += --n;
15365 } while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1 && parser_is_identchar(p));
15366 pushback(p, c);
15367 break;
15368 }
15369
15370 len = p->lex.pcur - (p->lex.pbeg + offset) - quote;
15371 if ((unsigned long)len >= HERETERM_LENGTH_MAX)
15372 yyerror0("too long here document identifier");
15373 dispatch_scan_event(p, tHEREDOC_BEG);
15374 lex_goto_eol(p);
15375
15376 p->lex.strterm = new_strterm(0, 0, 0, p->lex.lastline);
15377 p->lex.strterm->flags |= STRTERM_HEREDOC;
15378 rb_strterm_heredoc_t *here = &p->lex.strterm->u.heredoc;
15379 here->offset = offset;
15380 here->sourceline = p->ruby_sourceline;
15381 here->length = (int)len;
15382 here->quote = quote;
15383 here->func = func;
15384
15385 token_flush(p);
15386 p->heredoc_indent = indent;
15387 p->heredoc_line_indent = 0;
15388 return token;
15389}
15390
15391static void
15392heredoc_restore(struct parser_params *p, rb_strterm_heredoc_t *here)
15393{
15394 VALUE line;
15395
15396 p->lex.strterm = 0;
15397 line = here->lastline;
15398 p->lex.lastline = line;
15399 p->lex.pbeg = RSTRING_PTR(line);
15400 p->lex.pend = p->lex.pbeg + RSTRING_LEN(line);
15401 p->lex.pcur = p->lex.pbeg + here->offset + here->length + here->quote;
15402 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pbeg + here->offset - here->quote;
15403 p->heredoc_end = p->ruby_sourceline;
15404 p->ruby_sourceline = (int)here->sourceline;
15405 if (p->eofp) p->lex.nextline = Qnil;
15406 p->eofp = 0;
15407}
15408
15409static int
15410dedent_string(VALUE string, int width)
15411{
15412 char *str;
15413 long len;
15414 int i, col = 0;
15415
15416 RSTRING_GETMEM(string, str, len);
15417 for (i = 0; i < len && col < width; i++) {
15418 if (str[i] == ' ') {
15419 col++;
15420 }
15421 else if (str[i] == '\t') {
15422 int n = TAB_WIDTH * (col / TAB_WIDTH + 1);
15423 if (n > width) break;
15424 col = n;
15425 }
15426 else {
15427 break;
15428 }
15429 }
15430 if (!i) return 0;
15431 rb_str_modify(string);
15432 str = RSTRING_PTR(string);
15433 if (RSTRING_LEN(string) != len)
15434 rb_fatal("literal string changed: %+"PRIsVALUE, string);
15435 MEMMOVE(str, str + i, char, len - i);
15436 rb_str_set_len(string, len - i);
15437 return i;
15438}
15439
15440#ifndef RIPPER
15441static NODE *
15442heredoc_dedent(struct parser_params *p, NODE *root)
15443{
15444 NODE *node, *str_node, *prev_node;
15445 int indent = p->heredoc_indent;
15446 VALUE prev_lit = 0;
15447
15448 if (indent <= 0) return root;
15449 p->heredoc_indent = 0;
15450 if (!root) return root;
15451
15452 prev_node = node = str_node = root;
15453 if (nd_type_p(root, NODE_LIST)) str_node = root->nd_head;
15454
15455 while (str_node) {
15456 VALUE lit = str_node->nd_lit;
15457 if (str_node->flags & NODE_FL_NEWLINE) {
15458 dedent_string(lit, indent);
15459 }
15460 if (!prev_lit) {
15461 prev_lit = lit;
15462 }
15463 else if (!literal_concat0(p, prev_lit, lit)) {
15464 return 0;
15465 }
15466 else {
15467 NODE *end = node->nd_end;
15468 node = prev_node->nd_next = node->nd_next;
15469 if (!node) {
15470 if (nd_type_p(prev_node, NODE_DSTR))
15471 nd_set_type(prev_node, NODE_STR);
15472 break;
15473 }
15474 node->nd_end = end;
15475 goto next_str;
15476 }
15477
15478 str_node = 0;
15479 while ((node = (prev_node = node)->nd_next) != 0) {
15480 next_str:
15481 if (!nd_type_p(node, NODE_LIST)) break;
15482 if ((str_node = node->nd_head) != 0) {
15483 enum node_type type = nd_type(str_node);
15484 if (type == NODE_STR || type == NODE_DSTR) break;
15485 prev_lit = 0;
15486 str_node = 0;
15487 }
15488 }
15489 }
15490 return root;
15491}
15492#else /* RIPPER */
15493static VALUE
15494heredoc_dedent(struct parser_params *p, VALUE array)
15495{
15496 int indent = p->heredoc_indent;
15497
15498 if (indent <= 0) return array;
15499 p->heredoc_indent = 0;
15500 dispatch2(heredoc_dedent, array, INT2NUM(indent));
15501 return array;
15502}
15503
15504/*
15505 * call-seq:
15506 * Ripper.dedent_string(input, width) -> Integer
15507 *
15508 * USE OF RIPPER LIBRARY ONLY.
15509 *
15510 * Strips up to +width+ leading whitespaces from +input+,
15511 * and returns the stripped column width.
15512 */
15513static VALUE
15514parser_dedent_string(VALUE self, VALUE input, VALUE width)
15515{
15516 int wid, col;
15517
15518 StringValue(input);
15519 wid = NUM2UINT(width);
15520 col = dedent_string(input, wid);
15521 return INT2NUM(col);
15522}
15523#endif
15524
15525static int
15526whole_match_p(struct parser_params *p, const char *eos, long len, int indent)
15527{
15528 const char *ptr = p->lex.pbeg;
15529 long n;
15530
15531 if (indent) {
15532 while (*ptr && ISSPACE(*ptr)) ptr++;
15533 }
15534 n = p->lex.pend - (ptr + len);
15535 if (n < 0) return FALSE;
15536 if (n > 0 && ptr[len] != '\n') {
15537 if (ptr[len] != '\r') return FALSE;
15538 if (n <= 1 || ptr[len+1] != '\n') return FALSE;
15539 }
15540 return strncmp(eos, ptr, len) == 0;
15541}
15542
15543static int
15544word_match_p(struct parser_params *p, const char *word, long len)
15545{
15546 if (strncmp(p->lex.pcur, word, len)) return 0;
15547 if (p->lex.pcur + len == p->lex.pend) return 1;
15548 int c = (unsigned char)p->lex.pcur[len];
15549 if (ISSPACE(c)) return 1;
15550 switch (c) {
15551 case '\0': case '\004': case '\032': return 1;
15552 }
15553 return 0;
15554}
15555
15556#define NUM_SUFFIX_R (1<<0)
15557#define NUM_SUFFIX_I (1<<1)
15558#define NUM_SUFFIX_ALL 3
15559
15560static int
15561number_literal_suffix(struct parser_params *p, int mask)
15562{
15563 int c, result = 0;
15564 const char *lastp = p->lex.pcur;
15565
15566 while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1) {
15567 if ((mask & NUM_SUFFIX_I) && c == 'i') {
15568 result |= (mask & NUM_SUFFIX_I);
15569 mask &= ~NUM_SUFFIX_I;
15570 /* r after i, rational of complex is disallowed */
15571 mask &= ~NUM_SUFFIX_R;
15572 continue;
15573 }
15574 if ((mask & NUM_SUFFIX_R) && c == 'r') {
15575 result |= (mask & NUM_SUFFIX_R);
15576 mask &= ~NUM_SUFFIX_R;
15577 continue;
15578 }
15579 if (!ISASCII(c) || ISALPHA(c) || c == '_') {
15580 p->lex.pcur = lastp;
15581 literal_flush(p, p->lex.pcur);
15582 return 0;
15583 }
15584 pushback(p, c);
15585 break;
15586 }
15587 return result;
15588}
15589
15590static enum yytokentype
15591set_number_literal(struct parser_params *p, VALUE v,
15592 enum yytokentype type, int suffix)
15593{
15594 if (suffix & NUM_SUFFIX_I) {
15595 v = rb_complex_raw(INT2FIX(0), v);
15596 type = tIMAGINARY;
15597 }
15598 set_yylval_literal(v);
15599 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
15600 return type;
15601}
15602
15603static enum yytokentype
15604set_integer_literal(struct parser_params *p, VALUE v, int suffix)
15605{
15606 enum yytokentype type = tINTEGER;
15607 if (suffix & NUM_SUFFIX_R) {
15608 v = rb_rational_raw1(v);
15609 type = tRATIONAL;
15610 }
15611 return set_number_literal(p, v, type, suffix);
15612}
