15614#ifdef RIPPER
15615static void
15616dispatch_heredoc_end(struct parser_params *p)
15617{
15618 VALUE str;
15619 if (has_delayed_token(p))
15620 dispatch_delayed_token(p, tSTRING_CONTENT);
15621 str = STR_NEW(p->lex.ptok, p->lex.pend - p->lex.ptok);
15622 ripper_dispatch1(p, ripper_token2eventid(tHEREDOC_END), str);
15623 lex_goto_eol(p);
15624 token_flush(p);
15625}
15626
15627#else
15628#define dispatch_heredoc_end(p) ((void)0)
15629#endif
15630
15631static enum yytokentype
15632here_document(struct parser_params *p, rb_strterm_heredoc_t *here)
15633{
15634 int c, func, indent = 0;
15635 const char *eos, *ptr, *ptr_end;
15636 long len;
15637 VALUE str = 0;
15638 rb_encoding *enc = p->enc;
15639 rb_encoding *base_enc = 0;
15640 int bol;
15641
15642 eos = RSTRING_PTR(here->lastline) + here->offset;
15643 len = here->length;
15644 indent = (func = here->func) & STR_FUNC_INDENT;
15645
15646 if ((c = nextc(p)) == -1) {
15647 error:
15648#ifdef RIPPER
15649 if (!has_delayed_token(p)) {
15650 dispatch_scan_event(p, tSTRING_CONTENT);
15651 }
15652 else {
15653 if ((len = p->lex.pcur - p->lex.ptok) > 0) {
15654 if (!(func & STR_FUNC_REGEXP) && rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
15655 int cr = ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN;
15656 rb_str_coderange_scan_restartable(p->lex.ptok, p->lex.pcur, enc, &cr);
15657 if (cr != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT &&
15658 p->enc == rb_usascii_encoding() &&
15659 enc != rb_utf8_encoding()) {
15660 enc = rb_ascii8bit_encoding();
15661 }
15662 }
15663 rb_enc_str_buf_cat(p->delayed.token, p->lex.ptok, len, enc);
15664 }
15665 dispatch_delayed_token(p, tSTRING_CONTENT);
15666 }
15667 lex_goto_eol(p);
15668#endif
15669 heredoc_restore(p, &p->lex.strterm->u.heredoc);
15670 compile_error(p, "can't find string \"%.*s\" anywhere before EOF",
15671 (int)len, eos);
15672 token_flush(p);
15673 p->lex.strterm = 0;
15674 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
15675 return tSTRING_END;
15676 }
15677 bol = was_bol(p);
15678 if (!bol) {
15679 /* not beginning of line, cannot be the terminator */
15680 }
15681 else if (p->heredoc_line_indent == -1) {
15682 /* `heredoc_line_indent == -1` means
15683 * - "after an interpolation in the same line", or
15684 * - "in a continuing line"
15685 */
15686 p->heredoc_line_indent = 0;
15687 }
15688 else if (whole_match_p(p, eos, len, indent)) {
15689 dispatch_heredoc_end(p);
15690 restore:
15691 heredoc_restore(p, &p->lex.strterm->u.heredoc);
15692 token_flush(p);
15693 p->lex.strterm = 0;
15694 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
15695 return tSTRING_END;
15696 }
15697
15698 if (!(func & STR_FUNC_EXPAND)) {
15699 do {
15700 ptr = RSTRING_PTR(p->lex.lastline);
15701 ptr_end = p->lex.pend;
15702 if (ptr_end > ptr) {
15703 switch (ptr_end[-1]) {
15704 case '\n':
15705 if (--ptr_end == ptr || ptr_end[-1] != '\r') {
15706 ptr_end++;
15707 break;
15708 }
15709 case '\r':
15710 --ptr_end;
15711 }
15712 }
15713
15714 if (p->heredoc_indent > 0) {
15715 long i = 0;
15716 while (ptr + i < ptr_end && parser_update_heredoc_indent(p, ptr[i]))
15717 i++;
15718 p->heredoc_line_indent = 0;
15719 }
15720
15721 if (str)
15722 rb_str_cat(str, ptr, ptr_end - ptr);
15723 else
15724 str = STR_NEW(ptr, ptr_end - ptr);
15725 if (ptr_end < p->lex.pend) rb_str_cat(str, "\n", 1);
15726 lex_goto_eol(p);
15727 if (p->heredoc_indent > 0) {
15728 goto flush_str;
15729 }
15730 if (nextc(p) == -1) {
15731 if (str) {
15732 str = 0;
15733 }
15734 goto error;
15735 }
15736 } while (!whole_match_p(p, eos, len, indent));
15737 }
15738 else {
15739 /* int mb = ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT, *mbp = &mb;*/
15740 newtok(p);
15741 if (c == '#') {
15742 int t = parser_peek_variable_name(p);
15743 if (p->heredoc_line_indent != -1) {
15744 if (p->heredoc_indent > p->heredoc_line_indent) {
15745 p->heredoc_indent = p->heredoc_line_indent;
15746 }
15747 p->heredoc_line_indent = -1;
15748 }
15749 if (t) return t;
15750 tokadd(p, '#');
15751 c = nextc(p);
15752 }
15753 do {
15754 pushback(p, c);
15755 enc = p->enc;
15756 if ((c = tokadd_string(p, func, '\n', 0, NULL, &enc, &base_enc)) == -1) {
15757 if (p->eofp) goto error;
15758 goto restore;
15759 }
15760 if (c != '\n') {
15761 if (c == '\\') p->heredoc_line_indent = -1;
15762 flush:
15763 str = STR_NEW3(tok(p), toklen(p), enc, func);
15764 flush_str:
15765 set_yylval_str(str);
15766#ifndef RIPPER
15767 if (bol) yylval.node->flags |= NODE_FL_NEWLINE;
15768#endif
15769 flush_string_content(p, enc);
15770 return tSTRING_CONTENT;
15771 }
15772 tokadd(p, nextc(p));
15773 if (p->heredoc_indent > 0) {
15774 lex_goto_eol(p);
15775 goto flush;
15776 }
15777 /* if (mbp && mb == ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN) mbp = 0;*/
15778 if ((c = nextc(p)) == -1) goto error;
15779 } while (!whole_match_p(p, eos, len, indent));
15780 str = STR_NEW3(tok(p), toklen(p), enc, func);
15781 }
15782 dispatch_heredoc_end(p);
15783#ifdef RIPPER
15784 str = ripper_new_yylval(p, ripper_token2eventid(tSTRING_CONTENT),
15785 yylval.val, str);
15786#endif
15787 heredoc_restore(p, &p->lex.strterm->u.heredoc);
15788 token_flush(p);
15789 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(func | STR_FUNC_TERM, 0, 0);
15790 set_yylval_str(str);
15791#ifndef RIPPER
15792 if (bol) yylval.node->flags |= NODE_FL_NEWLINE;
15793#endif
15794 return tSTRING_CONTENT;
15795}
15796
15797#include "lex.c"
15798
15799static int
15800arg_ambiguous(struct parser_params *p, char c)
15801{
15802#ifndef RIPPER
15803 if (c == '/') {
15804 rb_warning1("ambiguity between regexp and two divisions: wrap regexp in parentheses or add a space after `%c' operator", WARN_I(c));
15805 }
15806 else {
15807 rb_warning1("ambiguous first argument; put parentheses or a space even after `%c' operator", WARN_I(c));
15808 }
15809#else
15810 dispatch1(arg_ambiguous, rb_usascii_str_new(&c, 1));
15811#endif
15812 return TRUE;
15813}
15814
15815static ID
15816#ifndef RIPPER
15817formal_argument(struct parser_params *p, ID lhs)
15818#else
15819formal_argument(struct parser_params *p, VALUE lhs)
15820#endif
15821{
15822 ID id = get_id(lhs);
15823
15824 switch (id_type(id)) {
15825 case ID_LOCAL:
15826 break;
15827#ifndef RIPPER
15828# define ERR(mesg) yyerror0(mesg)
15829#else
15830# define ERR(mesg) (dispatch2(param_error, WARN_S(mesg), lhs), ripper_error(p))
15831#endif
15832 case ID_CONST:
15833 ERR("formal argument cannot be a constant");
15834 return 0;
15835 case ID_INSTANCE:
15836 ERR("formal argument cannot be an instance variable");
15837 return 0;
15838 case ID_GLOBAL:
15839 ERR("formal argument cannot be a global variable");
15840 return 0;
15841 case ID_CLASS:
15842 ERR("formal argument cannot be a class variable");
15843 return 0;
15844 default:
15845 ERR("formal argument must be local variable");
15846 return 0;
15847#undef ERR
15848 }
15849 shadowing_lvar(p, id);
15850 return lhs;
15851}
15852
15853static int
15854lvar_defined(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
15855{
15856 return (dyna_in_block(p) && dvar_defined(p, id)) || local_id(p, id);
15857}
15858
15859/* emacsen -*- hack */
15860static long
15861parser_encode_length(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, long len)
15862{
15863 long nlen;
15864
15865 if (len > 5 && name[nlen = len - 5] == '-') {
15866 if (rb_memcicmp(name + nlen + 1, "unix", 4) == 0)
15867 return nlen;
15868 }
15869 if (len > 4 && name[nlen = len - 4] == '-') {
15870 if (rb_memcicmp(name + nlen + 1, "dos", 3) == 0)
15871 return nlen;
15872 if (rb_memcicmp(name + nlen + 1, "mac", 3) == 0 &&
15873 !(len == 8 && rb_memcicmp(name, "utf8-mac", len) == 0))
15874 /* exclude UTF8-MAC because the encoding named "UTF8" doesn't exist in Ruby */
15875 return nlen;
15876 }
15877 return len;
15878}
15879
15880static void
15881parser_set_encode(struct parser_params *p, const char *name)
15882{
15883 int idx = rb_enc_find_index(name);
15884 rb_encoding *enc;
15885 VALUE excargs[3];
15886
15887 if (idx < 0) {
15888 excargs[1] = rb_sprintf("unknown encoding name: %s", name);
15889 error:
15890 excargs[0] = rb_eArgError;
15891 excargs[2] = rb_make_backtrace();
15892 rb_ary_unshift(excargs[2], rb_sprintf("%"PRIsVALUE":%d", p->ruby_sourcefile_string, p->ruby_sourceline));
15893 rb_exc_raise(rb_make_exception(3, excargs));
15894 }
15895 enc = rb_enc_from_index(idx);
15896 if (!rb_enc_asciicompat(enc)) {
15897 excargs[1] = rb_sprintf("%s is not ASCII compatible", rb_enc_name(enc));
15898 goto error;
15899 }
15900 p->enc = enc;
15901#ifndef RIPPER
15902 if (p->debug_lines) {
15903 VALUE lines = p->debug_lines;
15904 long i, n = RARRAY_LEN(lines);
15905 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
15906 rb_enc_associate_index(RARRAY_AREF(lines, i), idx);
15907 }
15908 }
15909#endif
15910}
15911
15912static int
15913comment_at_top(struct parser_params *p)
15914{
15915 const char *ptr = p->lex.pbeg, *ptr_end = p->lex.pcur - 1;
15916 if (p->line_count != (p->has_shebang ? 2 : 1)) return 0;
15917 while (ptr < ptr_end) {
15918 if (!ISSPACE(*ptr)) return 0;
15919 ptr++;
15920 }
15921 return 1;
15922}
15923
15924typedef long (*rb_magic_comment_length_t)(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, long len);
15925typedef void (*rb_magic_comment_setter_t)(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val);
15926
15927static int parser_invalid_pragma_value(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val);
15928
15929static void
15930magic_comment_encoding(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
15931{
15932 if (!comment_at_top(p)) {
15933 return;
15934 }
15935 parser_set_encode(p, val);
15936}
15937
15938static int
15939parser_get_bool(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
15940{
15941 switch (*val) {
15942 case 't': case 'T':
15943 if (STRCASECMP(val, "true") == 0) {
15944 return TRUE;
15945 }
15946 break;
15947 case 'f': case 'F':
15948 if (STRCASECMP(val, "false") == 0) {
15949 return FALSE;
15950 }
15951 break;
15952 }
15953 return parser_invalid_pragma_value(p, name, val);
15954}
15955
15956static int
15957parser_invalid_pragma_value(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
15958{
15959 rb_warning2("invalid value for %s: %s", WARN_S(name), WARN_S(val));
15960 return -1;
15961}
15962
15963static void
15964parser_set_token_info(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
15965{
15966 int b = parser_get_bool(p, name, val);
15967 if (b >= 0) p->token_info_enabled = b;
15968}
15969
15970static void
15971parser_set_compile_option_flag(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
15972{
15973 int b;
15974
15975 if (p->token_seen) {
15976 rb_warning1("`%s' is ignored after any tokens", WARN_S(name));
15977 return;
15978 }
15979
15980 b = parser_get_bool(p, name, val);
15981 if (b < 0) return;
15982
15983 if (!p->compile_option)
15984 p->compile_option = rb_obj_hide(rb_ident_hash_new());
15985 rb_hash_aset(p->compile_option, ID2SYM(rb_intern(name)),
15986 RBOOL(b));
15987}
15988
15989static void
15990parser_set_shareable_constant_value(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
15991{
15992 for (const char *s = p->lex.pbeg, *e = p->lex.pcur; s < e; ++s) {
15993 if (*s == ' ' || *s == '\t') continue;
15994 if (*s == '#') break;
15995 rb_warning1("`%s' is ignored unless in comment-only line", WARN_S(name));
15996 return;
15997 }
15998
15999 switch (*val) {
16000 case 'n': case 'N':
16001 if (STRCASECMP(val, "none") == 0) {
16002 p->ctxt.shareable_constant_value = shareable_none;
16003 return;
16004 }
16005 break;
16006 case 'l': case 'L':
16007 if (STRCASECMP(val, "literal") == 0) {
16008 p->ctxt.shareable_constant_value = shareable_literal;
16009 return;
16010 }
16011 break;
16012 case 'e': case 'E':
16013 if (STRCASECMP(val, "experimental_copy") == 0) {
16014 p->ctxt.shareable_constant_value = shareable_copy;
16015 return;
16016 }
16017 if (STRCASECMP(val, "experimental_everything") == 0) {
16018 p->ctxt.shareable_constant_value = shareable_everything;
16019 return;
16020 }
16021 break;
16022 }
16023 parser_invalid_pragma_value(p, name, val);
16024}

16026# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
16027static void
16028parser_set_past_scope(struct parser_params *p, const char *name, const char *val)
16029{
16030 int b = parser_get_bool(p, name, val);
16031 if (b >= 0) p->past_scope_enabled = b;
16032}
16033# endif
16034
16035struct magic_comment {
16036 const char *name;
16037 rb_magic_comment_setter_t func;
16038 rb_magic_comment_length_t length;
16039};
16040
16041static const struct magic_comment magic_comments[] = {
16042 {"coding", magic_comment_encoding, parser_encode_length},
16043 {"encoding", magic_comment_encoding, parser_encode_length},
16044 {"frozen_string_literal", parser_set_compile_option_flag},
16045 {"shareable_constant_value", parser_set_shareable_constant_value},
16046 {"warn_indent", parser_set_token_info},
16047# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
16048 {"warn_past_scope", parser_set_past_scope},
16049# endif
16050};
16051
16052static const char *
16053magic_comment_marker(const char *str, long len)
16054{
16055 long i = 2;
16056
16057 while (i < len) {
16058 switch (str[i]) {
16059 case '-':
16060 if (str[i-1] == '*' && str[i-2] == '-') {
16061 return str + i + 1;
16062 }
16063 i += 2;
16064 break;
16065 case '*':
16066 if (i + 1 >= len) return 0;
16067 if (str[i+1] != '-') {
16068 i += 4;
16069 }
16070 else if (str[i-1] != '-') {
16071 i += 2;
16072 }
16073 else {
16074 return str + i + 2;
16075 }
16076 break;
16077 default:
16078 i += 3;
16079 break;
16080 }
16081 }
16082 return 0;
16083}
16084
16085static int
16086parser_magic_comment(struct parser_params *p, const char *str, long len)
16087{
16088 int indicator = 0;
16089 VALUE name = 0, val = 0;
16090 const char *beg, *end, *vbeg, *vend;
16091#define str_copy(_s, _p, _n) ((_s) \
16092 ? (void)(rb_str_resize((_s), (_n)), \
16093 MEMCPY(RSTRING_PTR(_s), (_p), char, (_n)), (_s)) \
16094 : (void)((_s) = STR_NEW((_p), (_n))))
16095
16096 if (len <= 7) return FALSE;
16097 if (!!(beg = magic_comment_marker(str, len))) {
16098 if (!(end = magic_comment_marker(beg, str + len - beg)))
16099 return FALSE;
16100 indicator = TRUE;
16101 str = beg;
16102 len = end - beg - 3;
16103 }
16104
16105 /* %r"([^\\s\'\":;]+)\\s*:\\s*(\"(?:\\\\.|[^\"])*\"|[^\"\\s;]+)[\\s;]*" */
16106 while (len > 0) {
16107 const struct magic_comment *mc = magic_comments;
16108 char *s;
16109 int i;
16110 long n = 0;
16111
16112 for (; len > 0 && *str; str++, --len) {
16113 switch (*str) {
16114 case '\'': case '"': case ':': case ';':
16115 continue;
16116 }
16117 if (!ISSPACE(*str)) break;
16118 }
16119 for (beg = str; len > 0; str++, --len) {
16120 switch (*str) {
16121 case '\'': case '"': case ':': case ';':
16122 break;
16123 default:
16124 if (ISSPACE(*str)) break;
16125 continue;
16126 }
16127 break;
16128 }
16129 for (end = str; len > 0 && ISSPACE(*str); str++, --len);
16130 if (!len) break;
16131 if (*str != ':') {
16132 if (!indicator) return FALSE;
16133 continue;
16134 }
16135
16136 do str++; while (--len > 0 && ISSPACE(*str));
16137 if (!len) break;
16138 if (*str == '"') {
16139 for (vbeg = ++str; --len > 0 && *str != '"'; str++) {
16140 if (*str == '\\') {
16141 --len;
16142 ++str;
16143 }
16144 }
16145 vend = str;
16146 if (len) {
16147 --len;
16148 ++str;
16149 }
16150 }
16151 else {
16152 for (vbeg = str; len > 0 && *str != '"' && *str != ';' && !ISSPACE(*str); --len, str++);
16153 vend = str;
16154 }
16155 if (indicator) {
16156 while (len > 0 && (*str == ';' || ISSPACE(*str))) --len, str++;
16157 }
16158 else {
16159 while (len > 0 && (ISSPACE(*str))) --len, str++;
16160 if (len) return FALSE;
16161 }
16162
16163 n = end - beg;
16164 str_copy(name, beg, n);
16165 s = RSTRING_PTR(name);
16166 for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
16167 if (s[i] == '-') s[i] = '_';
16168 }
16169 do {
16170 if (STRNCASECMP(mc->name, s, n) == 0 && !mc->name[n]) {
16171 n = vend - vbeg;
16172 if (mc->length) {
16173 n = (*mc->length)(p, vbeg, n);
16174 }
16175 str_copy(val, vbeg, n);
16176 (*mc->func)(p, mc->name, RSTRING_PTR(val));
16177 break;
16178 }
16179 } while (++mc < magic_comments + numberof(magic_comments));
16180#ifdef RIPPER
16181 str_copy(val, vbeg, vend - vbeg);
16182 dispatch2(magic_comment, name, val);
16183#endif
16184 }
16185
16186 return TRUE;
16187}
16188
16189static void
16190set_file_encoding(struct parser_params *p, const char *str, const char *send)
16191{
16192 int sep = 0;
16193 const char *beg = str;
16194 VALUE s;
16195
16196 for (;;) {
16197 if (send - str <= 6) return;
16198 switch (str[6]) {
16199 case 'C': case 'c': str += 6; continue;
16200 case 'O': case 'o': str += 5; continue;
16201 case 'D': case 'd': str += 4; continue;
16202 case 'I': case 'i': str += 3; continue;
16203 case 'N': case 'n': str += 2; continue;
16204 case 'G': case 'g': str += 1; continue;
16205 case '=': case ':':
16206 sep = 1;
16207 str += 6;
16208 break;
16209 default:
16210 str += 6;
16211 if (ISSPACE(*str)) break;
16212 continue;
16213 }
16214 if (STRNCASECMP(str-6, "coding", 6) == 0) break;
16215 sep = 0;
16216 }
16217 for (;;) {
16218 do {
16219 if (++str >= send) return;
16220 } while (ISSPACE(*str));
16221 if (sep) break;
16222 if (*str != '=' && *str != ':') return;
16223 sep = 1;
16224 str++;
16225 }
16226 beg = str;
16227 while ((*str == '-' || *str == '_' || ISALNUM(*str)) && ++str < send);
16228 s = rb_str_new(beg, parser_encode_length(p, beg, str - beg));
16229 parser_set_encode(p, RSTRING_PTR(s));
16230 rb_str_resize(s, 0);
16231}
16232
16233static void
16234parser_prepare(struct parser_params *p)
16235{
16236 int c = nextc(p);
16237 p->token_info_enabled = !compile_for_eval && RTEST(ruby_verbose);
16238 switch (c) {
16239 case '#':
16240 if (peek(p, '!')) p->has_shebang = 1;
16241 break;
16242 case 0xef: /* UTF-8 BOM marker */
16243 if (p->lex.pend - p->lex.pcur >= 2 &&
16244 (unsigned char)p->lex.pcur[0] == 0xbb &&
16245 (unsigned char)p->lex.pcur[1] == 0xbf) {
16246 p->enc = rb_utf8_encoding();
16247 p->lex.pcur += 2;
16248 p->lex.pbeg = p->lex.pcur;
16249 return;
16250 }
16251 break;
16252 case EOF:
16253 return;
16254 }
16255 pushback(p, c);
16256 p->enc = rb_enc_get(p->lex.lastline);
16257}
16258
16259#ifndef RIPPER
16260#define ambiguous_operator(tok, op, syn) ( \
16261 rb_warning0("`"op"' after local variable or literal is interpreted as binary operator"), \
16262 rb_warning0("even though it seems like "syn""))
16263#else
16264#define ambiguous_operator(tok, op, syn) \
16265 dispatch2(operator_ambiguous, TOKEN2VAL(tok), rb_str_new_cstr(syn))
16266#endif
16267#define warn_balanced(tok, op, syn) ((void) \
16268 (!IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_CLASS|EXPR_DOT|EXPR_FNAME|EXPR_ENDFN) && \
16269 space_seen && !ISSPACE(c) && \
16270 (ambiguous_operator(tok, op, syn), 0)), \
16271 (enum yytokentype)(tok))
16272
16273static VALUE
16274parse_rational(struct parser_params *p, char *str, int len, int seen_point)
16275{
16276 VALUE v;
16277 char *point = &str[seen_point];
16278 size_t fraclen = len-seen_point-1;
16279 memmove(point, point+1, fraclen+1);
16280 v = rb_cstr_to_inum(str, 10, FALSE);
16281 return rb_rational_new(v, rb_int_positive_pow(10, fraclen));
16282}
16283
16284static enum yytokentype
16285no_digits(struct parser_params *p)
16286{
16287 yyerror0("numeric literal without digits");
16288 if (peek(p, '_')) nextc(p);
16289 /* dummy 0, for tUMINUS_NUM at numeric */
16290 return set_integer_literal(p, INT2FIX(0), 0);
16291}
16292
16293static enum yytokentype
16294parse_numeric(struct parser_params *p, int c)
16295{
16296 int is_float, seen_point, seen_e, nondigit;
16297 int suffix;
16298
16299 is_float = seen_point = seen_e = nondigit = 0;
16300 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
16301 newtok(p);
16302 if (c == '-' || c == '+') {
16303 tokadd(p, c);
16304 c = nextc(p);
16305 }
16306 if (c == '0') {
16307 int start = toklen(p);
16308 c = nextc(p);
16309 if (c == 'x' || c == 'X') {
16310 /* hexadecimal */
16311 c = nextc(p);
16312 if (c != -1 && ISXDIGIT(c)) {
16313 do {
16314 if (c == '_') {
16315 if (nondigit) break;
16316 nondigit = c;
16317 continue;
16318 }
16319 if (!ISXDIGIT(c)) break;
16320 nondigit = 0;
16321 tokadd(p, c);
16322 } while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1);
16323 }
16324 pushback(p, c);
16325 tokfix(p);
16326 if (toklen(p) == start) {
16327 return no_digits(p);
16328 }
16329 else if (nondigit) goto trailing_uc;
16330 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16331 return set_integer_literal(p, rb_cstr_to_inum(tok(p), 16, FALSE), suffix);
16332 }
16333 if (c == 'b' || c == 'B') {
16334 /* binary */
16335 c = nextc(p);
16336 if (c == '0' || c == '1') {
16337 do {
16338 if (c == '_') {
16339 if (nondigit) break;
16340 nondigit = c;
16341 continue;
16342 }
16343 if (c != '0' && c != '1') break;
16344 nondigit = 0;
16345 tokadd(p, c);
16346 } while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1);
16347 }
16348 pushback(p, c);
16349 tokfix(p);
16350 if (toklen(p) == start) {
16351 return no_digits(p);
16352 }
16353 else if (nondigit) goto trailing_uc;
16354 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16355 return set_integer_literal(p, rb_cstr_to_inum(tok(p), 2, FALSE), suffix);
16356 }
16357 if (c == 'd' || c == 'D') {
16358 /* decimal */
16359 c = nextc(p);
16360 if (c != -1 && ISDIGIT(c)) {
16361 do {
16362 if (c == '_') {
16363 if (nondigit) break;
16364 nondigit = c;
16365 continue;
16366 }
16367 if (!ISDIGIT(c)) break;
16368 nondigit = 0;
16369 tokadd(p, c);
16370 } while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1);
16371 }
16372 pushback(p, c);
16373 tokfix(p);
16374 if (toklen(p) == start) {
16375 return no_digits(p);
16376 }
16377 else if (nondigit) goto trailing_uc;
16378 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16379 return set_integer_literal(p, rb_cstr_to_inum(tok(p), 10, FALSE), suffix);
16380 }
16381 if (c == '_') {
16382 /* 0_0 */
16383 goto octal_number;
16384 }
16385 if (c == 'o' || c == 'O') {
16386 /* prefixed octal */
16387 c = nextc(p);
16388 if (c == -1 || c == '_' || !ISDIGIT(c)) {
16389 return no_digits(p);
16390 }
16391 }
16392 if (c >= '0' && c <= '7') {
16393 /* octal */
16394 octal_number:
16395 do {
16396 if (c == '_') {
16397 if (nondigit) break;
16398 nondigit = c;
16399 continue;
16400 }
16401 if (c < '0' || c > '9') break;
16402 if (c > '7') goto invalid_octal;
16403 nondigit = 0;
16404 tokadd(p, c);
16405 } while ((c = nextc(p)) != -1);
16406 if (toklen(p) > start) {
16407 pushback(p, c);
16408 tokfix(p);
16409 if (nondigit) goto trailing_uc;
16410 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16411 return set_integer_literal(p, rb_cstr_to_inum(tok(p), 8, FALSE), suffix);
16412 }
16413 if (nondigit) {
16414 pushback(p, c);
16415 goto trailing_uc;
16416 }
16417 }
16418 if (c > '7' && c <= '9') {
16419 invalid_octal:
16420 yyerror0("Invalid octal digit");
16421 }
16422 else if (c == '.' || c == 'e' || c == 'E') {
16423 tokadd(p, '0');
16424 }
16425 else {
16426 pushback(p, c);
16427 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16428 return set_integer_literal(p, INT2FIX(0), suffix);
16429 }
16430 }
16431
16432 for (;;) {
16433 switch (c) {
16434 case '0': case '1': case '2': case '3': case '4':
16435 case '5': case '6': case '7': case '8': case '9':
16436 nondigit = 0;
16437 tokadd(p, c);
16438 break;
16439
16440 case '.':
16441 if (nondigit) goto trailing_uc;
16442 if (seen_point || seen_e) {
16443 goto decode_num;
16444 }
16445 else {
16446 int c0 = nextc(p);
16447 if (c0 == -1 || !ISDIGIT(c0)) {
16448 pushback(p, c0);
16449 goto decode_num;
16450 }
16451 c = c0;
16452 }
16453 seen_point = toklen(p);
16454 tokadd(p, '.');
16455 tokadd(p, c);
16456 is_float++;
16457 nondigit = 0;
16458 break;
16459
16460 case 'e':
16461 case 'E':
16462 if (nondigit) {
16463 pushback(p, c);
16464 c = nondigit;
16465 goto decode_num;
16466 }
16467 if (seen_e) {
16468 goto decode_num;
16469 }
16470 nondigit = c;
16471 c = nextc(p);
16472 if (c != '-' && c != '+' && !ISDIGIT(c)) {
16473 pushback(p, c);
16474 nondigit = 0;
16475 goto decode_num;
16476 }
16477 tokadd(p, nondigit);
16478 seen_e++;
16479 is_float++;
16480 tokadd(p, c);
16481 nondigit = (c == '-' || c == '+') ? c : 0;
16482 break;
16483
16484 case '_': /* `_' in number just ignored */
16485 if (nondigit) goto decode_num;
16486 nondigit = c;
16487 break;
16488
16489 default:
16490 goto decode_num;
16491 }
16492 c = nextc(p);
16493 }
16494
16495 decode_num:
16496 pushback(p, c);
16497 if (nondigit) {
16498 trailing_uc:
16499 literal_flush(p, p->lex.pcur - 1);
16500 YYLTYPE loc = RUBY_INIT_YYLLOC();
16501 compile_error(p, "trailing `%c' in number", nondigit);
16502 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
16503 }
16504 tokfix(p);
16505 if (is_float) {
16506 enum yytokentype type = tFLOAT;
16507 VALUE v;
16508
16509 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, seen_e ? NUM_SUFFIX_I : NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16510 if (suffix & NUM_SUFFIX_R) {
16511 type = tRATIONAL;
16512 v = parse_rational(p, tok(p), toklen(p), seen_point);
16513 }
16514 else {
16515 double d = strtod(tok(p), 0);
16516 if (errno == ERANGE) {
16517 rb_warning1("Float %s out of range", WARN_S(tok(p)));
16518 errno = 0;
16519 }
16520 v = DBL2NUM(d);
16521 }
16522 return set_number_literal(p, v, type, suffix);
16523 }
16524 suffix = number_literal_suffix(p, NUM_SUFFIX_ALL);
16525 return set_integer_literal(p, rb_cstr_to_inum(tok(p), 10, FALSE), suffix);
16526}
16527
16528static enum yytokentype
16529parse_qmark(struct parser_params *p, int space_seen)
16530{
16531 rb_encoding *enc;
16532 register int c;
16533 VALUE lit;
16534
16535 if (IS_END()) {
16536 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_VALUE);
16537 return '?';
16538 }
16539 c = nextc(p);
16540 if (c == -1) {
16541 compile_error(p, "incomplete character syntax");
16542 return 0;
16543 }
16544 if (rb_enc_isspace(c, p->enc)) {
16545 if (!IS_ARG()) {
16546 int c2 = escaped_control_code(c);
16547 if (c2) {
16548 WARN_SPACE_CHAR(c2, "?");
16549 }
16550 }
16551 ternary:
16552 pushback(p, c);
16553 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_VALUE);
16554 return '?';
16555 }
16556 newtok(p);
16557 enc = p->enc;
16558 if (!parser_isascii(p)) {
16559 if (tokadd_mbchar(p, c) == -1) return 0;
16560 }
16561 else if ((rb_enc_isalnum(c, p->enc) || c == '_') &&
16562 p->lex.pcur < p->lex.pend && is_identchar(p->lex.pcur, p->lex.pend, p->enc)) {
16563 if (space_seen) {
16564 const char *start = p->lex.pcur - 1, *ptr = start;
16565 do {
16566 int n = parser_precise_mbclen(p, ptr);
16567 if (n < 0) return -1;
16568 ptr += n;
16569 } while (ptr < p->lex.pend && is_identchar(ptr, p->lex.pend, p->enc));
16570 rb_warn2("`?' just followed by `%.*s' is interpreted as" \
16571 " a conditional operator, put a space after `?'",
16572 WARN_I((int)(ptr - start)), WARN_S_L(start, (ptr - start)));
16573 }
16574 goto ternary;
16575 }
16576 else if (c == '\\') {
16577 if (peek(p, 'u')) {
16578 nextc(p);
16579 enc = rb_utf8_encoding();
16580 tokadd_utf8(p, &enc, -1, 0, 0);
16581 }
16582 else if (!lex_eol_p(p) && !(c = *p->lex.pcur, ISASCII(c))) {
16583 nextc(p);
16584 if (tokadd_mbchar(p, c) == -1) return 0;
16585 }
16586 else {
16587 c = read_escape(p, 0, &enc);
16588 tokadd(p, c);
16589 }
16590 }
16591 else {
16592 tokadd(p, c);
16593 }
16594 tokfix(p);
16595 lit = STR_NEW3(tok(p), toklen(p), enc, 0);
16596 set_yylval_str(lit);
16597 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
16598 return tCHAR;
16599}
16600
16601static enum yytokentype
16602parse_percent(struct parser_params *p, const int space_seen, const enum lex_state_e last_state)
16603{
16604 register int c;
16605 const char *ptok = p->lex.pcur;
16606
16607 if (IS_BEG()) {
16608 int term;
16609 int paren;
16610
16611 c = nextc(p);
16612 quotation:
16613 if (c == -1) goto unterminated;
16614 if (!ISALNUM(c)) {
16615 term = c;
16616 if (!ISASCII(c)) goto unknown;
16617 c = 'Q';
16618 }
16619 else {
16620 term = nextc(p);
16621 if (rb_enc_isalnum(term, p->enc) || !parser_isascii(p)) {
16622 unknown:
16623 pushback(p, term);
16624 c = parser_precise_mbclen(p, p->lex.pcur);
16625 if (c < 0) return 0;
16626 p->lex.pcur += c;
16627 yyerror0("unknown type of %string");
16628 return 0;
16629 }
16630 }
16631 if (term == -1) {
16632 unterminated:
16633 compile_error(p, "unterminated quoted string meets end of file");
16634 return 0;
16635 }
16636 paren = term;
16637 if (term == '(') term = ')';
16638 else if (term == '[') term = ']';
16639 else if (term == '{') term = '}';
16640 else if (term == '<') term = '>';
16641 else paren = 0;
16642
16643 p->lex.ptok = ptok-1;
16644 switch (c) {
16645 case 'Q':
16646 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_dquote, term, paren);
16647 return tSTRING_BEG;
16648
16649 case 'q':
16650 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_squote, term, paren);
16651 return tSTRING_BEG;
16652
16653 case 'W':
16654 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_dword, term, paren);
16655 return tWORDS_BEG;
16656
16657 case 'w':
16658 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_sword, term, paren);
16659 return tQWORDS_BEG;
16660
16661 case 'I':
16662 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_dword, term, paren);
16663 return tSYMBOLS_BEG;
16664
16665 case 'i':
16666 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_sword, term, paren);
16667 return tQSYMBOLS_BEG;
16668
16669 case 'x':
16670 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_xquote, term, paren);
16671 return tXSTRING_BEG;
16672
16673 case 'r':
16674 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_regexp, term, paren);
16675 return tREGEXP_BEG;
16676
16677 case 's':
16678 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_ssym, term, paren);
16679 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_FNAME|EXPR_FITEM);
16680 return tSYMBEG;
16681
16682 default:
16683 yyerror0("unknown type of %string");
16684 return 0;
16685 }
16686 }
16687 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
16688 set_yylval_id('%');
16689 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
16690 return tOP_ASGN;
16691 }
16692 if (IS_SPCARG(c) || (IS_lex_state(EXPR_FITEM) && c == 's')) {
16693 goto quotation;
16694 }
16695 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
16696 pushback(p, c);
16697 return warn_balanced('%', "%%", "string literal");
16698}
16699
16700static int
16701tokadd_ident(struct parser_params *p, int c)
16702{
16703 do {
16704 if (tokadd_mbchar(p, c) == -1) return -1;
16705 c = nextc(p);
16706 } while (parser_is_identchar(p));
16707 pushback(p, c);
16708 return 0;
16709}
16710
16711static ID
16712tokenize_ident(struct parser_params *p, const enum lex_state_e last_state)
16713{
16714 ID ident = TOK_INTERN();
16715
16716 set_yylval_name(ident);
16717
16718 return ident;
16719}
16720
16721static int
16722parse_numvar(struct parser_params *p)
16723{
16724 size_t len;
16725 int overflow;
16726 unsigned long n = ruby_scan_digits(tok(p)+1, toklen(p)-1, 10, &len, &overflow);
16727 const unsigned long nth_ref_max =
16728 ((FIXNUM_MAX < INT_MAX) ? FIXNUM_MAX : INT_MAX) >> 1;
16729 /* NTH_REF is left-shifted to be ORed with back-ref flag and
16730 * turned into a Fixnum, in compile.c */
16731
16732 if (overflow || n > nth_ref_max) {
16733 /* compile_error()? */
16734 rb_warn1("`%s' is too big for a number variable, always nil", WARN_S(tok(p)));
16735 return 0; /* $0 is $PROGRAM_NAME, not NTH_REF */
16736 }
16737 else {
16738 return (int)n;
16739 }
16740}
16741
16742static enum yytokentype
16743parse_gvar(struct parser_params *p, const enum lex_state_e last_state)
16744{
16745 const char *ptr = p->lex.pcur;
16746 register int c;
16747
16748 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
16749 p->lex.ptok = ptr - 1; /* from '$' */
16750 newtok(p);
16751 c = nextc(p);
16752 switch (c) {
16753 case '_': /* $_: last read line string */
16754 c = nextc(p);
16755 if (parser_is_identchar(p)) {
16756 tokadd(p, '$');
16757 tokadd(p, '_');
16758 break;
16759 }
16760 pushback(p, c);
16761 c = '_';
16762 /* fall through */
16763 case '~': /* $~: match-data */
16764 case '*': /* $*: argv */
16765 case '$': /* $$: pid */
16766 case '?': /* $?: last status */
16767 case '!': /* $!: error string */
16768 case '@': /* $@: error position */
16769 case '/': /* $/: input record separator */
16770 case '\\': /* $\: output record separator */
16771 case ';': /* $;: field separator */
16772 case ',': /* $,: output field separator */
16773 case '.': /* $.: last read line number */
16774 case '=': /* $=: ignorecase */
16775 case ':': /* $:: load path */
16776 case '<': /* $<: reading filename */
16777 case '>': /* $>: default output handle */
16778 case '\"': /* $": already loaded files */
16779 tokadd(p, '$');
16780 tokadd(p, c);
16781 goto gvar;
16782
16783 case '-':
16784 tokadd(p, '$');
16785 tokadd(p, c);
16786 c = nextc(p);
16787 if (parser_is_identchar(p)) {
16788 if (tokadd_mbchar(p, c) == -1) return 0;
16789 }
16790 else {
16791 pushback(p, c);
16792 pushback(p, '-');
16793 return '$';
16794 }
16795 gvar:
16796 set_yylval_name(TOK_INTERN());
16797 return tGVAR;
16798
16799 case '&': /* $&: last match */
16800 case '`': /* $`: string before last match */
16801 case '\'': /* $': string after last match */
16802 case '+': /* $+: string matches last paren. */
16803 if (IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_FNAME)) {
16804 tokadd(p, '$');
16805 tokadd(p, c);
16806 goto gvar;
16807 }
16808 set_yylval_node(NEW_BACK_REF(c, &_cur_loc));
16809 return tBACK_REF;
16810
16811 case '1': case '2': case '3':
16812 case '4': case '5': case '6':
16813 case '7': case '8': case '9':
16814 tokadd(p, '$');
16815 do {
16816 tokadd(p, c);
16817 c = nextc(p);
16818 } while (c != -1 && ISDIGIT(c));
16819 pushback(p, c);
16820 if (IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_FNAME)) goto gvar;
16821 tokfix(p);
16822 c = parse_numvar(p);
16823 set_yylval_node(NEW_NTH_REF(c, &_cur_loc));
16824 return tNTH_REF;
16825
16826 default:
16827 if (!parser_is_identchar(p)) {
16828 YYLTYPE loc = RUBY_INIT_YYLLOC();
16829 if (c == -1 || ISSPACE(c)) {
16830 compile_error(p, "`$' without identifiers is not allowed as a global variable name");
16831 }
16832 else {
16833 pushback(p, c);
16834 compile_error(p, "`$%c' is not allowed as a global variable name", c);
16835 }
16836 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
16837 set_yylval_noname();
16838 return tGVAR;
16839 }
16840 /* fall through */
16841 case '0':
16842 tokadd(p, '$');
16843 }
16844
16845 if (tokadd_ident(p, c)) return 0;
16846 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
16847 tokenize_ident(p, last_state);
16848 return tGVAR;
16849}
16850
16851#ifndef RIPPER
16852static bool
16853parser_numbered_param(struct parser_params *p, int n)
16854{
16855 if (n < 0) return false;
16856
16857 if (DVARS_TERMINAL_P(p->lvtbl->args) || DVARS_TERMINAL_P(p->lvtbl->args->prev)) {
16858 return false;
16859 }
16860 if (p->max_numparam == ORDINAL_PARAM) {
16861 compile_error(p, "ordinary parameter is defined");
16862 return false;
16863 }
16864 struct vtable *args = p->lvtbl->args;
16865 if (p->max_numparam < n) {
16866 p->max_numparam = n;
16867 }
16868 while (n > args->pos) {
16869 vtable_add(args, NUMPARAM_IDX_TO_ID(args->pos+1));
16870 }
16871 return true;
16872}
16873#endif
16874
16875static enum yytokentype
16876parse_atmark(struct parser_params *p, const enum lex_state_e last_state)
16877{
16878 const char *ptr = p->lex.pcur;
16879 enum yytokentype result = tIVAR;
16880 register int c = nextc(p);
16881 YYLTYPE loc;
16882
16883 p->lex.ptok = ptr - 1; /* from '@' */
16884 newtok(p);
16885 tokadd(p, '@');
16886 if (c == '@') {
16887 result = tCVAR;
16888 tokadd(p, '@');
16889 c = nextc(p);
16890 }
16891 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_FNAME) ? EXPR_ENDFN : EXPR_END);
16892 if (c == -1 || !parser_is_identchar(p)) {
16893 pushback(p, c);
16894 RUBY_SET_YYLLOC(loc);
16895 if (result == tIVAR) {
16896 compile_error(p, "`@' without identifiers is not allowed as an instance variable name");
16897 }
16898 else {
16899 compile_error(p, "`@@' without identifiers is not allowed as a class variable name");
16900 }
16901 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
16902 set_yylval_noname();
16903 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
16904 return result;
16905 }
16906 else if (ISDIGIT(c)) {
16907 pushback(p, c);
16908 RUBY_SET_YYLLOC(loc);
16909 if (result == tIVAR) {
16910 compile_error(p, "`@%c' is not allowed as an instance variable name", c);
16911 }
16912 else {
16913 compile_error(p, "`@@%c' is not allowed as a class variable name", c);
16914 }
16915 parser_show_error_line(p, &loc);
16916 set_yylval_noname();
16917 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
16918 return result;
16919 }
16920
16921 if (tokadd_ident(p, c)) return 0;
16922 tokenize_ident(p, last_state);
16923 return result;
16924}
16925
16926static enum yytokentype
16927parse_ident(struct parser_params *p, int c, int cmd_state)
16928{
16929 enum yytokentype result;
16930 int mb = ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT;
16931 const enum lex_state_e last_state = p->lex.state;
16932 ID ident;
16933
16934 do {
16935 if (!ISASCII(c)) mb = ENC_CODERANGE_UNKNOWN;
16936 if (tokadd_mbchar(p, c) == -1) return 0;
16937 c = nextc(p);
16938 } while (parser_is_identchar(p));
16939 if ((c == '!' || c == '?') && !peek(p, '=')) {
16940 result = tFID;
16941 tokadd(p, c);
16942 }
16943 else if (c == '=' && IS_lex_state(EXPR_FNAME) &&
16944 (!peek(p, '~') && !peek(p, '>') && (!peek(p, '=') || (peek_n(p, '>', 1))))) {
16945 result = tIDENTIFIER;
16946 tokadd(p, c);
16947 }
16948 else {
16949 result = tCONSTANT; /* assume provisionally */
16950 pushback(p, c);
16951 }
16952 tokfix(p);
16953
16954 if (IS_LABEL_POSSIBLE()) {
16955 if (IS_LABEL_SUFFIX(0)) {
16956 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG|EXPR_LABELED);
16957 nextc(p);
16958 set_yylval_name(TOK_INTERN());
16959 return tLABEL;
16960 }
16961 }
16962 if (mb == ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT && !IS_lex_state(EXPR_DOT)) {
16963 const struct kwtable *kw;
16964
16965 /* See if it is a reserved word. */
16966 kw = rb_reserved_word(tok(p), toklen(p));
16967 if (kw) {
16968 enum lex_state_e state = p->lex.state;
16969 if (IS_lex_state_for(state, EXPR_FNAME)) {
16970 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ENDFN);
16971 set_yylval_name(rb_intern2(tok(p), toklen(p)));
16972 return kw->id[0];
16973 }
16974 SET_LEX_STATE(kw->state);
16975 if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_BEG)) {
16976 p->command_start = TRUE;
16977 }
16978 if (kw->id[0] == keyword_do) {
16979 if (lambda_beginning_p()) {
16980 p->lex.lpar_beg = -1; /* make lambda_beginning_p() == FALSE in the body of "-> do ... end" */
16981 return keyword_do_LAMBDA;
16982 }
16983 if (COND_P()) return keyword_do_cond;
16984 if (CMDARG_P() && !IS_lex_state_for(state, EXPR_CMDARG))
16985 return keyword_do_block;
16986 return keyword_do;
16987 }
16988 if (IS_lex_state_for(state, (EXPR_BEG | EXPR_LABELED)))
16989 return kw->id[0];
16990 else {
16991 if (kw->id[0] != kw->id[1])
16992 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG | EXPR_LABEL);
16993 return kw->id[1];
16994 }
16995 }
16996 }
16997
16998 if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_BEG_ANY | EXPR_ARG_ANY | EXPR_DOT)) {
16999 if (cmd_state) {
17000 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_CMDARG);
17001 }
17002 else {
17003 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17004 }
17005 }
17006 else if (p->lex.state == EXPR_FNAME) {
17007 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ENDFN);
17008 }
17009 else {
17010 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
17011 }
17012
17013 ident = tokenize_ident(p, last_state);
17014 if (result == tCONSTANT && is_local_id(ident)) result = tIDENTIFIER;
17015 if (!IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_DOT|EXPR_FNAME) &&
17016 (result == tIDENTIFIER) && /* not EXPR_FNAME, not attrasgn */
17017 lvar_defined(p, ident)) {
17018 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END|EXPR_LABEL);
17019 }
17020 return result;
17021}
17022
17023static enum yytokentype
17024parser_yylex(struct parser_params *p)
17025{
17026 register int c;
17027 int space_seen = 0;
17028 int cmd_state;
17029 int label;
17030 enum lex_state_e last_state;
17031 int fallthru = FALSE;
17032 int token_seen = p->token_seen;
17033
17034 if (p->lex.strterm) {
17035 if (p->lex.strterm->flags & STRTERM_HEREDOC) {
17036 return here_document(p, &p->lex.strterm->u.heredoc);
17037 }
17038 else {
17039 token_flush(p);
17040 return parse_string(p, &p->lex.strterm->u.literal);
17041 }
17042 }
17043 cmd_state = p->command_start;
17044 p->command_start = FALSE;
17045 p->token_seen = TRUE;
17046 retry:
17047 last_state = p->lex.state;
17048#ifndef RIPPER
17049 token_flush(p);
17050#endif
17051 switch (c = nextc(p)) {
17052 case '\0': /* NUL */
17053 case '\004': /* ^D */
17054 case '\032': /* ^Z */
17055 case -1: /* end of script. */
17056 return 0;
17057
17058 /* white spaces */
17059 case '\r':
17060 if (!p->cr_seen) {
17061 p->cr_seen = TRUE;
17062 /* carried over with p->lex.nextline for nextc() */
17063 rb_warn0("encountered \\r in middle of line, treated as a mere space");
17064 }
17065 /* fall through */
17066 case ' ': case '\t': case '\f':
17067 case '\13': /* '\v' */
17068 space_seen = 1;
17069#ifdef RIPPER
17070 while ((c = nextc(p))) {
17071 switch (c) {
17072 case ' ': case '\t': case '\f': case '\r':
17073 case '\13': /* '\v' */
17074 break;
17075 default:
17076 goto outofloop;
17077 }
17078 }
17079 outofloop:
17080 pushback(p, c);
17081 dispatch_scan_event(p, tSP);
17082#endif
17083 goto retry;
17084
17085 case '#': /* it's a comment */
17086 p->token_seen = token_seen;
17087 /* no magic_comment in shebang line */
17088 if (!parser_magic_comment(p, p->lex.pcur, p->lex.pend - p->lex.pcur)) {
17089 if (comment_at_top(p)) {
17090 set_file_encoding(p, p->lex.pcur, p->lex.pend);
17091 }
17092 }
17093 lex_goto_eol(p);
17094 dispatch_scan_event(p, tCOMMENT);
17095 fallthru = TRUE;
17096 /* fall through */
17097 case '\n':
17098 p->token_seen = token_seen;
17099 c = (IS_lex_state(EXPR_BEG|EXPR_CLASS|EXPR_FNAME|EXPR_DOT) &&
17100 !IS_lex_state(EXPR_LABELED));
17101 if (c || IS_lex_state_all(EXPR_ARG|EXPR_LABELED)) {
17102 if (!fallthru) {
17103 dispatch_scan_event(p, tIGNORED_NL);
17104 }
17105 fallthru = FALSE;
17106 if (!c && p->ctxt.in_kwarg) {
17107 goto normal_newline;
17108 }
17109 goto retry;
17110 }
17111 while (1) {
17112 switch (c = nextc(p)) {
17113 case ' ': case '\t': case '\f': case '\r':
17114 case '\13': /* '\v' */
17115 space_seen = 1;
17116 break;
17117 case '#':
17118 pushback(p, c);
17119 if (space_seen) dispatch_scan_event(p, tSP);
17120 goto retry;
17121 case '&':
17122 case '.': {
17123 dispatch_delayed_token(p, tIGNORED_NL);
17124 if (peek(p, '.') == (c == '&')) {
17125 pushback(p, c);
17126 dispatch_scan_event(p, tSP);
17127 goto retry;
17128 }
17129 }
17130 default:
17131 p->ruby_sourceline--;
17132 p->lex.nextline = p->lex.lastline;
17133 case -1: /* EOF no decrement*/
17134#ifndef RIPPER
17135 if (p->lex.prevline && !p->eofp) p->lex.lastline = p->lex.prevline;
17136 p->lex.pbeg = RSTRING_PTR(p->lex.lastline);
17137 p->lex.pend = p->lex.pcur = p->lex.pbeg + RSTRING_LEN(p->lex.lastline);
17138 pushback(p, 1); /* always pushback */
17139 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pcur;
17140#else
17141 lex_goto_eol(p);
17142 if (c != -1) {
17143 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pcur;
17144 }
17145#endif
17146 goto normal_newline;
17147 }
17148 }
17149 normal_newline:
17150 p->command_start = TRUE;
17151 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17152 return '\n';
17153
17154 case '*':
17155 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '*') {
17156 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17157 set_yylval_id(idPow);
17158 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17159 return tOP_ASGN;
17160 }
17161 pushback(p, c);
17162 if (IS_SPCARG(c)) {
17163 rb_warning0("`**' interpreted as argument prefix");
17164 c = tDSTAR;
17165 }
17166 else if (IS_BEG()) {
17167 c = tDSTAR;
17168 }
17169 else {
17170 c = warn_balanced((enum ruby_method_ids)tPOW, "**", "argument prefix");
17171 }
17172 }
17173 else {
17174 if (c == '=') {
17175 set_yylval_id('*');
17176 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17177 return tOP_ASGN;
17178 }
17179 pushback(p, c);
17180 if (IS_SPCARG(c)) {
17181 rb_warning0("`*' interpreted as argument prefix");
17182 c = tSTAR;
17183 }
17184 else if (IS_BEG()) {
17185 c = tSTAR;
17186 }
17187 else {
17188 c = warn_balanced('*', "*", "argument prefix");
17189 }
17190 }
17191 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
17192 return c;
17193
17194 case '!':
17195 c = nextc(p);
17196 if (IS_AFTER_OPERATOR()) {
17197 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17198 if (c == '@') {
17199 return '!';
17200 }
17201 }
17202 else {
17203 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17204 }
17205 if (c == '=') {
17206 return tNEQ;
17207 }
17208 if (c == '~') {
17209 return tNMATCH;
17210 }
17211 pushback(p, c);
17212 return '!';
17213
17214 case '=':
17215 if (was_bol(p)) {
17216 /* skip embedded rd document */
17217 if (word_match_p(p, "begin", 5)) {
17218 int first_p = TRUE;
17219
17220 lex_goto_eol(p);
17221 dispatch_scan_event(p, tEMBDOC_BEG);
17222 for (;;) {
17223 lex_goto_eol(p);
17224 if (!first_p) {
17225 dispatch_scan_event(p, tEMBDOC);
17226 }
17227 first_p = FALSE;
17228 c = nextc(p);
17229 if (c == -1) {
17230 compile_error(p, "embedded document meets end of file");
17231 return 0;
17232 }
17233 if (c == '=' && word_match_p(p, "end", 3)) {
17234 break;
17235 }
17236 pushback(p, c);
17237 }
17238 lex_goto_eol(p);
17239 dispatch_scan_event(p, tEMBDOC_END);
17240 goto retry;
17241 }
17242 }
17243
17244 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
17245 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17246 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17247 return tEQQ;
17248 }
17249 pushback(p, c);
17250 return tEQ;
17251 }
17252 if (c == '~') {
17253 return tMATCH;
17254 }
17255 else if (c == '>') {
17256 return tASSOC;
17257 }
17258 pushback(p, c);
17259 return '=';
17260
17261 case '<':
17262 c = nextc(p);
17263 if (c == '<' &&
17264 !IS_lex_state(EXPR_DOT | EXPR_CLASS) &&
17265 !IS_END() &&
17266 (!IS_ARG() || IS_lex_state(EXPR_LABELED) || space_seen)) {
17267 int token = heredoc_identifier(p);
17268 if (token) return token < 0 ? 0 : token;
17269 }
17270 if (IS_AFTER_OPERATOR()) {
17271 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17272 }
17273 else {
17274 if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_CLASS))
17275 p->command_start = TRUE;
17276 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17277 }
17278 if (c == '=') {
17279 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '>') {
17280 return tCMP;
17281 }
17282 pushback(p, c);
17283 return tLEQ;
17284 }
17285 if (c == '<') {
17286 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17287 set_yylval_id(idLTLT);
17288 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17289 return tOP_ASGN;
17290 }
17291 pushback(p, c);
17292 return warn_balanced((enum ruby_method_ids)tLSHFT, "<<", "here document");
17293 }
17294 pushback(p, c);
17295 return '<';
17296
17297 case '>':
17298 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
17299 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17300 return tGEQ;
17301 }
17302 if (c == '>') {
17303 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17304 set_yylval_id(idGTGT);
17305 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17306 return tOP_ASGN;
17307 }
17308 pushback(p, c);
17309 return tRSHFT;
17310 }
17311 pushback(p, c);
17312 return '>';
17313
17314 case '"':
17315 label = (IS_LABEL_POSSIBLE() ? str_label : 0);
17316 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_dquote | label, '"', 0);
17317 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pcur-1;
17318 return tSTRING_BEG;
17319
17320 case '`':
17321 if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_FNAME)) {
17322 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ENDFN);
17323 return c;
17324 }
17325 if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_DOT)) {
17326 if (cmd_state)
17327 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_CMDARG);
17328 else
17329 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17330 return c;
17331 }
17332 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_xquote, '`', 0);
17333 return tXSTRING_BEG;
17334
17335 case '\'':
17336 label = (IS_LABEL_POSSIBLE() ? str_label : 0);
17337 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_squote | label, '\'', 0);
17338 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pcur-1;
17339 return tSTRING_BEG;
17340
17341 case '?':
17342 return parse_qmark(p, space_seen);
17343
17344 case '&':
17345 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '&') {
17346 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17347 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17348 set_yylval_id(idANDOP);
17349 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17350 return tOP_ASGN;
17351 }
17352 pushback(p, c);
17353 return tANDOP;
17354 }
17355 else if (c == '=') {
17356 set_yylval_id('&');
17357 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17358 return tOP_ASGN;
17359 }
17360 else if (c == '.') {
17361 set_yylval_id(idANDDOT);
17362 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_DOT);
17363 return tANDDOT;
17364 }
17365 pushback(p, c);
17366 if (IS_SPCARG(c)) {
17367 if ((c != ':') ||
17368 (c = peekc_n(p, 1)) == -1 ||
17369 !(c == '\'' || c == '"' ||
17370 is_identchar((p->lex.pcur+1), p->lex.pend, p->enc))) {
17371 rb_warning0("`&' interpreted as argument prefix");
17372 }
17373 c = tAMPER;
17374 }
17375 else if (IS_BEG()) {
17376 c = tAMPER;
17377 }
17378 else {
17379 c = warn_balanced('&', "&", "argument prefix");
17380 }
17381 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
17382 return c;
17383
17384 case '|':
17385 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '|') {
17386 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17387 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17388 set_yylval_id(idOROP);
17389 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17390 return tOP_ASGN;
17391 }
17392 pushback(p, c);
17393 if (IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_BEG)) {
17394 c = '|';
17395 pushback(p, '|');
17396 return c;
17397 }
17398 return tOROP;
17399 }
17400 if (c == '=') {
17401 set_yylval_id('|');
17402 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17403 return tOP_ASGN;
17404 }
17405 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG|EXPR_LABEL);
17406 pushback(p, c);
17407 return '|';
17408
17409 case '+':
17410 c = nextc(p);
17411 if (IS_AFTER_OPERATOR()) {
17412 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17413 if (c == '@') {
17414 return tUPLUS;
17415 }
17416 pushback(p, c);
17417 return '+';
17418 }
17419 if (c == '=') {
17420 set_yylval_id('+');
17421 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17422 return tOP_ASGN;
17423 }
17424 if (IS_BEG() || (IS_SPCARG(c) && arg_ambiguous(p, '+'))) {
17425 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17426 pushback(p, c);
17427 if (c != -1 && ISDIGIT(c)) {
17428 return parse_numeric(p, '+');
17429 }
17430 return tUPLUS;
17431 }
17432 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17433 pushback(p, c);
17434 return warn_balanced('+', "+", "unary operator");
17435
17436 case '-':
17437 c = nextc(p);
17438 if (IS_AFTER_OPERATOR()) {
17439 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17440 if (c == '@') {
17441 return tUMINUS;
17442 }
17443 pushback(p, c);
17444 return '-';
17445 }
17446 if (c == '=') {
17447 set_yylval_id('-');
17448 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17449 return tOP_ASGN;
17450 }
17451 if (c == '>') {
17452 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ENDFN);
17453 return tLAMBDA;
17454 }
17455 if (IS_BEG() || (IS_SPCARG(c) && arg_ambiguous(p, '-'))) {
17456 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17457 pushback(p, c);
17458 if (c != -1 && ISDIGIT(c)) {
17459 return tUMINUS_NUM;
17460 }
17461 return tUMINUS;
17462 }
17463 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17464 pushback(p, c);
17465 return warn_balanced('-', "-", "unary operator");
17466
17467 case '.': {
17468 int is_beg = IS_BEG();
17469 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17470 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '.') {
17471 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '.') {
17472 if (p->ctxt.in_argdef) {
17473 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ENDARG);
17474 return tBDOT3;
17475 }
17476 if (p->lex.paren_nest == 0 && looking_at_eol_p(p)) {
17477 rb_warn0("... at EOL, should be parenthesized?");
17478 }
17479 else if (p->lex.lpar_beg >= 0 && p->lex.lpar_beg+1 == p->lex.paren_nest) {
17480 if (IS_lex_state_for(last_state, EXPR_LABEL))
17481 return tDOT3;
17482 }
17483 return is_beg ? tBDOT3 : tDOT3;
17484 }
17485 pushback(p, c);
17486 return is_beg ? tBDOT2 : tDOT2;
17487 }
17488 pushback(p, c);
17489 if (c != -1 && ISDIGIT(c)) {
17490 char prev = p->lex.pcur-1 > p->lex.pbeg ? *(p->lex.pcur-2) : 0;
17491 parse_numeric(p, '.');
17492 if (ISDIGIT(prev)) {
17493 yyerror0("unexpected fraction part after numeric literal");
17494 }
17495 else {
17496 yyerror0("no .<digit> floating literal anymore; put 0 before dot");
17497 }
17498 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
17499 p->lex.ptok = p->lex.pcur;
17500 goto retry;
17501 }
17502 set_yylval_id('.');
17503 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_DOT);
17504 return '.';
17505 }
17506
17507 case '0': case '1': case '2': case '3': case '4':
17508 case '5': case '6': case '7': case '8': case '9':
17509 return parse_numeric(p, c);
17510
17511 case ')':
17512 COND_POP();
17513 CMDARG_POP();
17514 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ENDFN);
17515 p->lex.paren_nest--;
17516 return c;
17517
17518 case ']':
17519 COND_POP();
17520 CMDARG_POP();
17521 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
17522 p->lex.paren_nest--;
17523 return c;
17524
17525 case '}':
17526 /* tSTRING_DEND does COND_POP and CMDARG_POP in the yacc's rule */
17527 if (!p->lex.brace_nest--) return tSTRING_DEND;
17528 COND_POP();
17529 CMDARG_POP();
17530 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_END);
17531 p->lex.paren_nest--;
17532 return c;
17533
17534 case ':':
17535 c = nextc(p);
17536 if (c == ':') {
17537 if (IS_BEG() || IS_lex_state(EXPR_CLASS) || IS_SPCARG(-1)) {
17538 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17539 return tCOLON3;
17540 }
17541 set_yylval_id(idCOLON2);
17542 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_DOT);
17543 return tCOLON2;
17544 }
17545 if (IS_END() || ISSPACE(c) || c == '#') {
17546 pushback(p, c);
17547 c = warn_balanced(':', ":", "symbol literal");
17548 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17549 return c;
17550 }
17551 switch (c) {
17552 case '\'':
17553 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_ssym, c, 0);
17554 break;
17555 case '"':
17556 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_dsym, c, 0);
17557 break;
17558 default:
17559 pushback(p, c);
17560 break;
17561 }
17562 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_FNAME);
17563 return tSYMBEG;
17564
17565 case '/':
17566 if (IS_BEG()) {
17567 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_regexp, '/', 0);
17568 return tREGEXP_BEG;
17569 }
17570 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17571 set_yylval_id('/');
17572 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17573 return tOP_ASGN;
17574 }
17575 pushback(p, c);
17576 if (IS_SPCARG(c)) {
17577 arg_ambiguous(p, '/');
17578 p->lex.strterm = NEW_STRTERM(str_regexp, '/', 0);
17579 return tREGEXP_BEG;
17580 }
17581 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
17582 return warn_balanced('/', "/", "regexp literal");
17583
17584 case '^':
17585 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17586 set_yylval_id('^');
17587 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17588 return tOP_ASGN;
17589 }
17590 SET_LEX_STATE(IS_AFTER_OPERATOR() ? EXPR_ARG : EXPR_BEG);
17591 pushback(p, c);
17592 return '^';
17593
17594 case ';':
17595 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17596 p->command_start = TRUE;
17597 return ';';
17598
17599 case ',':
17600 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG|EXPR_LABEL);
17601 return ',';
17602
17603 case '~':
17604 if (IS_AFTER_OPERATOR()) {
17605 if ((c = nextc(p)) != '@') {
17606 pushback(p, c);
17607 }
17608 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17609 }
17610 else {
17611 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17612 }
17613 return '~';
17614
17615 case '(':
17616 if (IS_BEG()) {
17617 c = tLPAREN;
17618 }
17619 else if (!space_seen) {
17620 /* foo( ... ) => method call, no ambiguity */
17621 }
17622 else if (IS_ARG() || IS_lex_state_all(EXPR_END|EXPR_LABEL)) {
17623 c = tLPAREN_ARG;
17624 }
17625 else if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_ENDFN) && !lambda_beginning_p()) {
17626 rb_warning0("parentheses after method name is interpreted as "
17627 "an argument list, not a decomposed argument");
17628 }
17629 p->lex.paren_nest++;
17630 COND_PUSH(0);
17631 CMDARG_PUSH(0);
17632 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG|EXPR_LABEL);
17633 return c;
17634
17635 case '[':
17636 p->lex.paren_nest++;
17637 if (IS_AFTER_OPERATOR()) {
17638 if ((c = nextc(p)) == ']') {
17639 p->lex.paren_nest--;
17640 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG);
17641 if ((c = nextc(p)) == '=') {
17642 return tASET;
17643 }
17644 pushback(p, c);
17645 return tAREF;
17646 }
17647 pushback(p, c);
17648 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_ARG|EXPR_LABEL);
17649 return '[';
17650 }
17651 else if (IS_BEG()) {
17652 c = tLBRACK;
17653 }
17654 else if (IS_ARG() && (space_seen || IS_lex_state(EXPR_LABELED))) {
17655 c = tLBRACK;
17656 }
17657 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG|EXPR_LABEL);
17658 COND_PUSH(0);
17659 CMDARG_PUSH(0);
17660 return c;
17661
17662 case '{':
17663 ++p->lex.brace_nest;
17664 if (lambda_beginning_p())
17665 c = tLAMBEG;
17666 else if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_LABELED))
17667 c = tLBRACE; /* hash */
17668 else if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_ARG_ANY | EXPR_END | EXPR_ENDFN))
17669 c = '{'; /* block (primary) */
17670 else if (IS_lex_state(EXPR_ENDARG))
17671 c = tLBRACE_ARG; /* block (expr) */
17672 else
17673 c = tLBRACE; /* hash */
17674 if (c != tLBRACE) {
17675 p->command_start = TRUE;
17676 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG);
17677 }
17678 else {
17679 SET_LEX_STATE(EXPR_BEG|EXPR_LABEL);
17680 }
17681 ++p->lex.paren_nest; /* after lambda_beginning_p() */
17682 COND_PUSH(0);
17683 CMDARG_PUSH(0);
17684 return c;
17685
17686 case '\\':
17687 c = nextc(p);
17688 if (c == '\n') {
17689 space_seen = 1;
17690 dispatch_scan_event(p, tSP);
17691 goto retry; /* skip \\n */
17692 }
17693 if (c == ' ') return tSP;
17694 if (ISSPACE(c)) return c;
17695 pushback(p, c);
17696 return '\\';
17697
17698 case '%':
17699 return parse_percent(p, space_seen, last_state);
17700
17701 case '$':
17702 return parse_gvar(p, last_state);
17703
17704 case '@':
17705 return parse_atmark(p, last_state);
17706
17707 case '_':
17708 if (was_bol(p) && whole_match_p(p, "__END__", 7, 0)) {
17709 p->ruby__end__seen = 1;
17710 p->eofp = 1;
17711#ifndef RIPPER
17712 return -1;
17713#else
17714 lex_goto_eol(p);
17715 dispatch_scan_event(p, k__END__);
17716 return 0;
17717#endif
17718 }
17719 newtok(p);
17720 break;
17721
17722 default:
17723 if (!parser_is_identchar(p)) {
17724 compile_error(p, "Invalid char `\\x%02X' in expression", c);
17725 token_flush(p);
17726 goto retry;
17727 }
17728
17729 newtok(p);
17730 break;
17731 }
17732
17733 return parse_ident(p, c, cmd_state);
17734}
17735
17736static enum yytokentype
17737yylex(YYSTYPE *lval, YYLTYPE *yylloc, struct parser_params *p)
17738{
17739 enum yytokentype t;
17740
17741 p->lval = lval;
17742 lval->val = Qundef;
17743 t = parser_yylex(p);
17744
17745 if (p->lex.strterm && (p->lex.strterm->flags & STRTERM_HEREDOC))
17746 RUBY_SET_YYLLOC_FROM_STRTERM_HEREDOC(*yylloc);
17747 else
17748 RUBY_SET_YYLLOC(*yylloc);
17749
17750 if (has_delayed_token(p))
17751 dispatch_delayed_token(p, t);
17752 else if (t != 0)
17753 dispatch_scan_event(p, t);
17754
17755 return t;
17756}
17757
17758#define LVAR_USED ((ID)1 << (sizeof(ID) * CHAR_BIT - 1))
17759
17760static NODE*
17761node_newnode(struct parser_params *p, enum node_type type, VALUE a0, VALUE a1, VALUE a2, const rb_code_location_t *loc)
17762{
17763 NODE *n = rb_ast_newnode(p->ast, type);
17764
17765 rb_node_init(n, type, a0, a1, a2);
17766
17767 nd_set_loc(n, loc);
17768 nd_set_node_id(n, parser_get_node_id(p));
17769 return n;
17770}

17773nd_set_loc(NODE *nd, const YYLTYPE *loc)
17774{
17775 nd->nd_loc = *loc;
17776 nd_set_line(nd, loc->beg_pos.lineno);
17777 return nd;
17778}

17804fixpos(NODE *node, NODE *orig)
17805{
17806 if (!node) return;
17807 if (!orig) return;
17808 nd_set_line(node, nd_line(orig));
17809}

17814 rb_compile_warning(p->ruby_sourcefile, nd_line(node), "%s", mesg);

17822
17823static NODE*
17824block_append(struct parser_params *p, NODE *head, NODE *tail)
17825{
17826 NODE *end, *h = head, *nd;
17827
17828 if (tail == 0) return head;
17829
17830 if (h == 0) return tail;
17831 switch (nd_type(h)) {
17832 case NODE_LIT:
17833 case NODE_STR:
17834 case NODE_SELF:
17835 case NODE_TRUE:
17836 case NODE_FALSE:
17837 case NODE_NIL:
17838 parser_warning(p, h, "unused literal ignored");
17839 return tail;
17840 default:
17841 h = end = NEW_BLOCK(head, &head->nd_loc);
17842 end->nd_end = end;
17843 head = end;
17844 break;
17845 case NODE_BLOCK:
17846 end = h->nd_end;
17847 break;
17848 }
17849
17850 nd = end->nd_head;
17851 switch (nd_type(nd)) {
17852 case NODE_RETURN:
17853 case NODE_BREAK:
17854 case NODE_NEXT:
17855 case NODE_REDO:
17856 case NODE_RETRY:
17857 if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) {
17858 parser_warning(p, tail, "statement not reached");
17859 }
17860 break;
17861
17862 default:
17863 break;
17864 }
17865
17866 if (!nd_type_p(tail, NODE_BLOCK)) {
17867 tail = NEW_BLOCK(tail, &tail->nd_loc);
17868 tail->nd_end = tail;
17869 }
17870 end->nd_next = tail;
17871 h->nd_end = tail->nd_end;
17872 nd_set_last_loc(head, nd_last_loc(tail));
17873 return head;
17874}
17875
17876/* append item to the list */
17877static NODE*
17878list_append(struct parser_params *p, NODE *list, NODE *item)
17879{
17880 NODE *last;
17881
17882 if (list == 0) return NEW_LIST(item, &item->nd_loc);
17883 if (list->nd_next) {
17884 last = list->nd_next->nd_end;
17885 }
17886 else {
17887 last = list;
17888 }
17889
17890 list->nd_alen += 1;
17891 last->nd_next = NEW_LIST(item, &item->nd_loc);
17892 list->nd_next->nd_end = last->nd_next;
17893
17894 nd_set_last_loc(list, nd_last_loc(item));
17895
17896 return list;
17897}
17898
17899/* concat two lists */
17900static NODE*
17901list_concat(NODE *head, NODE *tail)
17902{
17903 NODE *last;
17904
17905 if (head->nd_next) {
17906 last = head->nd_next->nd_end;
17907 }
17908 else {
17909 last = head;
17910 }
17911
17912 head->nd_alen += tail->nd_alen;
17913 last->nd_next = tail;
17914 if (tail->nd_next) {
17915 head->nd_next->nd_end = tail->nd_next->nd_end;
17916 }
17917 else {
17918 head->nd_next->nd_end = tail;
17919 }
17920
17921 nd_set_last_loc(head, nd_last_loc(tail));
17922
17923 return head;
17924}
17925
17926static int
17927literal_concat0(struct parser_params *p, VALUE head, VALUE tail)
17928{
17929 if (NIL_P(tail)) return 1;
17930 if (!rb_enc_compatible(head, tail)) {
17931 compile_error(p, "string literal encodings differ (%s / %s)",
17932 rb_enc_name(rb_enc_get(head)),
17933 rb_enc_name(rb_enc_get(tail)));
17934 rb_str_resize(head, 0);
17935 rb_str_resize(tail, 0);
17936 return 0;
17937 }
17938 rb_str_buf_append(head, tail);
17939 return 1;
17940}
17941
17942static VALUE
17943string_literal_head(enum node_type htype, NODE *head)
17944{
17945 if (htype != NODE_DSTR) return Qfalse;
17946 if (head->nd_next) {
17947 head = head->nd_next->nd_end->nd_head;
17948 if (!head || !nd_type_p(head, NODE_STR)) return Qfalse;
17949 }
17950 const VALUE lit = head->nd_lit;
17951 ASSUME(lit != Qfalse);
17952 return lit;
17953}
17954
17955/* concat two string literals */
17956static NODE *
17957literal_concat(struct parser_params *p, NODE *head, NODE *tail, const YYLTYPE *loc)
17958{
17959 enum node_type htype;
17960 VALUE lit;
17961
17962 if (!head) return tail;
17963 if (!tail) return head;
17964
17965 htype = nd_type(head);
17966 if (htype == NODE_EVSTR) {
17967 head = new_dstr(p, head, loc);
17968 htype = NODE_DSTR;
17969 }
17970 if (p->heredoc_indent > 0) {
17971 switch (htype) {
17972 case NODE_STR:
17973 nd_set_type(head, NODE_DSTR);
17974 case NODE_DSTR:
17975 return list_append(p, head, tail);
17976 default:
17977 break;
17978 }
17979 }
17980 switch (nd_type(tail)) {
17981 case NODE_STR:
17982 if ((lit = string_literal_head(htype, head)) != Qfalse) {
17983 htype = NODE_STR;
17984 }
17985 else {
17986 lit = head->nd_lit;
17987 }
17988 if (htype == NODE_STR) {
17989 if (!literal_concat0(p, lit, tail->nd_lit)) {
17990 error:
17991 rb_discard_node(p, head);
17992 rb_discard_node(p, tail);
17993 return 0;
17994 }
17995 rb_discard_node(p, tail);
17996 }
17997 else {
17998 list_append(p, head, tail);
17999 }
18000 break;
18001
18002 case NODE_DSTR:
18003 if (htype == NODE_STR) {
18004 if (!literal_concat0(p, head->nd_lit, tail->nd_lit))
18005 goto error;
18006 tail->nd_lit = head->nd_lit;
18007 rb_discard_node(p, head);
18008 head = tail;
18009 }
18010 else if (NIL_P(tail->nd_lit)) {
18011 append:
18012 head->nd_alen += tail->nd_alen - 1;
18013 if (!head->nd_next) {
18014 head->nd_next = tail->nd_next;
18015 }
18016 else if (tail->nd_next) {
18017 head->nd_next->nd_end->nd_next = tail->nd_next;
18018 head->nd_next->nd_end = tail->nd_next->nd_end;
18019 }
18020 rb_discard_node(p, tail);
18021 }
18022 else if ((lit = string_literal_head(htype, head)) != Qfalse) {
18023 if (!literal_concat0(p, lit, tail->nd_lit))
18024 goto error;
18025 tail->nd_lit = Qnil;
18026 goto append;
18027 }
18028 else {
18029 list_concat(head, NEW_NODE(NODE_LIST, NEW_STR(tail->nd_lit, loc), tail->nd_alen, tail->nd_next, loc));
18030 }
18031 break;
18032
18033 case NODE_EVSTR:
18034 if (htype == NODE_STR) {
18035 nd_set_type(head, NODE_DSTR);
18036 head->nd_alen = 1;
18037 }
18038 list_append(p, head, tail);
18039 break;
18040 }
18041 return head;
18042}
18043
18044static NODE *
18045evstr2dstr(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
18046{
18047 if (nd_type_p(node, NODE_EVSTR)) {
18048 node = new_dstr(p, node, &node->nd_loc);
18049 }
18050 return node;
18051}

18053static NODE *
18054new_evstr(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18055{
18056 NODE *head = node;
18057
18058 if (node) {
18059 switch (nd_type(node)) {
18060 case NODE_STR:
18061 nd_set_type(node, NODE_DSTR);
18062 return node;
18063 case NODE_DSTR:
18064 break;
18065 case NODE_EVSTR:
18066 return node;
18067 }
18068 }
18069 return NEW_EVSTR(head, loc);
18070}

18074{

18077 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, lit);
18078 return list_append(p, dstr, node);
18079}

18081static NODE *

18103static NODE *
18104new_qcall(struct parser_params* p, ID atype, NODE *recv, ID mid, NODE *args, const YYLTYPE *op_loc, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18105{
18106 NODE *qcall = NEW_QCALL(atype, recv, mid, args, loc);
18107 nd_set_line(qcall, op_loc->beg_pos.lineno);

18110
18111static NODE*
18112new_command_qcall(struct parser_params* p, ID atype, NODE *recv, ID mid, NODE *args, NODE *block, const YYLTYPE *op_loc, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18113{
18114 NODE *ret;
18115 if (block) block_dup_check(p, args, block);
18116 ret = new_qcall(p, atype, recv, mid, args, op_loc, loc);
18117 if (block) ret = method_add_block(p, ret, block, loc);
18118 fixpos(ret, recv);
18119 return ret;
18120}
18121
18122#define nd_once_body(node) (nd_type_p((node), NODE_ONCE) ? (node)->nd_body : node)
18123static NODE*
18124match_op(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node1, NODE *node2, const YYLTYPE *op_loc, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18125{
18126 NODE *n;
18127 int line = op_loc->beg_pos.lineno;
18128
18129 value_expr(node1);
18130 value_expr(node2);
18131 if (node1 && (n = nd_once_body(node1)) != 0) {
18132 switch (nd_type(n)) {
18133 case NODE_DREGX:
18134 {
18135 NODE *match = NEW_MATCH2(node1, node2, loc);
18136 nd_set_line(match, line);
18137 return match;
18138 }
18139
18140 case NODE_LIT:
18141 if (RB_TYPE_P(n->nd_lit, T_REGEXP)) {
18142 const VALUE lit = n->nd_lit;
18143 NODE *match = NEW_MATCH2(node1, node2, loc);
18144 match->nd_args = reg_named_capture_assign(p, lit, loc);
18145 nd_set_line(match, line);
18146 return match;
18147 }
18148 }
18149 }
18150
18151 if (node2 && (n = nd_once_body(node2)) != 0) {
18152 NODE *match3;
18153
18154 switch (nd_type(n)) {
18155 case NODE_LIT:
18156 if (!RB_TYPE_P(n->nd_lit, T_REGEXP)) break;
18157 /* fallthru */
18158 case NODE_DREGX:
18159 match3 = NEW_MATCH3(node2, node1, loc);
18160 return match3;
18161 }
18162 }
18163
18164 n = NEW_CALL(node1, tMATCH, NEW_LIST(node2, &node2->nd_loc), loc);
18165 nd_set_line(n, line);
18166 return n;
18167}
18168
18169# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
18170static int
18171past_dvar_p(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
18172{
18173 struct vtable *past = p->lvtbl->past;
18174 while (past) {
18175 if (vtable_included(past, id)) return 1;
18176 past = past->prev;
18177 }
18178 return 0;
18179}
18180# endif
18181
18182static int
18183numparam_nested_p(struct parser_params *p)
18184{
18185 struct local_vars *local = p->lvtbl;
18186 NODE *outer = local->numparam.outer;
18187 NODE *inner = local->numparam.inner;
18188 if (outer || inner) {
18189 NODE *used = outer ? outer : inner;
18190 compile_error(p, "numbered parameter is already used in\n"
18191 "%s:%d: %s block here",
18192 p->ruby_sourcefile, nd_line(used),
18193 outer ? "outer" : "inner");
18194 parser_show_error_line(p, &used->nd_loc);
18195 return 1;
18196 }
18197 return 0;
18198}
18199
18200static NODE*
18201gettable(struct parser_params *p, ID id, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18202{
18203 ID *vidp = NULL;
18204 NODE *node;
18205 switch (id) {
18206 case keyword_self:
18207 return NEW_SELF(loc);
18208 case keyword_nil:
18209 return NEW_NIL(loc);
18210 case keyword_true:
18211 return NEW_TRUE(loc);
18212 case keyword_false:
18213 return NEW_FALSE(loc);
18214 case keyword__FILE__:
18215 {
18216 VALUE file = p->ruby_sourcefile_string;
18217 if (NIL_P(file))
18218 file = rb_str_new(0, 0);
18219 else
18220 file = rb_str_dup(file);
18221 node = NEW_STR(file, loc);
18222 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, file);
18223 }
18224 return node;
18225 case keyword__LINE__:
18226 return NEW_LIT(INT2FIX(p->tokline), loc);
18227 case keyword__ENCODING__:
18228 node = NEW_LIT(rb_enc_from_encoding(p->enc), loc);
18229 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, node->nd_lit);
18230 return node;
18231
18232 }
18233 switch (id_type(id)) {
18234 case ID_LOCAL:
18235 if (dyna_in_block(p) && dvar_defined_ref(p, id, &vidp)) {
18236 if (NUMPARAM_ID_P(id) && numparam_nested_p(p)) return 0;
18237 if (id == p->cur_arg) {
18238 compile_error(p, "circular argument reference - %"PRIsWARN, rb_id2str(id));
18239 return 0;
18240 }
18241 if (vidp) *vidp |= LVAR_USED;
18242 node = NEW_DVAR(id, loc);
18243 return node;
18244 }
18245 if (local_id_ref(p, id, &vidp)) {
18246 if (id == p->cur_arg) {
18247 compile_error(p, "circular argument reference - %"PRIsWARN, rb_id2str(id));
18248 return 0;
18249 }
18250 if (vidp) *vidp |= LVAR_USED;
18251 node = NEW_LVAR(id, loc);
18252 return node;
18253 }
18254 if (dyna_in_block(p) && NUMPARAM_ID_P(id) &&
18255 parser_numbered_param(p, NUMPARAM_ID_TO_IDX(id))) {
18256 if (numparam_nested_p(p)) return 0;
18257 node = NEW_DVAR(id, loc);
18258 struct local_vars *local = p->lvtbl;
18259 if (!local->numparam.current) local->numparam.current = node;
18260 return node;
18261 }
18262# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
18263 if (!p->ctxt.in_defined && RTEST(ruby_verbose) && past_dvar_p(p, id)) {
18264 rb_warning1("possible reference to past scope - %"PRIsWARN, rb_id2str(id));
18265 }
18266# endif
18267 /* method call without arguments */
18268 return NEW_VCALL(id, loc);
18269 case ID_GLOBAL:
18270 return NEW_GVAR(id, loc);
18271 case ID_INSTANCE:
18272 return NEW_IVAR(id, loc);
18273 case ID_CONST:
18274 return NEW_CONST(id, loc);
18275 case ID_CLASS:
18276 return NEW_CVAR(id, loc);
18277 }
18278 compile_error(p, "identifier %"PRIsVALUE" is not valid to get", rb_id2str(id));
18279 return 0;
18280}
18281
18282static NODE *
18283opt_arg_append(NODE *opt_list, NODE *opt)
18284{
18285 NODE *opts = opt_list;
18286 opts->nd_loc.end_pos = opt->nd_loc.end_pos;
18287
18288 while (opts->nd_next) {
18289 opts = opts->nd_next;
18290 opts->nd_loc.end_pos = opt->nd_loc.end_pos;
18291 }
18292 opts->nd_next = opt;
18293
18294 return opt_list;
18295}
18296
18297static NODE *
18298kwd_append(NODE *kwlist, NODE *kw)
18299{
18300 if (kwlist) {
18301 NODE *kws = kwlist;
18302 kws->nd_loc.end_pos = kw->nd_loc.end_pos;
18303 while (kws->nd_next) {
18304 kws = kws->nd_next;
18305 kws->nd_loc.end_pos = kw->nd_loc.end_pos;
18306 }
18307 kws->nd_next = kw;
18308 }
18309 return kwlist;
18310}

18312static NODE *
18313new_defined(struct parser_params *p, NODE *expr, const YYLTYPE *loc)

18317
18318static NODE*
18319symbol_append(struct parser_params *p, NODE *symbols, NODE *symbol)
18320{
18321 enum node_type type = nd_type(symbol);
18322 switch (type) {
18323 case NODE_DSTR:
18324 nd_set_type(symbol, NODE_DSYM);
18325 break;
18326 case NODE_STR:
18327 nd_set_type(symbol, NODE_LIT);
18328 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, symbol->nd_lit = rb_str_intern(symbol->nd_lit));
18329 break;
18330 default:
18331 compile_error(p, "unexpected node as symbol: %s", ruby_node_name(type));
18332 }
18333 return list_append(p, symbols, symbol);
18334}
18335
18336static NODE *
18337new_regexp(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, int options, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18338{
18339 NODE *list, *prev;
18340 VALUE lit;
18341
18342 if (!node) {
18343 node = NEW_LIT(reg_compile(p, STR_NEW0(), options), loc);
18344 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, node->nd_lit);
18345 return node;
18346 }
18347 switch (nd_type(node)) {
18348 case NODE_STR:
18349 {
18350 VALUE src = node->nd_lit;
18351 nd_set_type(node, NODE_LIT);
18352 nd_set_loc(node, loc);
18353 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, node->nd_lit = reg_compile(p, src, options));
18354 }
18355 break;
18356 default:
18357 lit = STR_NEW0();
18358 node = NEW_NODE(NODE_DSTR, lit, 1, NEW_LIST(node, loc), loc);
18359 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, lit);
18360 /* fall through */
18361 case NODE_DSTR:
18362 nd_set_type(node, NODE_DREGX);
18363 nd_set_loc(node, loc);
18364 node->nd_cflag = options & RE_OPTION_MASK;
18365 if (!NIL_P(node->nd_lit)) reg_fragment_check(p, node->nd_lit, options);
18366 for (list = (prev = node)->nd_next; list; list = list->nd_next) {
18367 NODE *frag = list->nd_head;
18368 enum node_type type = nd_type(frag);
18369 if (type == NODE_STR || (type == NODE_DSTR && !frag->nd_next)) {
18370 VALUE tail = frag->nd_lit;
18371 if (reg_fragment_check(p, tail, options) && prev && !NIL_P(prev->nd_lit)) {
18372 VALUE lit = prev == node ? prev->nd_lit : prev->nd_head->nd_lit;
18373 if (!literal_concat0(p, lit, tail)) {
18374 return NEW_NIL(loc); /* dummy node on error */
18375 }
18376 rb_str_resize(tail, 0);
18377 prev->nd_next = list->nd_next;
18378 rb_discard_node(p, list->nd_head);
18379 rb_discard_node(p, list);
18380 list = prev;
18381 }
18382 else {
18383 prev = list;
18384 }
18385 }
18386 else {
18387 prev = 0;
18388 }
18389 }
18390 if (!node->nd_next) {
18391 VALUE src = node->nd_lit;
18392 nd_set_type(node, NODE_LIT);
18393 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, node->nd_lit = reg_compile(p, src, options));
18394 }
18395 if (options & RE_OPTION_ONCE) {
18396 node = NEW_NODE(NODE_ONCE, 0, node, 0, loc);
18397 }
18398 break;
18399 }
18400 return node;
18401}
18402
18403static NODE *
18404new_kw_arg(struct parser_params *p, NODE *k, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18405{
18406 if (!k) return 0;
18407 return NEW_KW_ARG(0, (k), loc);
18408}
18409
18410static NODE *
18411new_xstring(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18412{
18413 if (!node) {
18414 VALUE lit = STR_NEW0();
18415 NODE *xstr = NEW_XSTR(lit, loc);
18416 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, lit);
18417 return xstr;
18418 }
18419 switch (nd_type(node)) {
18420 case NODE_STR:
18421 nd_set_type(node, NODE_XSTR);
18422 nd_set_loc(node, loc);
18423 break;
18424 case NODE_DSTR:
18425 nd_set_type(node, NODE_DXSTR);
18426 nd_set_loc(node, loc);
18427 break;
18428 default:
18429 node = NEW_NODE(NODE_DXSTR, Qnil, 1, NEW_LIST(node, loc), loc);
18430 break;
18431 }
18432 return node;
18433}
18434
18435static void
18436check_literal_when(struct parser_params *p, NODE *arg, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18437{
18438 VALUE lit;
18439
18440 if (!arg || !p->case_labels) return;
18441
18442 lit = rb_node_case_when_optimizable_literal(arg);
18443 if (lit == Qundef) return;
18444 if (nd_type_p(arg, NODE_STR)) {
18445 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, arg->nd_lit = lit);
18446 }
18447
18448 if (NIL_P(p->case_labels)) {
18449 p->case_labels = rb_obj_hide(rb_hash_new());
18450 }
18451 else {
18452 VALUE line = rb_hash_lookup(p->case_labels, lit);
18453 if (!NIL_P(line)) {
18454 rb_warning1("duplicated `when' clause with line %d is ignored",
18455 WARN_IVAL(line));
18456 return;
18457 }
18458 }
18459 rb_hash_aset(p->case_labels, lit, INT2NUM(p->ruby_sourceline));
18460}
18461
18462#else /* !RIPPER */
18463static int
18464id_is_var(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
18465{
18466 if (is_notop_id(id)) {
18467 switch (id & ID_SCOPE_MASK) {
18468 case ID_GLOBAL: case ID_INSTANCE: case ID_CONST: case ID_CLASS:
18469 return 1;
18470 case ID_LOCAL:
18471 if (dyna_in_block(p)) {
18472 if (NUMPARAM_ID_P(id) || dvar_defined(p, id)) return 1;
18473 }
18474 if (local_id(p, id)) return 1;
18475 /* method call without arguments */
18476 return 0;
18477 }
18478 }
18479 compile_error(p, "identifier %"PRIsVALUE" is not valid to get", rb_id2str(id));
18480 return 0;
18481}
18482
18483static VALUE
18484new_regexp(struct parser_params *p, VALUE re, VALUE opt, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18485{
18486 VALUE src = 0, err;
18487 int options = 0;
18488 if (ripper_is_node_yylval(re)) {
18489 src = RNODE(re)->nd_cval;
18490 re = RNODE(re)->nd_rval;
18491 }
18492 if (ripper_is_node_yylval(opt)) {
18493 options = (int)RNODE(opt)->nd_tag;
18494 opt = RNODE(opt)->nd_rval;
18495 }
18496 if (src && NIL_P(parser_reg_compile(p, src, options, &err))) {
18497 compile_error(p, "%"PRIsVALUE, err);
18498 }
18499 return dispatch2(regexp_literal, re, opt);
18500}
18501#endif /* !RIPPER */

18503static inline enum lex_state_e
18504parser_set_lex_state(struct parser_params *p, enum lex_state_e ls, int line)
18505{
18506 if (p->debug) {
18507 ls = rb_parser_trace_lex_state(p, p->lex.state, ls, line);
18508 }
18509 return p->lex.state = ls;
18510}
18511
18512#ifndef RIPPER
18513static const char rb_parser_lex_state_names[][8] = {
18514 "BEG", "END", "ENDARG", "ENDFN", "ARG",
18515 "CMDARG", "MID", "FNAME", "DOT", "CLASS",
18516 "LABEL", "LABELED","FITEM",
18517};
18518
18519static VALUE
18520append_lex_state_name(enum lex_state_e state, VALUE buf)
18521{
18522 int i, sep = 0;
18523 unsigned int mask = 1;
18524 static const char none[] = "NONE";
18525
18526 for (i = 0; i < EXPR_MAX_STATE; ++i, mask <<= 1) {
18527 if ((unsigned)state & mask) {
18528 if (sep) {
18529 rb_str_cat(buf, "|", 1);
18530 }
18531 sep = 1;
18532 rb_str_cat_cstr(buf, rb_parser_lex_state_names[i]);
18533 }
18534 }
18535 if (!sep) {
18536 rb_str_cat(buf, none, sizeof(none)-1);
18537 }
18538 return buf;
18539}
18540
18541static void
18542flush_debug_buffer(struct parser_params *p, VALUE out, VALUE str)
18543{
18544 VALUE mesg = p->debug_buffer;
18545
18546 if (!NIL_P(mesg) && RSTRING_LEN(mesg)) {
18547 p->debug_buffer = Qnil;
18548 rb_io_puts(1, &mesg, out);
18549 }
18550 if (!NIL_P(str) && RSTRING_LEN(str)) {
18551 rb_io_write(p->debug_output, str);
18552 }
18553}
18554
18555enum lex_state_e
18556rb_parser_trace_lex_state(struct parser_params *p, enum lex_state_e from,
18557 enum lex_state_e to, int line)
18558{
18559 VALUE mesg;
18560 mesg = rb_str_new_cstr("lex_state: ");
18561 append_lex_state_name(from, mesg);
18562 rb_str_cat_cstr(mesg, " -> ");
18563 append_lex_state_name(to, mesg);
18564 rb_str_catf(mesg, " at line %d\n", line);
18565 flush_debug_buffer(p, p->debug_output, mesg);
18566 return to;
18567}
18568
18569VALUE
18570rb_parser_lex_state_name(enum lex_state_e state)
18571{
18572 return rb_fstring(append_lex_state_name(state, rb_str_new(0, 0)));
18573}
18574
18575static void
18576append_bitstack_value(stack_type stack, VALUE mesg)
18577{
18578 if (stack == 0) {
18579 rb_str_cat_cstr(mesg, "0");
18580 }
18581 else {
18582 stack_type mask = (stack_type)1U << (CHAR_BIT * sizeof(stack_type) - 1);
18583 for (; mask && !(stack & mask); mask >>= 1) continue;
18584 for (; mask; mask >>= 1) rb_str_cat(mesg, stack & mask ? "1" : "0", 1);
18585 }
18586}
18587
18588void
18589rb_parser_show_bitstack(struct parser_params *p, stack_type stack,
18590 const char *name, int line)
18591{
18592 VALUE mesg = rb_sprintf("%s: ", name);
18593 append_bitstack_value(stack, mesg);
18594 rb_str_catf(mesg, " at line %d\n", line);
18595 flush_debug_buffer(p, p->debug_output, mesg);
18596}
18597
18598void
18599rb_parser_fatal(struct parser_params *p, const char *fmt, ...)
18600{
18601 va_list ap;
18602 VALUE mesg = rb_str_new_cstr("internal parser error: ");
18603
18604 va_start(ap, fmt);
18605 rb_str_vcatf(mesg, fmt, ap);
18606 va_end(ap);
18607 yyerror0(RSTRING_PTR(mesg));
18608 RB_GC_GUARD(mesg);
18609
18610 mesg = rb_str_new(0, 0);
18611 append_lex_state_name(p->lex.state, mesg);
18612 compile_error(p, "lex.state: %"PRIsVALUE, mesg);
18613 rb_str_resize(mesg, 0);
18614 append_bitstack_value(p->cond_stack, mesg);
18615 compile_error(p, "cond_stack: %"PRIsVALUE, mesg);
18616 rb_str_resize(mesg, 0);
18617 append_bitstack_value(p->cmdarg_stack, mesg);
18618 compile_error(p, "cmdarg_stack: %"PRIsVALUE, mesg);
18619 if (p->debug_output == rb_ractor_stdout())
18620 p->debug_output = rb_ractor_stderr();
18621 p->debug = TRUE;
18622}

18625rb_parser_set_pos(YYLTYPE *yylloc, int sourceline, int beg_pos, int end_pos)
18626{
18627 yylloc->beg_pos.lineno = sourceline;
18628 yylloc->beg_pos.column = beg_pos;
18629 yylloc->end_pos.lineno = sourceline;
18630 yylloc->end_pos.column = end_pos;
18631 return yylloc;
18632}

18634YYLTYPE *
18635rb_parser_set_location_from_strterm_heredoc(struct parser_params *p, rb_strterm_heredoc_t *here, YYLTYPE *yylloc)
18636{
18637 int sourceline = here->sourceline;
18638 int beg_pos = (int)here->offset - here->quote
18639 - (rb_strlen_lit("<<-") - !(here->func & STR_FUNC_INDENT));
18640 int end_pos = (int)here->offset + here->length + here->quote;
18641
18642 return rb_parser_set_pos(yylloc, sourceline, beg_pos, end_pos);
18643}

18649 int beg_pos = (int)(p->lex.ptok - p->lex.pbeg);
18650 int end_pos = (int)(p->lex.ptok - p->lex.pbeg);
18651 return rb_parser_set_pos(yylloc, sourceline, beg_pos, end_pos);
18652}
