18658 int beg_pos = (int)(p->lex.ptok - p->lex.pbeg);
18659 int end_pos = (int)(p->lex.pcur - p->lex.pbeg);
18660 return rb_parser_set_pos(yylloc, sourceline, beg_pos, end_pos);

18663
18664static int
18665assignable0(struct parser_params *p, ID id, const char **err)
18666{
18667 if (!id) return -1;
18668 switch (id) {
18669 case keyword_self:
18670 *err = "Can't change the value of self";
18671 return -1;
18672 case keyword_nil:
18673 *err = "Can't assign to nil";
18674 return -1;
18675 case keyword_true:
18676 *err = "Can't assign to true";
18677 return -1;
18678 case keyword_false:
18679 *err = "Can't assign to false";
18680 return -1;
18681 case keyword__FILE__:
18682 *err = "Can't assign to __FILE__";
18683 return -1;
18684 case keyword__LINE__:
18685 *err = "Can't assign to __LINE__";
18686 return -1;
18687 case keyword__ENCODING__:
18688 *err = "Can't assign to __ENCODING__";
18689 return -1;
18690 }
18691 switch (id_type(id)) {
18692 case ID_LOCAL:
18693 if (dyna_in_block(p)) {
18694 if (p->max_numparam > NO_PARAM && NUMPARAM_ID_P(id)) {
18695 compile_error(p, "Can't assign to numbered parameter _%d",
18696 NUMPARAM_ID_TO_IDX(id));
18697 return -1;
18698 }
18699 if (dvar_curr(p, id)) return NODE_DASGN;
18700 if (dvar_defined(p, id)) return NODE_DASGN;
18701 if (local_id(p, id)) return NODE_LASGN;
18702 dyna_var(p, id);
18703 return NODE_DASGN;
18704 }
18705 else {
18706 if (!local_id(p, id)) local_var(p, id);
18707 return NODE_LASGN;
18708 }
18709 break;
18710 case ID_GLOBAL: return NODE_GASGN;
18711 case ID_INSTANCE: return NODE_IASGN;
18712 case ID_CONST:
18713 if (!p->ctxt.in_def) return NODE_CDECL;
18714 *err = "dynamic constant assignment";
18715 return -1;
18716 case ID_CLASS: return NODE_CVASGN;
18717 default:
18718 compile_error(p, "identifier %"PRIsVALUE" is not valid to set", rb_id2str(id));
18719 }
18720 return -1;
18721}
18722
18723#ifndef RIPPER
18724static NODE*
18725assignable(struct parser_params *p, ID id, NODE *val, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18726{
18727 const char *err = 0;
18728 int node_type = assignable0(p, id, &err);
18729 switch (node_type) {
18730 case NODE_DASGN: return NEW_DASGN(id, val, loc);
18731 case NODE_LASGN: return NEW_LASGN(id, val, loc);
18732 case NODE_GASGN: return NEW_GASGN(id, val, loc);
18733 case NODE_IASGN: return NEW_IASGN(id, val, loc);
18734 case NODE_CDECL: return NEW_CDECL(id, val, 0, loc);
18735 case NODE_CVASGN: return NEW_CVASGN(id, val, loc);
18736 }
18737 if (err) yyerror1(loc, err);
18738 return NEW_BEGIN(0, loc);
18739}
18740#else
18741static VALUE
18742assignable(struct parser_params *p, VALUE lhs)
18743{
18744 const char *err = 0;
18745 assignable0(p, get_id(lhs), &err);
18746 if (err) lhs = assign_error(p, err, lhs);
18747 return lhs;
18748}
18749#endif

18751static int
18752is_private_local_id(ID name)
18753{
18754 VALUE s;
18755 if (name == idUScore) return 1;
18756 if (!is_local_id(name)) return 0;
18757 s = rb_id2str(name);
18758 if (!s) return 0;
18759 return RSTRING_PTR(s)[0] == '_';
18760}
18761
18762static int
18763shadowing_lvar_0(struct parser_params *p, ID name)
18764{
18765 if (dyna_in_block(p)) {
18766 if (dvar_curr(p, name)) {
18767 if (is_private_local_id(name)) return 1;
18768 yyerror0("duplicated argument name");
18769 }
18770 else if (dvar_defined(p, name) || local_id(p, name)) {
18771 vtable_add(p->lvtbl->vars, name);
18772 if (p->lvtbl->used) {
18773 vtable_add(p->lvtbl->used, (ID)p->ruby_sourceline | LVAR_USED);
18774 }
18775 return 0;
18776 }
18777 }
18778 else {
18779 if (local_id(p, name)) {
18780 if (is_private_local_id(name)) return 1;
18781 yyerror0("duplicated argument name");
18782 }
18783 }
18784 return 1;
18785}
18786
18787static ID
18788shadowing_lvar(struct parser_params *p, ID name)
18789{
18790 shadowing_lvar_0(p, name);
18791 return name;
18792}
18793
18794static void
18795new_bv(struct parser_params *p, ID name)
18796{
18797 if (!name) return;
18798 if (!is_local_id(name)) {
18799 compile_error(p, "invalid local variable - %"PRIsVALUE,
18800 rb_id2str(name));
18801 return;
18802 }
18803 if (!shadowing_lvar_0(p, name)) return;
18804 dyna_var(p, name);
18805}

18814static void
18815block_dup_check(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node1, NODE *node2)
18816{
18817 if (node2 && node1 && nd_type_p(node1, NODE_BLOCK_PASS)) {
18818 compile_error(p, "both block arg and actual block given");
18819 }
18820}

18829static void
18830rb_backref_error(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
18831{
18832 switch (nd_type(node)) {
18833 case NODE_NTH_REF:
18834 compile_error(p, "Can't set variable $%ld", node->nd_nth);
18835 break;
18836 case NODE_BACK_REF:
18837 compile_error(p, "Can't set variable $%c", (int)node->nd_nth);
18838 break;
18839 }
18840}
18841#else
18842static VALUE
18843backref_error(struct parser_params *p, NODE *ref, VALUE expr)
18844{
18845 VALUE mesg = rb_str_new_cstr("Can't set variable ");
18846 rb_str_append(mesg, ref->nd_cval);
18847 return dispatch2(assign_error, mesg, expr);
18848}

18851#ifndef RIPPER
18852static NODE *
18853arg_append(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node1, NODE *node2, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18854{
18855 if (!node1) return NEW_LIST(node2, &node2->nd_loc);
18856 switch (nd_type(node1)) {
18857 case NODE_LIST:
18858 return list_append(p, node1, node2);
18859 case NODE_BLOCK_PASS:
18860 node1->nd_head = arg_append(p, node1->nd_head, node2, loc);
18861 node1->nd_loc.end_pos = node1->nd_head->nd_loc.end_pos;
18862 return node1;
18863 case NODE_ARGSPUSH:
18864 node1->nd_body = list_append(p, NEW_LIST(node1->nd_body, &node1->nd_body->nd_loc), node2);
18865 node1->nd_loc.end_pos = node1->nd_body->nd_loc.end_pos;
18866 nd_set_type(node1, NODE_ARGSCAT);
18867 return node1;
18868 case NODE_ARGSCAT:
18869 if (!nd_type_p(node1->nd_body, NODE_LIST)) break;
18870 node1->nd_body = list_append(p, node1->nd_body, node2);
18871 node1->nd_loc.end_pos = node1->nd_body->nd_loc.end_pos;
18872 return node1;
18873 }
18874 return NEW_ARGSPUSH(node1, node2, loc);
18875}
18876
18877static NODE *
18878arg_concat(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node1, NODE *node2, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18879{
18880 if (!node2) return node1;
18881 switch (nd_type(node1)) {
18882 case NODE_BLOCK_PASS:
18883 if (node1->nd_head)
18884 node1->nd_head = arg_concat(p, node1->nd_head, node2, loc);
18885 else
18886 node1->nd_head = NEW_LIST(node2, loc);
18887 return node1;
18888 case NODE_ARGSPUSH:
18889 if (!nd_type_p(node2, NODE_LIST)) break;
18890 node1->nd_body = list_concat(NEW_LIST(node1->nd_body, loc), node2);
18891 nd_set_type(node1, NODE_ARGSCAT);
18892 return node1;
18893 case NODE_ARGSCAT:
18894 if (!nd_type_p(node2, NODE_LIST) ||
18895 !nd_type_p(node1->nd_body, NODE_LIST)) break;
18896 node1->nd_body = list_concat(node1->nd_body, node2);
18897 return node1;
18898 }
18899 return NEW_ARGSCAT(node1, node2, loc);
18900}
18901
18902static NODE *
18903last_arg_append(struct parser_params *p, NODE *args, NODE *last_arg, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18904{
18905 NODE *n1;
18906 if ((n1 = splat_array(args)) != 0) {
18907 return list_append(p, n1, last_arg);
18908 }
18909 return arg_append(p, args, last_arg, loc);
18910}
18911
18912static NODE *
18913rest_arg_append(struct parser_params *p, NODE *args, NODE *rest_arg, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18914{
18915 NODE *n1;
18916 if ((nd_type_p(rest_arg, NODE_LIST)) && (n1 = splat_array(args)) != 0) {
18917 return list_concat(n1, rest_arg);
18918 }
18919 return arg_concat(p, args, rest_arg, loc);
18920}
18921
18922static NODE *
18923splat_array(NODE* node)
18924{
18925 if (nd_type_p(node, NODE_SPLAT)) node = node->nd_head;
18926 if (nd_type_p(node, NODE_LIST)) return node;
18927 return 0;
18928}
18929
18930static void
18931mark_lvar_used(struct parser_params *p, NODE *rhs)
18932{
18933 ID *vidp = NULL;
18934 if (!rhs) return;
18935 switch (nd_type(rhs)) {
18936 case NODE_LASGN:
18937 if (local_id_ref(p, rhs->nd_vid, &vidp)) {
18938 if (vidp) *vidp |= LVAR_USED;
18939 }
18940 break;
18941 case NODE_DASGN:
18942 if (dvar_defined_ref(p, rhs->nd_vid, &vidp)) {
18943 if (vidp) *vidp |= LVAR_USED;
18944 }
18945 break;
18946#if 0
18947 case NODE_MASGN:
18948 for (rhs = rhs->nd_head; rhs; rhs = rhs->nd_next) {
18949 mark_lvar_used(p, rhs->nd_head);
18950 }
18951 break;
18952#endif
18953 }
18954}
18955
18956static NODE *
18957const_decl_path(struct parser_params *p, NODE **dest)
18958{
18959 NODE *n = *dest;
18960 if (!nd_type_p(n, NODE_CALL)) {
18961 const YYLTYPE *loc = &n->nd_loc;
18962 VALUE path;
18963 if (n->nd_vid) {
18964 path = rb_id2str(n->nd_vid);
18965 }
18966 else {
18967 n = n->nd_else;
18968 path = rb_ary_new();
18969 for (; n && nd_type_p(n, NODE_COLON2); n = n->nd_head) {
18970 rb_ary_push(path, rb_id2str(n->nd_mid));
18971 }
18972 if (n && nd_type_p(n, NODE_CONST)) {
18973 // Const::Name
18974 rb_ary_push(path, rb_id2str(n->nd_vid));
18975 }
18976 else if (n && nd_type_p(n, NODE_COLON3)) {
18977 // ::Const::Name
18978 rb_ary_push(path, rb_str_new(0, 0));
18979 }
18980 else {
18981 // expression::Name
18982 rb_ary_push(path, rb_str_new_cstr("..."));
18983 }
18984 path = rb_ary_join(rb_ary_reverse(path), rb_str_new_cstr("::"));
18985 path = rb_fstring(path);
18986 }
18987 *dest = n = NEW_LIT(path, loc);
18988 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, n->nd_lit);
18989 }
18990 return n;
18991}
18992
18993extern VALUE rb_mRubyVMFrozenCore;
18994
18995static NODE *
18996make_shareable_node(struct parser_params *p, NODE *value, bool copy, const YYLTYPE *loc)
18997{
18998 NODE *fcore = NEW_LIT(rb_mRubyVMFrozenCore, loc);
18999
19000 if (copy) {
19001 return NEW_CALL(fcore, rb_intern("make_shareable_copy"),
19002 NEW_LIST(value, loc), loc);
19003 }
19004 else {
19005 return NEW_CALL(fcore, rb_intern("make_shareable"),
19006 NEW_LIST(value, loc), loc);
19007 }
19008}
19009
19010static NODE *
19011ensure_shareable_node(struct parser_params *p, NODE **dest, NODE *value, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19012{
19013 NODE *fcore = NEW_LIT(rb_mRubyVMFrozenCore, loc);
19014 NODE *args = NEW_LIST(value, loc);
19015 args = list_append(p, args, const_decl_path(p, dest));
19016 return NEW_CALL(fcore, rb_intern("ensure_shareable"), args, loc);
19017}
19018
19019static int is_static_content(NODE *node);
19020
19021static VALUE
19022shareable_literal_value(NODE *node)
19023{
19024 if (!node) return Qnil;
19025 enum node_type type = nd_type(node);
19026 switch (type) {
19027 case NODE_TRUE:
19028 return Qtrue;
19029 case NODE_FALSE:
19030 return Qfalse;
19031 case NODE_NIL:
19032 return Qnil;
19033 case NODE_LIT:
19034 return node->nd_lit;
19035 default:
19036 return Qundef;
19037 }
19038}
19039
19040#ifndef SHAREABLE_BARE_EXPRESSION
19041#define SHAREABLE_BARE_EXPRESSION 1
19042#endif
19043
19044static NODE *
19045shareable_literal_constant(struct parser_params *p, enum shareability shareable,
19046 NODE **dest, NODE *value, const YYLTYPE *loc, size_t level)
19047{
19048# define shareable_literal_constant_next(n) \
19049 shareable_literal_constant(p, shareable, dest, (n), &(n)->nd_loc, level+1)
19050 VALUE lit = Qnil;
19051
19052 if (!value) return 0;
19053 enum node_type type = nd_type(value);
19054 switch (type) {
19055 case NODE_TRUE:
19056 case NODE_FALSE:
19057 case NODE_NIL:
19058 case NODE_LIT:
19059 return value;
19060
19061 case NODE_DSTR:
19062 if (shareable == shareable_literal) {
19063 value = NEW_CALL(value, idUMinus, 0, loc);
19064 }
19065 return value;
19066
19067 case NODE_STR:
19068 lit = rb_fstring(value->nd_lit);
19069 nd_set_type(value, NODE_LIT);
19070 RB_OBJ_WRITE(p->ast, &value->nd_lit, lit);
19071 return value;
19072
19073 case NODE_ZLIST:
19074 lit = rb_ary_new();
19075 OBJ_FREEZE_RAW(lit);
19076 NODE *n = NEW_LIT(lit, loc);
19077 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, n->nd_lit);
19078 return n;
19079
19080 case NODE_LIST:
19081 lit = rb_ary_new();
19082 for (NODE *n = value; n; n = n->nd_next) {
19083 NODE *elt = n->nd_head;
19084 if (elt) {
19085 elt = shareable_literal_constant_next(elt);
19086 if (elt) {
19087 n->nd_head = elt;
19088 }
19089 else if (RTEST(lit)) {
19090 rb_ary_clear(lit);
19091 lit = Qfalse;
19092 }
19093 }
19094 if (RTEST(lit)) {
19095 VALUE e = shareable_literal_value(elt);
19096 if (e != Qundef) {
19097 rb_ary_push(lit, e);
19098 }
19099 else {
19100 rb_ary_clear(lit);
19101 lit = Qnil; /* make shareable at runtime */
19102 }
19103 }
19104 }
19105 break;
19106
19107 case NODE_HASH:
19108 if (!value->nd_brace) return 0;
19109 lit = rb_hash_new();
19110 for (NODE *n = value->nd_head; n; n = n->nd_next->nd_next) {
19111 NODE *key = n->nd_head;
19112 NODE *val = n->nd_next->nd_head;
19113 if (key) {
19114 key = shareable_literal_constant_next(key);
19115 if (key) {
19116 n->nd_head = key;
19117 }
19118 else if (RTEST(lit)) {
19119 rb_hash_clear(lit);
19120 lit = Qfalse;
19121 }
19122 }
19123 if (val) {
19124 val = shareable_literal_constant_next(val);
19125 if (val) {
19126 n->nd_next->nd_head = val;
19127 }
19128 else if (RTEST(lit)) {
19129 rb_hash_clear(lit);
19130 lit = Qfalse;
19131 }
19132 }
19133 if (RTEST(lit)) {
19134 VALUE k = shareable_literal_value(key);
19135 VALUE v = shareable_literal_value(val);
19136 if (k != Qundef && v != Qundef) {
19137 rb_hash_aset(lit, k, v);
19138 }
19139 else {
19140 rb_hash_clear(lit);
19141 lit = Qnil; /* make shareable at runtime */
19142 }
19143 }
19144 }
19145 break;
19146
19147 default:
19148 if (shareable == shareable_literal &&
19149 (SHAREABLE_BARE_EXPRESSION || level > 0)) {
19150 return ensure_shareable_node(p, dest, value, loc);
19151 }
19152 return 0;
19153 }
19154
19155 /* Array or Hash */
19156 if (!lit) return 0;
19157 if (NIL_P(lit)) {
19158 // if shareable_literal, all elements should have been ensured
19159 // as shareable
19160 value = make_shareable_node(p, value, false, loc);
19161 }
19162 else {
19163 value = NEW_LIT(rb_ractor_make_shareable(lit), loc);
19164 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, value->nd_lit);
19165 }
19166
19167 return value;
19168# undef shareable_literal_constant_next
19169}
19170
19171static NODE *
19172shareable_constant_value(struct parser_params *p, enum shareability shareable,
19173 NODE *lhs, NODE *value, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19174{
19175 if (!value) return 0;
19176 switch (shareable) {
19177 case shareable_none:
19178 return value;
19179
19180 case shareable_literal:
19181 {
19182 NODE *lit = shareable_literal_constant(p, shareable, &lhs, value, loc, 0);
19183 if (lit) return lit;
19184 return value;
19185 }
19186 break;
19187
19188 case shareable_copy:
19189 case shareable_everything:
19190 {
19191 NODE *lit = shareable_literal_constant(p, shareable, &lhs, value, loc, 0);
19192 if (lit) return lit;
19193 return make_shareable_node(p, value, shareable == shareable_copy, loc);
19194 }
19195 break;
19196
19197 default:
19198 UNREACHABLE_RETURN(0);
19199 }
19200}
19201
19202static NODE *
19203node_assign(struct parser_params *p, NODE *lhs, NODE *rhs, struct lex_context ctxt, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19204{
19205 if (!lhs) return 0;
19206
19207 switch (nd_type(lhs)) {
19208 case NODE_CDECL:
19209 rhs = shareable_constant_value(p, ctxt.shareable_constant_value, lhs, rhs, loc);
19210 /* fallthru */
19211
19212 case NODE_GASGN:
19213 case NODE_IASGN:
19214 case NODE_LASGN:
19215 case NODE_DASGN:
19216 case NODE_MASGN:
19217 case NODE_CVASGN:
19218 lhs->nd_value = rhs;
19219 nd_set_loc(lhs, loc);
19220 break;
19221
19222 case NODE_ATTRASGN:
19223 lhs->nd_args = arg_append(p, lhs->nd_args, rhs, loc);
19224 nd_set_loc(lhs, loc);
19225 break;
19226
19227 default:
19228 /* should not happen */
19229 break;
19230 }
19231
19232 return lhs;
19233}
19234
19235static NODE *
19236value_expr_check(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
19237{
19238 NODE *void_node = 0, *vn;
19239
19240 if (!node) {
19241 rb_warning0("empty expression");
19242 }
19243 while (node) {
19244 switch (nd_type(node)) {
19245 case NODE_RETURN:
19246 case NODE_BREAK:
19247 case NODE_NEXT:
19248 case NODE_REDO:
19249 case NODE_RETRY:
19250 return void_node ? void_node : node;
19251
19252 case NODE_CASE3:
19253 if (!node->nd_body || !nd_type_p(node->nd_body, NODE_IN)) {
19254 compile_error(p, "unexpected node");
19255 return NULL;
19256 }
19257 if (node->nd_body->nd_body) {
19258 return NULL;
19259 }
19260 /* single line pattern matching */
19261 return void_node ? void_node : node;
19262
19263 case NODE_BLOCK:
19264 while (node->nd_next) {
19265 node = node->nd_next;
19266 }
19267 node = node->nd_head;
19268 break;
19269
19270 case NODE_BEGIN:
19271 node = node->nd_body;
19272 break;
19273
19274 case NODE_IF:
19275 case NODE_UNLESS:
19276 if (!node->nd_body) {
19277 return NULL;
19278 }
19279 else if (!node->nd_else) {
19280 return NULL;
19281 }
19282 vn = value_expr_check(p, node->nd_body);
19283 if (!vn) return NULL;
19284 if (!void_node) void_node = vn;
19285 node = node->nd_else;
19286 break;
19287
19288 case NODE_AND:
19289 case NODE_OR:
19290 node = node->nd_1st;
19291 break;
19292
19293 case NODE_LASGN:
19294 case NODE_DASGN:
19295 case NODE_MASGN:
19296 mark_lvar_used(p, node);
19297 return NULL;
19298
19299 default:
19300 return NULL;
19301 }
19302 }
19303
19304 return NULL;
19305}
19306
19307static int
19308value_expr_gen(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
19309{
19310 NODE *void_node = value_expr_check(p, node);
19311 if (void_node) {
19312 yyerror1(&void_node->nd_loc, "void value expression");
19313 /* or "control never reach"? */
19314 return FALSE;
19315 }
19316 return TRUE;
19317}
19318static void
19319void_expr(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
19320{
19321 const char *useless = 0;
19322
19323 if (!RTEST(ruby_verbose)) return;
19324
19325 if (!node || !(node = nd_once_body(node))) return;
19326 switch (nd_type(node)) {
19327 case NODE_OPCALL:
19328 switch (node->nd_mid) {
19329 case '+':
19330 case '-':
19331 case '*':
19332 case '/':
19333 case '%':
19334 case tPOW:
19335 case tUPLUS:
19336 case tUMINUS:
19337 case '|':
19338 case '^':
19339 case '&':
19340 case tCMP:
19341 case '>':
19342 case tGEQ:
19343 case '<':
19344 case tLEQ:
19345 case tEQ:
19346 case tNEQ:
19347 useless = rb_id2name(node->nd_mid);
19348 break;
19349 }
19350 break;
19351
19352 case NODE_LVAR:
19353 case NODE_DVAR:
19354 case NODE_GVAR:
19355 case NODE_IVAR:
19356 case NODE_CVAR:
19357 case NODE_NTH_REF:
19358 case NODE_BACK_REF:
19359 useless = "a variable";
19360 break;
19361 case NODE_CONST:
19362 useless = "a constant";
19363 break;
19364 case NODE_LIT:
19365 case NODE_STR:
19366 case NODE_DSTR:
19367 case NODE_DREGX:
19368 useless = "a literal";
19369 break;
19370 case NODE_COLON2:
19371 case NODE_COLON3:
19372 useless = "::";
19373 break;
19374 case NODE_DOT2:
19375 useless = "..";
19376 break;
19377 case NODE_DOT3:
19378 useless = "...";
19379 break;
19380 case NODE_SELF:
19381 useless = "self";
19382 break;
19383 case NODE_NIL:
19384 useless = "nil";
19385 break;
19386 case NODE_TRUE:
19387 useless = "true";
19388 break;
19389 case NODE_FALSE:
19390 useless = "false";
19391 break;
19392 case NODE_DEFINED:
19393 useless = "defined?";
19394 break;
19395 }
19396
19397 if (useless) {
19398 rb_warn1L(nd_line(node), "possibly useless use of %s in void context", WARN_S(useless));
19399 }
19400}
19401
19402static NODE *
19403void_stmts(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
19404{
19405 NODE *const n = node;
19406 if (!RTEST(ruby_verbose)) return n;
19407 if (!node) return n;
19408 if (!nd_type_p(node, NODE_BLOCK)) return n;
19409
19410 while (node->nd_next) {
19411 void_expr(p, node->nd_head);
19412 node = node->nd_next;
19413 }
19414 return n;
19415}
19416
19417static NODE *
19418remove_begin(NODE *node)
19419{
19420 NODE **n = &node, *n1 = node;
19421 while (n1 && nd_type_p(n1, NODE_BEGIN) && n1->nd_body) {
19422 *n = n1 = n1->nd_body;
19423 }
19424 return node;
19425}
19426
19427static NODE *
19428remove_begin_all(NODE *node)
19429{
19430 NODE **n = &node, *n1 = node;
19431 while (n1 && nd_type_p(n1, NODE_BEGIN)) {
19432 *n = n1 = n1->nd_body;
19433 }
19434 return node;
19435}
19436
19437static void
19438reduce_nodes(struct parser_params *p, NODE **body)
19439{
19440 NODE *node = *body;
19441
19442 if (!node) {
19443 *body = NEW_NIL(&NULL_LOC);
19444 return;
19445 }
19446#define subnodes(n1, n2) \
19447 ((!node->n1) ? (node->n2 ? (body = &node->n2, 1) : 0) : \
19448 (!node->n2) ? (body = &node->n1, 1) : \
19449 (reduce_nodes(p, &node->n1), body = &node->n2, 1))
19450
19451 while (node) {
19452 int newline = (int)(node->flags & NODE_FL_NEWLINE);
19453 switch (nd_type(node)) {
19454 end:
19455 case NODE_NIL:
19456 *body = 0;
19457 return;
19458 case NODE_RETURN:
19459 *body = node = node->nd_stts;
19460 if (newline && node) node->flags |= NODE_FL_NEWLINE;
19461 continue;
19462 case NODE_BEGIN:
19463 *body = node = node->nd_body;
19464 if (newline && node) node->flags |= NODE_FL_NEWLINE;
19465 continue;
19466 case NODE_BLOCK:
19467 body = &node->nd_end->nd_head;
19468 break;
19469 case NODE_IF:
19470 case NODE_UNLESS:
19471 if (subnodes(nd_body, nd_else)) break;
19472 return;
19473 case NODE_CASE:
19474 body = &node->nd_body;
19475 break;
19476 case NODE_WHEN:
19477 if (!subnodes(nd_body, nd_next)) goto end;
19478 break;
19479 case NODE_ENSURE:
19480 if (!subnodes(nd_head, nd_resq)) goto end;
19481 break;
19482 case NODE_RESCUE:
19483 if (node->nd_else) {
19484 body = &node->nd_resq;
19485 break;
19486 }
19487 if (!subnodes(nd_head, nd_resq)) goto end;
19488 break;
19489 default:
19490 return;
19491 }
19492 node = *body;
19493 if (newline && node) node->flags |= NODE_FL_NEWLINE;
19494 }
19495
19496#undef subnodes
19497}
19498
19499static int
19500is_static_content(NODE *node)
19501{
19502 if (!node) return 1;
19503 switch (nd_type(node)) {
19504 case NODE_HASH:
19505 if (!(node = node->nd_head)) break;
19506 case NODE_LIST:
19507 do {
19508 if (!is_static_content(node->nd_head)) return 0;
19509 } while ((node = node->nd_next) != 0);
19510 case NODE_LIT:
19511 case NODE_STR:
19512 case NODE_NIL:
19513 case NODE_TRUE:
19514 case NODE_FALSE:
19515 case NODE_ZLIST:
19516 break;
19517 default:
19518 return 0;
19519 }
19520 return 1;
19521}
19522
19523static int
19524assign_in_cond(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
19525{
19526 switch (nd_type(node)) {
19527 case NODE_MASGN:
19528 case NODE_LASGN:
19529 case NODE_DASGN:
19530 case NODE_GASGN:
19531 case NODE_IASGN:
19532 break;
19533
19534 default:
19535 return 0;
19536 }
19537
19538 if (!node->nd_value) return 1;
19539 if (is_static_content(node->nd_value)) {
19540 /* reports always */
19541 parser_warn(p, node->nd_value, "found `= literal' in conditional, should be ==");
19542 }
19543 return 1;
19544}
19545
19546enum cond_type {
19547 COND_IN_OP,
19548 COND_IN_COND,
19549 COND_IN_FF
19550};
19551
19552#define SWITCH_BY_COND_TYPE(t, w, arg) \
19553 switch (t) { \
19554 case COND_IN_OP: break; \
19555 case COND_IN_COND: rb_##w##0(arg "literal in condition"); break; \
19556 case COND_IN_FF: rb_##w##0(arg "literal in flip-flop"); break; \
19557 }
19558
19559static NODE *cond0(struct parser_params*,NODE*,enum cond_type,const YYLTYPE*);
19560
19561static NODE*
19562range_op(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19563{
19564 enum node_type type;
19565
19566 if (node == 0) return 0;
19567
19568 type = nd_type(node);
19569 value_expr(node);
19570 if (type == NODE_LIT && FIXNUM_P(node->nd_lit)) {
19571 if (!e_option_supplied(p)) parser_warn(p, node, "integer literal in flip-flop");
19572 ID lineno = rb_intern("$.");
19573 return NEW_CALL(node, tEQ, NEW_LIST(NEW_GVAR(lineno, loc), loc), loc);
19574 }
19575 return cond0(p, node, COND_IN_FF, loc);
19576}
19577
19578static NODE*
19579cond0(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, enum cond_type type, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19580{
19581 if (node == 0) return 0;
19582 if (!(node = nd_once_body(node))) return 0;
19583 assign_in_cond(p, node);
19584
19585 switch (nd_type(node)) {
19586 case NODE_DSTR:
19587 case NODE_EVSTR:
19588 case NODE_STR:
19589 SWITCH_BY_COND_TYPE(type, warn, "string ")
19590 break;
19591
19592 case NODE_DREGX:
19593 if (!e_option_supplied(p)) SWITCH_BY_COND_TYPE(type, warning, "regex ")
19594
19595 return NEW_MATCH2(node, NEW_GVAR(idLASTLINE, loc), loc);
19596
19597 case NODE_AND:
19598 case NODE_OR:
19599 node->nd_1st = cond0(p, node->nd_1st, COND_IN_COND, loc);
19600 node->nd_2nd = cond0(p, node->nd_2nd, COND_IN_COND, loc);
19601 break;
19602
19603 case NODE_DOT2:
19604 case NODE_DOT3:
19605 node->nd_beg = range_op(p, node->nd_beg, loc);
19606 node->nd_end = range_op(p, node->nd_end, loc);
19607 if (nd_type_p(node, NODE_DOT2)) nd_set_type(node,NODE_FLIP2);
19608 else if (nd_type_p(node, NODE_DOT3)) nd_set_type(node, NODE_FLIP3);
19609 break;
19610
19611 case NODE_DSYM:
19612 warn_symbol:
19613 SWITCH_BY_COND_TYPE(type, warning, "symbol ")
19614 break;
19615
19616 case NODE_LIT:
19617 if (RB_TYPE_P(node->nd_lit, T_REGEXP)) {
19618 if (!e_option_supplied(p)) SWITCH_BY_COND_TYPE(type, warn, "regex ")
19619 nd_set_type(node, NODE_MATCH);
19620 }
19621 else if (node->nd_lit == Qtrue ||
19622 node->nd_lit == Qfalse) {
19623 /* booleans are OK, e.g., while true */
19624 }
19625 else if (SYMBOL_P(node->nd_lit)) {
19626 goto warn_symbol;
19627 }
19628 else {
19629 SWITCH_BY_COND_TYPE(type, warning, "")
19630 }
19631 default:
19632 break;
19633 }
19634 return node;
19635}
19636
19637static NODE*
19638cond(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19639{
19640 if (node == 0) return 0;
19641 return cond0(p, node, COND_IN_COND, loc);
19642}
19643
19644static NODE*
19645method_cond(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19646{
19647 if (node == 0) return 0;
19648 return cond0(p, node, COND_IN_OP, loc);
19649}
19650
19651static NODE*
19652new_nil_at(struct parser_params *p, const rb_code_position_t *pos)
19653{
19654 YYLTYPE loc = {*pos, *pos};
19655 return NEW_NIL(&loc);
19656}
19657
19658static NODE*
19659new_if(struct parser_params *p, NODE *cc, NODE *left, NODE *right, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19660{
19661 if (!cc) return right;
19662 cc = cond0(p, cc, COND_IN_COND, loc);
19663 return newline_node(NEW_IF(cc, left, right, loc));
19664}
19665
19666static NODE*
19667new_unless(struct parser_params *p, NODE *cc, NODE *left, NODE *right, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19668{
19669 if (!cc) return right;
19670 cc = cond0(p, cc, COND_IN_COND, loc);
19671 return newline_node(NEW_UNLESS(cc, left, right, loc));
19672}
19673
19674static NODE*
19675logop(struct parser_params *p, ID id, NODE *left, NODE *right,
19676 const YYLTYPE *op_loc, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19677{
19678 enum node_type type = id == idAND || id == idANDOP ? NODE_AND : NODE_OR;
19679 NODE *op;
19680 value_expr(left);
19681 if (left && nd_type_p(left, type)) {
19682 NODE *node = left, *second;
19683 while ((second = node->nd_2nd) != 0 && nd_type_p(second, type)) {
19684 node = second;
19685 }
19686 node->nd_2nd = NEW_NODE(type, second, right, 0, loc);
19687 nd_set_line(node->nd_2nd, op_loc->beg_pos.lineno);
19688 left->nd_loc.end_pos = loc->end_pos;
19689 return left;
19690 }
19691 op = NEW_NODE(type, left, right, 0, loc);
19692 nd_set_line(op, op_loc->beg_pos.lineno);
19693 return op;
19694}

19698{
19699 if (node && nd_type_p(node, NODE_BLOCK_PASS)) {
19700 compile_error(p, "block argument should not be given");
19701 }
19702}
19703
19704static NODE *
19705ret_args(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
19706{
19707 if (node) {
19708 no_blockarg(p, node);
19709 if (nd_type_p(node, NODE_LIST)) {
19710 if (node->nd_next == 0) {
19711 node = node->nd_head;
19712 }
19713 else {
19714 nd_set_type(node, NODE_VALUES);
19715 }
19716 }
19717 }
19718 return node;
19719}

19721static NODE *
19722new_yield(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)

19725

19728
19729static VALUE
19730negate_lit(struct parser_params *p, VALUE lit)
19731{
19732 if (FIXNUM_P(lit)) {
19733 return LONG2FIX(-FIX2LONG(lit));
19734 }
19735 if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(lit)) {
19736#if USE_FLONUM
19737 if (FLONUM_P(lit)) {
19738 return DBL2NUM(-RFLOAT_VALUE(lit));
19739 }
19740#endif
19741 goto unknown;
19742 }
19743 switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(lit)) {
19744 case T_BIGNUM:
19745 BIGNUM_NEGATE(lit);
19746 lit = rb_big_norm(lit);
19747 break;
19748 case T_RATIONAL:
19749 RATIONAL_SET_NUM(lit, negate_lit(p, RRATIONAL(lit)->num));
19750 break;
19751 case T_COMPLEX:
19752 RCOMPLEX_SET_REAL(lit, negate_lit(p, RCOMPLEX(lit)->real));
19753 RCOMPLEX_SET_IMAG(lit, negate_lit(p, RCOMPLEX(lit)->imag));
19754 break;
19755 case T_FLOAT:
19756 lit = DBL2NUM(-RFLOAT_VALUE(lit));
19757 break;
19758 unknown:
19759 default:
19760 rb_parser_fatal(p, "unknown literal type (%s) passed to negate_lit",
19761 rb_builtin_class_name(lit));
19762 break;
19763 }
19764 return lit;
19765}
19766
19767static NODE *
19768arg_blk_pass(NODE *node1, NODE *node2)
19769{
19770 if (node2) {
19771 if (!node1) return node2;
19772 node2->nd_head = node1;
19773 nd_set_first_lineno(node2, nd_first_lineno(node1));
19774 nd_set_first_column(node2, nd_first_column(node1));
19775 return node2;
19776 }
19777 return node1;
19778}
19779
19780static bool
19781args_info_empty_p(struct rb_args_info *args)
19782{
19783 if (args->pre_args_num) return false;
19784 if (args->post_args_num) return false;
19785 if (args->rest_arg) return false;
19786 if (args->opt_args) return false;
19787 if (args->block_arg) return false;
19788 if (args->kw_args) return false;
19789 if (args->kw_rest_arg) return false;
19790 return true;
19791}
19792
19793static NODE*
19794new_args(struct parser_params *p, NODE *pre_args, NODE *opt_args, ID rest_arg, NODE *post_args, NODE *tail, const YYLTYPE *loc)
19795{
19796 int saved_line = p->ruby_sourceline;
19797 struct rb_args_info *args = tail->nd_ainfo;
19798
19799 if (args->block_arg == idFWD_BLOCK) {
19800 if (rest_arg) {
19801 yyerror1(&tail->nd_loc, "... after rest argument");
19802 return tail;
19803 }
19804 rest_arg = idFWD_REST;
19805 }
19806
19807 args->pre_args_num = pre_args ? rb_long2int(pre_args->nd_plen) : 0;
19808 args->pre_init = pre_args ? pre_args->nd_next : 0;
19809
19810 args->post_args_num = post_args ? rb_long2int(post_args->nd_plen) : 0;
19811 args->post_init = post_args ? post_args->nd_next : 0;
19812 args->first_post_arg = post_args ? post_args->nd_pid : 0;
19813
19814 args->rest_arg = rest_arg;
19815
19816 args->opt_args = opt_args;
19817
19818 args->ruby2_keywords = rest_arg == idFWD_REST;
19819
19820 p->ruby_sourceline = saved_line;
19821 nd_set_loc(tail, loc);
19822
19823 return tail;
19824}
19825
19826static NODE*
19827new_args_tail(struct parser_params *p, NODE *kw_args, ID kw_rest_arg, ID block, const YYLTYPE *kw_rest_loc)
19828{
19829 int saved_line = p->ruby_sourceline;
19830 NODE *node;
19831 VALUE tmpbuf = rb_imemo_tmpbuf_auto_free_pointer();
19832 struct rb_args_info *args = ZALLOC(struct rb_args_info);
19833 rb_imemo_tmpbuf_set_ptr(tmpbuf, args);
19834 args->imemo = tmpbuf;
19835 node = NEW_NODE(NODE_ARGS, 0, 0, args, &NULL_LOC);
19836 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, tmpbuf);
19837 if (p->error_p) return node;
19838
19839 args->block_arg = block;
19840 args->kw_args = kw_args;
19841
19842 if (kw_args) {
19843 /*
19844 * def foo(k1: 1, kr1:, k2: 2, **krest, &b)
19845 * variable order: k1, kr1, k2, &b, internal_id, krest
19846 * #=> <reorder>
19847 * variable order: kr1, k1, k2, internal_id, krest, &b
19848 */
19849 ID kw_bits = internal_id(p), *required_kw_vars, *kw_vars;
19850 struct vtable *vtargs = p->lvtbl->args;
19851 NODE *kwn = kw_args;
19852
19853 if (block) block = vtargs->tbl[vtargs->pos-1];
19854 vtable_pop(vtargs, !!block + !!kw_rest_arg);
19855 required_kw_vars = kw_vars = &vtargs->tbl[vtargs->pos];
19856 while (kwn) {
19857 if (!NODE_REQUIRED_KEYWORD_P(kwn->nd_body))
19858 --kw_vars;
19859 --required_kw_vars;
19860 kwn = kwn->nd_next;
19861 }
19862
19863 for (kwn = kw_args; kwn; kwn = kwn->nd_next) {
19864 ID vid = kwn->nd_body->nd_vid;
19865 if (NODE_REQUIRED_KEYWORD_P(kwn->nd_body)) {
19866 *required_kw_vars++ = vid;
19867 }
19868 else {
19869 *kw_vars++ = vid;
19870 }
19871 }
19872
19873 arg_var(p, kw_bits);
19874 if (kw_rest_arg) arg_var(p, kw_rest_arg);
19875 if (block) arg_var(p, block);
19876
19877 args->kw_rest_arg = NEW_DVAR(kw_rest_arg, kw_rest_loc);
19878 args->kw_rest_arg->nd_cflag = kw_bits;
19879 }
19880 else if (kw_rest_arg == idNil) {
19881 args->no_kwarg = 1;
19882 }
19883 else if (kw_rest_arg) {
19884 args->kw_rest_arg = NEW_DVAR(kw_rest_arg, kw_rest_loc);
19885 }
19886
19887 p->ruby_sourceline = saved_line;
19888 return node;
19889}

19891static NODE *
19892args_with_numbered(struct parser_params *p, NODE *args, int max_numparam)
19893{
19894 if (max_numparam > NO_PARAM) {
19895 if (!args) {
19896 YYLTYPE loc = RUBY_INIT_YYLLOC();
19897 args = new_args_tail(p, 0, 0, 0, 0);
19898 nd_set_loc(args, &loc);
19899 }
19900 args->nd_ainfo->pre_args_num = max_numparam;
19901 }
19902 return args;
19903}

20011static NODE*
20012dsym_node(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20013{
20014 VALUE lit;
20015
20016 if (!node) {
20017 return NEW_LIT(ID2SYM(idNULL), loc);
20018 }
20019
20020 switch (nd_type(node)) {
20021 case NODE_DSTR:
20022 nd_set_type(node, NODE_DSYM);
20023 nd_set_loc(node, loc);
20024 break;
20025 case NODE_STR:
20026 lit = node->nd_lit;
20027 RB_OBJ_WRITTEN(p->ast, Qnil, node->nd_lit = ID2SYM(rb_intern_str(lit)));
20028 nd_set_type(node, NODE_LIT);
20029 nd_set_loc(node, loc);
20030 break;
20031 default:
20032 node = NEW_NODE(NODE_DSYM, Qnil, 1, NEW_LIST(node, loc), loc);
20033 break;
20034 }
20035 return node;
20036}
20037
20038static int
20039append_literal_keys(st_data_t k, st_data_t v, st_data_t h)
20040{
20041 NODE *node = (NODE *)v;
20042 NODE **result = (NODE **)h;
20043 node->nd_alen = 2;
20044 node->nd_next->nd_end = node->nd_next;
20045 node->nd_next->nd_next = 0;
20046 if (*result)
20047 list_concat(*result, node);
20048 else
20049 *result = node;
20050 return ST_CONTINUE;
20051}
20052
20053static bool
20054hash_literal_key_p(VALUE k)
20055{
20056 switch (OBJ_BUILTIN_TYPE(k)) {
20057 case T_NODE:
20058 return false;
20059 default:
20060 return true;
20061 }
20062}
20063
20064static int
20065literal_cmp(VALUE val, VALUE lit)
20066{
20067 if (val == lit) return 0;
20068 if (!hash_literal_key_p(val) || !hash_literal_key_p(lit)) return -1;
20069 return rb_iseq_cdhash_cmp(val, lit);
20070}
20071
20072static st_index_t
20073literal_hash(VALUE a)
20074{
20075 if (!hash_literal_key_p(a)) return (st_index_t)a;
20076 return rb_iseq_cdhash_hash(a);
20077}
20078
20079static const struct st_hash_type literal_type = {
20080 literal_cmp,
20081 literal_hash,
20082};
20083
20084static NODE *
20085remove_duplicate_keys(struct parser_params *p, NODE *hash)
20086{
20087 st_table *literal_keys = st_init_table_with_size(&literal_type, hash->nd_alen / 2);
20088 NODE *result = 0;
20089 NODE *last_expr = 0;
20090 rb_code_location_t loc = hash->nd_loc;
20091 while (hash && hash->nd_head && hash->nd_next) {
20092 NODE *head = hash->nd_head;
20093 NODE *value = hash->nd_next;
20094 NODE *next = value->nd_next;
20095 st_data_t key = (st_data_t)head;
20096 st_data_t data;
20097 value->nd_next = 0;
20098 if (nd_type_p(head, NODE_LIT) &&
20099 st_delete(literal_keys, (key = (st_data_t)head->nd_lit, &key), &data)) {
20100 NODE *dup_value = ((NODE *)data)->nd_next;
20101 rb_compile_warn(p->ruby_sourcefile, nd_line((NODE *)data),
20102 "key %+"PRIsVALUE" is duplicated and overwritten on line %d",
20103 head->nd_lit, nd_line(head));
20104 if (dup_value == last_expr) {
20105 value->nd_head = block_append(p, dup_value->nd_head, value->nd_head);
20106 }
20107 else {
20108 last_expr->nd_head = block_append(p, dup_value->nd_head, last_expr->nd_head);
20109 }
20110 }
20111 st_insert(literal_keys, (st_data_t)key, (st_data_t)hash);
20112 last_expr = nd_type_p(head, NODE_LIT) ? value : head;
20113 hash = next;
20114 }
20115 st_foreach(literal_keys, append_literal_keys, (st_data_t)&result);
20116 st_free_table(literal_keys);
20117 if (hash) {
20118 if (!result) result = hash;
20119 else list_concat(result, hash);
20120 }
20121 result->nd_loc = loc;
20122 return result;
20123}
20124
20125static NODE *
20126new_hash(struct parser_params *p, NODE *hash, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20127{
20128 if (hash) hash = remove_duplicate_keys(p, hash);
20129 return NEW_HASH(hash, loc);
20130}
20131#endif

20133static void
20134error_duplicate_pattern_variable(struct parser_params *p, ID id, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20135{
20136 if (is_private_local_id(id)) {
20137 return;
20138 }
20139 if (st_is_member(p->pvtbl, id)) {
20140 yyerror1(loc, "duplicated variable name");
20141 }
20142 else {
20143 st_insert(p->pvtbl, (st_data_t)id, 0);
20144 }
20145}
20146
20147static void
20148error_duplicate_pattern_key(struct parser_params *p, VALUE key, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20149{
20150 if (!p->pktbl) {
20151 p->pktbl = st_init_numtable();
20152 }
20153 else if (st_is_member(p->pktbl, key)) {
20154 yyerror1(loc, "duplicated key name");
20155 return;
20156 }
20157 st_insert(p->pktbl, (st_data_t)key, 0);
20158}

20168#ifndef RIPPER
20169static NODE *
20170new_op_assign(struct parser_params *p, NODE *lhs, ID op, NODE *rhs, struct lex_context ctxt, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20171{
20172 NODE *asgn;
20173
20174 if (lhs) {
20175 ID vid = lhs->nd_vid;
20176 YYLTYPE lhs_loc = lhs->nd_loc;
20177 int shareable = ctxt.shareable_constant_value;
20178 if (shareable) {
20179 switch (nd_type(lhs)) {
20180 case NODE_CDECL:
20181 case NODE_COLON2:
20182 case NODE_COLON3:
20183 break;
20184 default:
20185 shareable = 0;
20186 break;
20187 }
20188 }
20189 if (op == tOROP) {
20190 rhs = shareable_constant_value(p, shareable, lhs, rhs, &rhs->nd_loc);
20191 lhs->nd_value = rhs;
20192 nd_set_loc(lhs, loc);
20193 asgn = NEW_OP_ASGN_OR(gettable(p, vid, &lhs_loc), lhs, loc);
20194 if (is_notop_id(vid)) {
20195 switch (id_type(vid)) {
20196 case ID_GLOBAL:
20197 case ID_INSTANCE:
20198 case ID_CLASS:
20199 asgn->nd_aid = vid;
20200 }
20201 }
20202 }
20203 else if (op == tANDOP) {
20204 if (shareable) {
20205 rhs = shareable_constant_value(p, shareable, lhs, rhs, &rhs->nd_loc);
20206 }
20207 lhs->nd_value = rhs;
20208 nd_set_loc(lhs, loc);
20209 asgn = NEW_OP_ASGN_AND(gettable(p, vid, &lhs_loc), lhs, loc);
20210 }
20211 else {
20212 asgn = lhs;
20213 rhs = NEW_CALL(gettable(p, vid, &lhs_loc), op, NEW_LIST(rhs, &rhs->nd_loc), loc);
20214 if (shareable) {
20215 rhs = shareable_constant_value(p, shareable, lhs, rhs, &rhs->nd_loc);
20216 }
20217 asgn->nd_value = rhs;
20218 nd_set_loc(asgn, loc);
20219 }
20220 }
20221 else {
20222 asgn = NEW_BEGIN(0, loc);
20223 }
20224 return asgn;
20225}

20227static NODE *
20228new_ary_op_assign(struct parser_params *p, NODE *ary,
20229 NODE *args, ID op, NODE *rhs, const YYLTYPE *args_loc, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20230{
20231 NODE *asgn;
20232
20233 args = make_list(args, args_loc);
20234 if (nd_type_p(args, NODE_BLOCK_PASS)) {
20235 args = NEW_ARGSCAT(args, rhs, loc);
20236 }
20237 else {
20238 args = arg_concat(p, args, rhs, loc);
20239 }
20240 asgn = NEW_OP_ASGN1(ary, op, args, loc);
20241 fixpos(asgn, ary);
20242 return asgn;
20243}

20305#ifndef RIPPER
20306static NODE *
20307new_bodystmt(struct parser_params *p, NODE *head, NODE *rescue, NODE *rescue_else, NODE *ensure, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20308{
20309 NODE *result = head;
20310 if (rescue) {
20311 NODE *tmp = rescue_else ? rescue_else : rescue;
20312 YYLTYPE rescue_loc = code_loc_gen(&head->nd_loc, &tmp->nd_loc);
20313
20314 result = NEW_RESCUE(head, rescue, rescue_else, &rescue_loc);
20315 nd_set_line(result, rescue->nd_loc.beg_pos.lineno);
20316 }
20317 else if (rescue_else) {
20318 result = block_append(p, result, rescue_else);
20319 }
20320 if (ensure) {
20321 result = NEW_ENSURE(result, ensure, loc);
20322 }
20323 fixpos(result, head);
20324 return result;
20325}
20326#endif
20327
20328static void
20329warn_unused_var(struct parser_params *p, struct local_vars *local)
20330{
20331 int cnt;
20332
20333 if (!local->used) return;
20334 cnt = local->used->pos;
20335 if (cnt != local->vars->pos) {
20336 rb_parser_fatal(p, "local->used->pos != local->vars->pos");
20337 }
20338#ifndef RIPPER
20339 ID *v = local->vars->tbl;
20340 ID *u = local->used->tbl;
20341 for (int i = 0; i < cnt; ++i) {
20342 if (!v[i] || (u[i] & LVAR_USED)) continue;
20343 if (is_private_local_id(v[i])) continue;
20344 rb_warn1L((int)u[i], "assigned but unused variable - %"PRIsWARN, rb_id2str(v[i]));
20345 }
20346#endif
20347}
20348
20349static void
20350local_push(struct parser_params *p, int toplevel_scope)
20351{
20352 struct local_vars *local;
20353 int inherits_dvars = toplevel_scope && compile_for_eval;
20354 int warn_unused_vars = RTEST(ruby_verbose);
20355
20356 local = ALLOC(struct local_vars);
20357 local->prev = p->lvtbl;
20358 local->args = vtable_alloc(0);
20359 local->vars = vtable_alloc(inherits_dvars ? DVARS_INHERIT : DVARS_TOPSCOPE);
20360#ifndef RIPPER
20361 if (toplevel_scope && compile_for_eval) warn_unused_vars = 0;
20362 if (toplevel_scope && e_option_supplied(p)) warn_unused_vars = 0;
20363 local->numparam.outer = 0;
20364 local->numparam.inner = 0;
20365 local->numparam.current = 0;
20366#endif
20367 local->used = warn_unused_vars ? vtable_alloc(0) : 0;
20368
20369# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
20370 local->past = 0;
20371# endif
20372 CMDARG_PUSH(0);
20373 COND_PUSH(0);
20374 p->lvtbl = local;
20375}
20376
20377static void
20378local_pop(struct parser_params *p)
20379{
20380 struct local_vars *local = p->lvtbl->prev;
20381 if (p->lvtbl->used) {
20382 warn_unused_var(p, p->lvtbl);
20383 vtable_free(p->lvtbl->used);
20384 }
20385# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
20386 while (p->lvtbl->past) {
20387 struct vtable *past = p->lvtbl->past;
20388 p->lvtbl->past = past->prev;
20389 vtable_free(past);
20390 }
20391# endif
20392 vtable_free(p->lvtbl->args);
20393 vtable_free(p->lvtbl->vars);
20394 CMDARG_POP();
20395 COND_POP();
20396 ruby_sized_xfree(p->lvtbl, sizeof(*p->lvtbl));
20397 p->lvtbl = local;
20398}
20399
20400#ifndef RIPPER
20401static rb_ast_id_table_t *
20402local_tbl(struct parser_params *p)
20403{
20404 int cnt_args = vtable_size(p->lvtbl->args);
20405 int cnt_vars = vtable_size(p->lvtbl->vars);
20406 int cnt = cnt_args + cnt_vars;
20407 int i, j;
20408 rb_ast_id_table_t *tbl;
20409
20410 if (cnt <= 0) return 0;
20411 tbl = rb_ast_new_local_table(p->ast, cnt);
20412 MEMCPY(tbl->ids, p->lvtbl->args->tbl, ID, cnt_args);
20413 /* remove IDs duplicated to warn shadowing */
20414 for (i = 0, j = cnt_args; i < cnt_vars; ++i) {
20415 ID id = p->lvtbl->vars->tbl[i];
20416 if (!vtable_included(p->lvtbl->args, id)) {
20417 tbl->ids[j++] = id;
20418 }
20419 }
20420 if (j < cnt) {
20421 tbl = rb_ast_resize_latest_local_table(p->ast, j);
20422 }
20423
20424 return tbl;
20425}
20426
20427static NODE*
20428node_newnode_with_locals(struct parser_params *p, enum node_type type, VALUE a1, VALUE a2, const rb_code_location_t *loc)
20429{
20430 rb_ast_id_table_t *a0;
20431 NODE *n;
20432
20433 a0 = local_tbl(p);
20434 n = NEW_NODE(type, a0, a1, a2, loc);
20435 return n;
20436}
20437
20438#endif
20439
20440static void
20441numparam_name(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
20442{
20443 if (!NUMPARAM_ID_P(id)) return;
20444 compile_error(p, "_%d is reserved for numbered parameter",
20445 NUMPARAM_ID_TO_IDX(id));
20446}
20447
20448static void
20449arg_var(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
20450{
20451 numparam_name(p, id);
20452 vtable_add(p->lvtbl->args, id);
20453}
20454
20455static void
20456local_var(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
20457{
20458 numparam_name(p, id);
20459 vtable_add(p->lvtbl->vars, id);
20460 if (p->lvtbl->used) {
20461 vtable_add(p->lvtbl->used, (ID)p->ruby_sourceline);
20462 }
20463}
20464
20465static int
20466local_id_ref(struct parser_params *p, ID id, ID **vidrefp)
20467{
20468 struct vtable *vars, *args, *used;
20469
20470 vars = p->lvtbl->vars;
20471 args = p->lvtbl->args;
20472 used = p->lvtbl->used;
20473
20474 while (vars && !DVARS_TERMINAL_P(vars->prev)) {
20475 vars = vars->prev;
20476 args = args->prev;
20477 if (used) used = used->prev;
20478 }
20479
20480 if (vars && vars->prev == DVARS_INHERIT) {
20481 return rb_local_defined(id, p->parent_iseq);
20482 }
20483 else if (vtable_included(args, id)) {
20484 return 1;
20485 }
20486 else {
20487 int i = vtable_included(vars, id);
20488 if (i && used && vidrefp) *vidrefp = &used->tbl[i-1];
20489 return i != 0;
20490 }
20491}
20492
20493static int
20494local_id(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
20495{
20496 return local_id_ref(p, id, NULL);
20497}
20498
20499static int
20500check_forwarding_args(struct parser_params *p)
20501{
20502 if (local_id(p, idFWD_REST) &&
20503#if idFWD_KWREST
20504 local_id(p, idFWD_KWREST) &&
20505#endif
20506 local_id(p, idFWD_BLOCK)) return TRUE;
20507 compile_error(p, "unexpected ...");
20508 return FALSE;
20509}
20510
20511static void
20512add_forwarding_args(struct parser_params *p)
20513{
20514 arg_var(p, idFWD_REST);
20515#if idFWD_KWREST
20516 arg_var(p, idFWD_KWREST);
20517#endif
20518 arg_var(p, idFWD_BLOCK);
20519}
20520
20521#ifndef RIPPER
20522static NODE *
20523new_args_forward_call(struct parser_params *p, NODE *leading, const YYLTYPE *loc, const YYLTYPE *argsloc)
20524{
20525 NODE *splat = NEW_SPLAT(NEW_LVAR(idFWD_REST, loc), loc);
20526#if idFWD_KWREST
20527 NODE *kwrest = list_append(p, NEW_LIST(0, loc), NEW_LVAR(idFWD_KWREST, loc));
20528#endif
20529 NODE *block = NEW_BLOCK_PASS(NEW_LVAR(idFWD_BLOCK, loc), loc);
20530 NODE *args = leading ? rest_arg_append(p, leading, splat, argsloc) : splat;
20531#if idFWD_KWREST
20532 args = arg_append(p, splat, new_hash(p, kwrest, loc), loc);
20533#endif
20534 return arg_blk_pass(args, block);
20535}
20536#endif
20537
20538static NODE *
20539numparam_push(struct parser_params *p)
20540{
20541#ifndef RIPPER
20542 struct local_vars *local = p->lvtbl;
20543 NODE *inner = local->numparam.inner;
20544 if (!local->numparam.outer) {
20545 local->numparam.outer = local->numparam.current;
20546 }
20547 local->numparam.inner = 0;
20548 local->numparam.current = 0;
20549 return inner;
20550#else
20551 return 0;
20552#endif
20553}
20554
20555static void
20556numparam_pop(struct parser_params *p, NODE *prev_inner)
20557{
20558#ifndef RIPPER
20559 struct local_vars *local = p->lvtbl;
20560 if (prev_inner) {
20561 /* prefer first one */
20562 local->numparam.inner = prev_inner;
20563 }
20564 else if (local->numparam.current) {
20565 /* current and inner are exclusive */
20566 local->numparam.inner = local->numparam.current;
20567 }
20568 if (p->max_numparam > NO_PARAM) {
20569 /* current and outer are exclusive */
20570 local->numparam.current = local->numparam.outer;
20571 local->numparam.outer = 0;
20572 }
20573 else {
20574 /* no numbered parameter */
20575 local->numparam.current = 0;
20576 }
20577#endif
20578}
20579
20580static const struct vtable *
20581dyna_push(struct parser_params *p)
20582{
20583 p->lvtbl->args = vtable_alloc(p->lvtbl->args);
20584 p->lvtbl->vars = vtable_alloc(p->lvtbl->vars);
20585 if (p->lvtbl->used) {
20586 p->lvtbl->used = vtable_alloc(p->lvtbl->used);
20587 }
20588 return p->lvtbl->args;
20589}
20590
20591static void
20592dyna_pop_vtable(struct parser_params *p, struct vtable **vtblp)
20593{
20594 struct vtable *tmp = *vtblp;
20595 *vtblp = tmp->prev;
20596# if WARN_PAST_SCOPE
20597 if (p->past_scope_enabled) {
20598 tmp->prev = p->lvtbl->past;
20599 p->lvtbl->past = tmp;
20600 return;
20601 }
20602# endif
20603 vtable_free(tmp);
20604}
20605
20606static void
20607dyna_pop_1(struct parser_params *p)
20608{
20609 struct vtable *tmp;
20610
20611 if ((tmp = p->lvtbl->used) != 0) {
20612 warn_unused_var(p, p->lvtbl);
20613 p->lvtbl->used = p->lvtbl->used->prev;
20614 vtable_free(tmp);
20615 }
20616 dyna_pop_vtable(p, &p->lvtbl->args);
20617 dyna_pop_vtable(p, &p->lvtbl->vars);
20618}
20619
20620static void
20621dyna_pop(struct parser_params *p, const struct vtable *lvargs)
20622{
20623 while (p->lvtbl->args != lvargs) {
20624 dyna_pop_1(p);
20625 if (!p->lvtbl->args) {
20626 struct local_vars *local = p->lvtbl->prev;
20627 ruby_sized_xfree(p->lvtbl, sizeof(*p->lvtbl));
20628 p->lvtbl = local;
20629 }
20630 }
20631 dyna_pop_1(p);
20632}
20633
20634static int
20635dyna_in_block(struct parser_params *p)
20636{
20637 return !DVARS_TERMINAL_P(p->lvtbl->vars) && p->lvtbl->vars->prev != DVARS_TOPSCOPE;
20638}
20639
20640static int
20641dvar_defined_ref(struct parser_params *p, ID id, ID **vidrefp)
20642{
20643 struct vtable *vars, *args, *used;
20644 int i;
20645
20646 args = p->lvtbl->args;
20647 vars = p->lvtbl->vars;
20648 used = p->lvtbl->used;
20649
20650 while (!DVARS_TERMINAL_P(vars)) {
20651 if (vtable_included(args, id)) {
20652 return 1;
20653 }
20654 if ((i = vtable_included(vars, id)) != 0) {
20655 if (used && vidrefp) *vidrefp = &used->tbl[i-1];
20656 return 1;
20657 }
20658 args = args->prev;
20659 vars = vars->prev;
20660 if (!vidrefp) used = 0;
20661 if (used) used = used->prev;
20662 }
20663
20664 if (vars == DVARS_INHERIT && !NUMPARAM_ID_P(id)) {
20665 return rb_dvar_defined(id, p->parent_iseq);
20666 }
20667
20668 return 0;
20669}
20670
20671static int
20672dvar_defined(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
20673{
20674 return dvar_defined_ref(p, id, NULL);
20675}
20676
20677static int
20678dvar_curr(struct parser_params *p, ID id)
20679{
20680 return (vtable_included(p->lvtbl->args, id) ||
20681 vtable_included(p->lvtbl->vars, id));
20682}
20683
20684static void
20685reg_fragment_enc_error(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int c)
20686{
20687 compile_error(p,
20688 "regexp encoding option '%c' differs from source encoding '%s'",
20689 c, rb_enc_name(rb_enc_get(str)));
20690}
20691
20692#ifndef RIPPER
20693int
20694rb_reg_fragment_setenc(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options)
20695{
20696 int c = RE_OPTION_ENCODING_IDX(options);
20697
20698 if (c) {
20699 int opt, idx;
20700 rb_char_to_option_kcode(c, &opt, &idx);
20701 if (idx != ENCODING_GET(str) &&
20702 rb_enc_str_coderange(str) != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) {
20703 goto error;
20704 }
20705 ENCODING_SET(str, idx);
20706 }
20707 else if (RE_OPTION_ENCODING_NONE(options)) {
20708 if (!ENCODING_IS_ASCII8BIT(str) &&
20709 rb_enc_str_coderange(str) != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) {
20710 c = 'n';
20711 goto error;
20712 }
20713 rb_enc_associate(str, rb_ascii8bit_encoding());
20714 }
20715 else if (p->enc == rb_usascii_encoding()) {
20716 if (rb_enc_str_coderange(str) != ENC_CODERANGE_7BIT) {
20717 /* raise in re.c */
20718 rb_enc_associate(str, rb_usascii_encoding());
20719 }
20720 else {
20721 rb_enc_associate(str, rb_ascii8bit_encoding());
20722 }
20723 }
20724 return 0;
20725
20726 error:
20727 return c;
20728}
20729
20730static void
20731reg_fragment_setenc(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options)
20732{
20733 int c = rb_reg_fragment_setenc(p, str, options);
20734 if (c) reg_fragment_enc_error(p, str, c);
20735}
20736
20737static int
20738reg_fragment_check(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options)
20739{
20740 VALUE err;
20741 reg_fragment_setenc(p, str, options);
20742 err = rb_reg_check_preprocess(str);
20743 if (err != Qnil) {
20744 err = rb_obj_as_string(err);
20745 compile_error(p, "%"PRIsVALUE, err);
20746 return 0;
20747 }
20748 return 1;
20749}
20750
20751typedef struct {
20752 struct parser_params* parser;
20753 rb_encoding *enc;
20754 NODE *succ_block;
20755 const YYLTYPE *loc;
20756} reg_named_capture_assign_t;
20757
20758static int
20759reg_named_capture_assign_iter(const OnigUChar *name, const OnigUChar *name_end,
20760 int back_num, int *back_refs, OnigRegex regex, void *arg0)
20761{
20762 reg_named_capture_assign_t *arg = (reg_named_capture_assign_t*)arg0;
20763 struct parser_params* p = arg->parser;
20764 rb_encoding *enc = arg->enc;
20765 long len = name_end - name;
20766 const char *s = (const char *)name;
20767 ID var;
20768 NODE *node, *succ;
20769
20770 if (!len) return ST_CONTINUE;
20771 if (rb_enc_symname_type(s, len, enc, (1U<<ID_LOCAL)) != ID_LOCAL)
20772 return ST_CONTINUE;
20773
20774 var = intern_cstr(s, len, enc);
20775 if (len < MAX_WORD_LENGTH && rb_reserved_word(s, (int)len)) {
20776 if (!lvar_defined(p, var)) return ST_CONTINUE;
20777 }
20778 node = node_assign(p, assignable(p, var, 0, arg->loc), NEW_LIT(ID2SYM(var), arg->loc), NO_LEX_CTXT, arg->loc);
20779 succ = arg->succ_block;
20780 if (!succ) succ = NEW_BEGIN(0, arg->loc);
20781 succ = block_append(p, succ, node);
20782 arg->succ_block = succ;
20783 return ST_CONTINUE;
20784}
20785
20786static NODE *
20787reg_named_capture_assign(struct parser_params* p, VALUE regexp, const YYLTYPE *loc)
20788{
20789 reg_named_capture_assign_t arg;
20790
20791 arg.parser = p;
20792 arg.enc = rb_enc_get(regexp);
20793 arg.succ_block = 0;
20794 arg.loc = loc;
20795 onig_foreach_name(RREGEXP_PTR(regexp), reg_named_capture_assign_iter, &arg);
20796
20797 if (!arg.succ_block) return 0;
20798 return arg.succ_block->nd_next;
20799}
20800
20801static VALUE
20802parser_reg_compile(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options)
20803{
20804 reg_fragment_setenc(p, str, options);
20805 return rb_parser_reg_compile(p, str, options);
20806}
20807
20808VALUE
20809rb_parser_reg_compile(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options)
20810{
20811 return rb_reg_compile(str, options & RE_OPTION_MASK, p->ruby_sourcefile, p->ruby_sourceline);
20812}
20813
20814static VALUE
20815reg_compile(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options)
20816{
20817 VALUE re;
20818 VALUE err;
20819
20820 err = rb_errinfo();
20821 re = parser_reg_compile(p, str, options);
20822 if (NIL_P(re)) {
20823 VALUE m = rb_attr_get(rb_errinfo(), idMesg);
20824 rb_set_errinfo(err);
20825 compile_error(p, "%"PRIsVALUE, m);
20826 return Qnil;
20827 }
20828 return re;
20829}
20830#else
20831static VALUE
20832parser_reg_compile(struct parser_params* p, VALUE str, int options, VALUE *errmsg)
20833{
20834 VALUE err = rb_errinfo();
20835 VALUE re;
20836 str = ripper_is_node_yylval(str) ? RNODE(str)->nd_cval : str;
20837 int c = rb_reg_fragment_setenc(p, str, options);
20838 if (c) reg_fragment_enc_error(p, str, c);
20839 re = rb_parser_reg_compile(p, str, options);
20840 if (NIL_P(re)) {
20841 *errmsg = rb_attr_get(rb_errinfo(), idMesg);
20842 rb_set_errinfo(err);
20843 }
20844 return re;
20845}
20846#endif
20847
20848#ifndef RIPPER
20849void
20850rb_parser_set_options(VALUE vparser, int print, int loop, int chomp, int split)
20851{
20852 struct parser_params *p;
20853 TypedData_Get_Struct(vparser, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
20854 p->do_print = print;
20855 p->do_loop = loop;
20856 p->do_chomp = chomp;
20857 p->do_split = split;
20858}
20859
20860static NODE *
20861parser_append_options(struct parser_params *p, NODE *node)
20862{
20863 static const YYLTYPE default_location = {{1, 0}, {1, 0}};
20864 const YYLTYPE *const LOC = &default_location;
20865
20866 if (p->do_print) {
20867 NODE *print = NEW_FCALL(rb_intern("print"),
20868 NEW_LIST(NEW_GVAR(idLASTLINE, LOC), LOC),
20869 LOC);
20870 node = block_append(p, node, print);
20871 }
20872
20873 if (p->do_loop) {
20874 NODE *irs = NEW_LIST(NEW_GVAR(rb_intern("$/"), LOC), LOC);
20875
20876 if (p->do_split) {
20877 ID ifs = rb_intern("$;");
20878 ID fields = rb_intern("$F");
20879 NODE *args = NEW_LIST(NEW_GVAR(ifs, LOC), LOC);
20880 NODE *split = NEW_GASGN(fields,
20881 NEW_CALL(NEW_GVAR(idLASTLINE, LOC),
20882 rb_intern("split"), args, LOC),
20883 LOC);
20884 node = block_append(p, split, node);
20885 }
20886 if (p->do_chomp) {
20887 NODE *chomp = NEW_LIT(ID2SYM(rb_intern("chomp")), LOC);
20888 chomp = list_append(p, NEW_LIST(chomp, LOC), NEW_TRUE(LOC));
20889 irs = list_append(p, irs, NEW_HASH(chomp, LOC));
20890 }
20891
20892 node = NEW_WHILE(NEW_FCALL(idGets, irs, LOC), node, 1, LOC);
20893 }
20894
20895 return node;
20896}

20902 (void)nodetype;
20903 (void)nodeline;

20910}

20913static void
20914parser_initialize(struct parser_params *p)
20915{
20916 /* note: we rely on TypedData_Make_Struct to set most fields to 0 */
20917 p->command_start = TRUE;
20918 p->ruby_sourcefile_string = Qnil;
20919 p->lex.lpar_beg = -1; /* make lambda_beginning_p() == FALSE at first */
20920 p->node_id = 0;
20921#ifdef RIPPER
20922 p->delayed.token = Qnil;
20923 p->result = Qnil;
20924 p->parsing_thread = Qnil;
20925#else
20926 p->error_buffer = Qfalse;
20927#endif
20928 p->debug_buffer = Qnil;
20929 p->debug_output = rb_ractor_stdout();
20930 p->enc = rb_utf8_encoding();
20931}

20933#ifdef RIPPER
20934#define parser_mark ripper_parser_mark
20935#define parser_free ripper_parser_free
20936#endif
20937
20938static void
20939parser_mark(void *ptr)
20940{
20941 struct parser_params *p = (struct parser_params*)ptr;
20942
20943 rb_gc_mark(p->lex.input);
20944 rb_gc_mark(p->lex.prevline);
20945 rb_gc_mark(p->lex.lastline);
20946 rb_gc_mark(p->lex.nextline);
20947 rb_gc_mark(p->ruby_sourcefile_string);
20948 rb_gc_mark((VALUE)p->lex.strterm);
20949 rb_gc_mark((VALUE)p->ast);
20950 rb_gc_mark(p->case_labels);
20951#ifndef RIPPER
20952 rb_gc_mark(p->debug_lines);
20953 rb_gc_mark(p->compile_option);
20954 rb_gc_mark(p->error_buffer);
20955#else
20956 rb_gc_mark(p->delayed.token);
20957 rb_gc_mark(p->value);
20958 rb_gc_mark(p->result);
20959 rb_gc_mark(p->parsing_thread);
20960#endif
20961 rb_gc_mark(p->debug_buffer);
20962 rb_gc_mark(p->debug_output);
20963#ifdef YYMALLOC
20964 rb_gc_mark((VALUE)p->heap);
20965#endif
20966}
20967
20968static void
20969parser_free(void *ptr)
20970{
20971 struct parser_params *p = (struct parser_params*)ptr;
20972 struct local_vars *local, *prev;
20973
20974 if (p->tokenbuf) {
20975 ruby_sized_xfree(p->tokenbuf, p->toksiz);
20976 }
20977 for (local = p->lvtbl; local; local = prev) {
20978 if (local->vars) xfree(local->vars);
20979 prev = local->prev;
20980 xfree(local);
20981 }
20982 {
20983 token_info *ptinfo;
20984 while ((ptinfo = p->token_info) != 0) {
20985 p->token_info = ptinfo->next;
20986 xfree(ptinfo);
20987 }
20988 }
20989 xfree(ptr);
20990}
20991
20992static size_t
20993parser_memsize(const void *ptr)
20994{
20995 struct parser_params *p = (struct parser_params*)ptr;
20996 struct local_vars *local;
20997 size_t size = sizeof(*p);
20998
20999 size += p->toksiz;
21000 for (local = p->lvtbl; local; local = local->prev) {
21001 size += sizeof(*local);
21002 if (local->vars) size += local->vars->capa * sizeof(ID);
21003 }
21004 return size;
21005}

21009 "parser",

21011 "ripper",
21012#endif
21013 {
21014 parser_mark,
21015 parser_free,
21016 parser_memsize,
21017 },
21018 0, 0, RUBY_TYPED_FREE_IMMEDIATELY
21019};

21075/*
21076 * call-seq:
21077 * ripper.error? -> Boolean
21078 *
21079 * Return true if parsed source has errors.
21080 */
21081static VALUE
21082ripper_error_p(VALUE vparser)
21083{
21084 struct parser_params *p;
21085
21086 TypedData_Get_Struct(vparser, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);

21184#ifndef RIPPER
21185#ifdef YYMALLOC
21186#define HEAPCNT(n, size) ((n) * (size) / sizeof(YYSTYPE))
21187/* Keep the order; NEWHEAP then xmalloc and ADD2HEAP to get rid of
21188 * potential memory leak */
21189#define NEWHEAP() rb_imemo_tmpbuf_parser_heap(0, p->heap, 0)
21190#define ADD2HEAP(new, cnt, ptr) ((p->heap = (new))->ptr = (ptr), \
21191 (new)->cnt = (cnt), (ptr))
21192
21193void *
21194rb_parser_malloc(struct parser_params *p, size_t size)
21195{
21196 size_t cnt = HEAPCNT(1, size);
21197 rb_imemo_tmpbuf_t *n = NEWHEAP();
21198 void *ptr = xmalloc(size);
21199
21200 return ADD2HEAP(n, cnt, ptr);
21201}
21202
21203void *
21204rb_parser_calloc(struct parser_params *p, size_t nelem, size_t size)
21205{
21206 size_t cnt = HEAPCNT(nelem, size);
21207 rb_imemo_tmpbuf_t *n = NEWHEAP();
21208 void *ptr = xcalloc(nelem, size);
21209
21210 return ADD2HEAP(n, cnt, ptr);
21211}
21212
21213void *
21214rb_parser_realloc(struct parser_params *p, void *ptr, size_t size)
21215{
21216 rb_imemo_tmpbuf_t *n;
21217 size_t cnt = HEAPCNT(1, size);
21218
21219 if (ptr && (n = p->heap) != NULL) {
21220 do {
21221 if (n->ptr == ptr) {
21222 n->ptr = ptr = xrealloc(ptr, size);
21223 if (n->cnt) n->cnt = cnt;
21224 return ptr;
21225 }
21226 } while ((n = n->next) != NULL);
21227 }
21228 n = NEWHEAP();
21229 ptr = xrealloc(ptr, size);
21230 return ADD2HEAP(n, cnt, ptr);
21231}
21232
21233void
21234rb_parser_free(struct parser_params *p, void *ptr)
21235{
21236 rb_imemo_tmpbuf_t **prev = &p->heap, *n;
21237
21238 while ((n = *prev) != NULL) {
21239 if (n->ptr == ptr) {
21240 *prev = n->next;
21241 break;
21242 }
21243 prev = &n->next;
21244 }
21245}
21246#endif
21247
21248void
21249rb_parser_printf(struct parser_params *p, const char *fmt, ...)
21250{
21251 va_list ap;
21252 VALUE mesg = p->debug_buffer;
21253
21254 if (NIL_P(mesg)) p->debug_buffer = mesg = rb_str_new(0, 0);
21255 va_start(ap, fmt);
21256 rb_str_vcatf(mesg, fmt, ap);
21257 va_end(ap);
21258 if (RSTRING_END(mesg)[-1] == '\n') {
21259 rb_io_write(p->debug_output, mesg);
21260 p->debug_buffer = Qnil;
21261 }
21262}
21263
21264static void
21265parser_compile_error(struct parser_params *p, const char *fmt, ...)
21266{
21267 va_list ap;
21268
21269 rb_io_flush(p->debug_output);
21270 p->error_p = 1;
21271 va_start(ap, fmt);
21272 p->error_buffer =
21273 rb_syntax_error_append(p->error_buffer,
21274 p->ruby_sourcefile_string,
21275 p->ruby_sourceline,
21276 rb_long2int(p->lex.pcur - p->lex.pbeg),
21277 p->enc, fmt, ap);
21278 va_end(ap);
21279}
21280
21281static size_t
21282count_char(const char *str, int c)
21283{
21284 int n = 0;
21285 while (str[n] == c) ++n;
21286 return n;
21287}
21288
21289/*
21290 * strip enclosing double-quotes, same as the default yytnamerr except
21291 * for that single-quotes matching back-quotes do not stop stripping.
21292 *
21293 * "\"`class' keyword\"" => "`class' keyword"
21294 */
21295RUBY_FUNC_EXPORTED size_t
21296rb_yytnamerr(struct parser_params *p, char *yyres, const char *yystr)
21297{
21298 if (*yystr == '"') {
21299 size_t yyn = 0, bquote = 0;
21300 const char *yyp = yystr;
21301
21302 while (*++yyp) {
21303 switch (*yyp) {
21304 case '`':
21305 if (!bquote) {
21306 bquote = count_char(yyp+1, '`') + 1;
21307 if (yyres) memcpy(&yyres[yyn], yyp, bquote);
21308 yyn += bquote;
21309 yyp += bquote - 1;
21310 break;
21311 }
21312 goto default_char;
21313
21314 case '\'':
21315 if (bquote && count_char(yyp+1, '\'') + 1 == bquote) {
21316 if (yyres) memcpy(yyres + yyn, yyp, bquote);
21317 yyn += bquote;
21318 yyp += bquote - 1;
21319 bquote = 0;
21320 break;
21321 }
21322 if (yyp[1] && yyp[1] != '\'' && yyp[2] == '\'') {
21323 if (yyres) memcpy(yyres + yyn, yyp, 3);
21324 yyn += 3;
21325 yyp += 2;
21326 break;
21327 }
21328 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
21329
21330 case ',':
21331 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
21332
21333 case '\\':
21334 if (*++yyp != '\\')
21335 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
21336 /* Fall through. */
21337 default_char:
21338 default:
21339 if (yyres)
21340 yyres[yyn] = *yyp;
21341 yyn++;
21342 break;
21343
21344 case '"':
21345 case '\0':
21346 if (yyres)
21347 yyres[yyn] = '\0';
21348 return yyn;
21349 }
21350 }
21351 do_not_strip_quotes: ;
21352 }
21353
21354 if (!yyres) return strlen(yystr);
21355
21356 return (YYSIZE_T)(yystpcpy(yyres, yystr) - yyres);
21357}
21358#endif
21359
21360#ifdef RIPPER
21361#ifdef RIPPER_DEBUG
21362/* :nodoc: */
21363static VALUE
21364ripper_validate_object(VALUE self, VALUE x)
21365{
21366 if (x == Qfalse) return x;
21367 if (x == Qtrue) return x;
21368 if (x == Qnil) return x;
21369 if (x == Qundef)
21370 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "Qundef given");
21371 if (FIXNUM_P(x)) return x;
21372 if (SYMBOL_P(x)) return x;
21373 switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(x)) {
21374 case T_STRING:
21375 case T_OBJECT:
21376 case T_ARRAY:
21377 case T_BIGNUM:
21378 case T_FLOAT:
21379 case T_COMPLEX:
21380 case T_RATIONAL:
21381 break;
21382 case T_NODE:
21383 if (!nd_type_p((NODE *)x, NODE_RIPPER)) {
21384 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "NODE given: %p", (void *)x);
21385 }
21386 x = ((NODE *)x)->nd_rval;
21387 break;
21388 default:
21389 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "wrong type of ruby object: %p (%s)",
21390 (void *)x, rb_obj_classname(x));
21391 }
21392 if (!RBASIC_CLASS(x)) {
21393 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "hidden ruby object: %p (%s)",
21394 (void *)x, rb_builtin_type_name(TYPE(x)));
21395 }
21396 return x;
21397}
21398#endif

21466static ID
21467ripper_get_id(VALUE v)
21468{
21469 NODE *nd;
21470 if (!RB_TYPE_P(v, T_NODE)) return 0;
21471 nd = (NODE *)v;
21472 if (!nd_type_p(nd, NODE_RIPPER)) return 0;
21473 return nd->nd_vid;
21474}

21476static VALUE
21477ripper_get_value(VALUE v)
21478{
21479 NODE *nd;
21480 if (v == Qundef) return Qnil;
21481 if (!RB_TYPE_P(v, T_NODE)) return v;
21482 nd = (NODE *)v;
21483 if (!nd_type_p(nd, NODE_RIPPER)) return Qnil;
21484 return nd->nd_rval;
21485}

21490 p->error_p = TRUE;
21491}

21494ripper_compile_error(struct parser_params *p, const char *fmt, ...)
21495{
21496 VALUE str;
21497 va_list args;
21498
21499 va_start(args, fmt);
21500 str = rb_vsprintf(fmt, args);
21501 va_end(args);
21502 rb_funcall(p->value, rb_intern("compile_error"), 1, str);
21503 ripper_error(p);
21504}

21506static VALUE
21507ripper_lex_get_generic(struct parser_params *p, VALUE src)
21508{
21509 VALUE line = rb_funcallv_public(src, id_gets, 0, 0);
21510 if (!NIL_P(line) && !RB_TYPE_P(line, T_STRING)) {
21511 rb_raise(rb_eTypeError,
21512 "gets returned %"PRIsVALUE" (expected String or nil)",
21513 rb_obj_class(line));
21514 }
21515 return line;
21516}
21517
21518static VALUE
21519ripper_lex_io_get(struct parser_params *p, VALUE src)
21520{
21521 return rb_io_gets(src);
21522}
21523
21524static VALUE
21525ripper_s_allocate(VALUE klass)
21526{
21527 struct parser_params *p;
21528 VALUE self = TypedData_Make_Struct(klass, struct parser_params,
21529 &parser_data_type, p);
21530 p->value = self;
21531 return self;
21532}
21533
21534#define ripper_initialized_p(r) ((r)->lex.input != 0)
21535
21536/*
21537 * call-seq:
21538 * Ripper.new(src, filename="(ripper)", lineno=1) -> ripper
21539 *
21540 * Create a new Ripper object.
21541 * _src_ must be a String, an IO, or an Object which has #gets method.
21542 *
21543 * This method does not starts parsing.
21544 * See also Ripper#parse and Ripper.parse.
21545 */
21546static VALUE
21547ripper_initialize(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)
21548{
21549 struct parser_params *p;
21550 VALUE src, fname, lineno;
21551
21552 TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
21553 rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "12", &src, &fname, &lineno);
21554 if (RB_TYPE_P(src, T_FILE)) {
21555 p->lex.gets = ripper_lex_io_get;
21556 }
21557 else if (rb_respond_to(src, id_gets)) {
21558 p->lex.gets = ripper_lex_get_generic;
21559 }
21560 else {
21561 StringValue(src);
21562 p->lex.gets = lex_get_str;
21563 }
21564 p->lex.input = src;
21565 p->eofp = 0;
21566 if (NIL_P(fname)) {
21567 fname = STR_NEW2("(ripper)");
21568 OBJ_FREEZE(fname);
21569 }
21570 else {
21571 StringValueCStr(fname);
21572 fname = rb_str_new_frozen(fname);
21573 }
21574 parser_initialize(p);
21575
21576 p->ruby_sourcefile_string = fname;
21577 p->ruby_sourcefile = RSTRING_PTR(fname);
21578 p->ruby_sourceline = NIL_P(lineno) ? 0 : NUM2INT(lineno) - 1;
21579
21580 return Qnil;
21581}
21582
21583static VALUE
21584ripper_parse0(VALUE parser_v)
21585{
21586 struct parser_params *p;
21587
21588 TypedData_Get_Struct(parser_v, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
21589 parser_prepare(p);
21590 p->ast = rb_ast_new();
21591 ripper_yyparse((void*)p);
21592 rb_ast_dispose(p->ast);
21593 p->ast = 0;
21594 return p->result;
21595}
21596
21597static VALUE
21598ripper_ensure(VALUE parser_v)
21599{
21600 struct parser_params *p;
21601
21602 TypedData_Get_Struct(parser_v, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
21603 p->parsing_thread = Qnil;
21604 return Qnil;
21605}
21606
21607/*
21608 * call-seq:
21609 * ripper.parse
21610 *
21611 * Start parsing and returns the value of the root action.
21612 */
21613static VALUE
21614ripper_parse(VALUE self)
21615{
21616 struct parser_params *p;
21617
21618 TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
21619 if (!ripper_initialized_p(p)) {
21620 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "method called for uninitialized object");
21621 }
21622 if (!NIL_P(p->parsing_thread)) {
21623 if (p->parsing_thread == rb_thread_current())
21624 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "Ripper#parse is not reentrant");
21625 else
21626 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "Ripper#parse is not multithread-safe");
21627 }
21628 p->parsing_thread = rb_thread_current();
21629 rb_ensure(ripper_parse0, self, ripper_ensure, self);
21630
21631 return p->result;
21632}
21633
21634/*
21635 * call-seq:
21636 * ripper.column -> Integer
21637 *
21638 * Return column number of current parsing line.
21639 * This number starts from 0.
21640 */
21641static VALUE
21642ripper_column(VALUE self)
21643{
21644 struct parser_params *p;
21645 long col;
21646
21647 TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
21648 if (!ripper_initialized_p(p)) {
21649 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "method called for uninitialized object");
21650 }
21651 if (NIL_P(p->parsing_thread)) return Qnil;
21652 col = p->lex.ptok - p->lex.pbeg;
21653 return LONG2NUM(col);
21654}

21662static VALUE
21663ripper_filename(VALUE self)

21666

21668 if (!ripper_initialized_p(p)) {
21669 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "method called for uninitialized object");
21670 }
21671 return p->ruby_sourcefile_string;
21672}

21681static VALUE

21692}

21694/*

21700static VALUE
21701ripper_state(VALUE self)

21706 if (!ripper_initialized_p(p)) {
21707 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "method called for uninitialized object");

21713/*
21714 * call-seq:
21715 * ripper.token -> String
21716 *
21717 * Return the current token string.
21718 */
21719static VALUE
21720ripper_token(VALUE self)
21721{
21722 struct parser_params *p;
21723 long pos, len;
21724
21725 TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct parser_params, &parser_data_type, p);
21726 if (!ripper_initialized_p(p)) {
21727 rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "method called for uninitialized object");
21728 }
21729 if (NIL_P(p->parsing_thread)) return Qnil;
21730 pos = p->lex.ptok - p->lex.pbeg;
21731 len = p->lex.pcur - p->lex.ptok;
21732 return rb_str_subseq(p->lex.lastline, pos, len);
21733}

21767void
21768Init_ripper(void)
21769{
21770 ripper_init_eventids1();
21771 ripper_init_eventids2();
21772 id_warn = rb_intern_const("warn");
21773 id_warning = rb_intern_const("warning");
21774 id_gets = rb_intern_const("gets");
21775 id_assoc = rb_intern_const("=>");
21776
21777 (void)yystpcpy; /* may not used in newer bison */
21778
21779 InitVM(ripper);
21780}
21781
21782void
21783InitVM_ripper(void)
21784{
21785 VALUE Ripper;
21786
21787 Ripper = rb_define_class("Ripper", rb_cObject);
21788 /* version of Ripper */
21789 rb_define_const(Ripper, "Version", rb_usascii_str_new2(RIPPER_VERSION));
21790 rb_define_alloc_func(Ripper, ripper_s_allocate);
21791 rb_define_method(Ripper, "initialize", ripper_initialize, -1);
21792 rb_define_method(Ripper, "parse", ripper_parse, 0);
21793 rb_define_method(Ripper, "column", ripper_column, 0);
21794 rb_define_method(Ripper, "filename", ripper_filename, 0);
21795 rb_define_method(Ripper, "lineno", ripper_lineno, 0);
21796 rb_define_method(Ripper, "state", ripper_state, 0);
21797 rb_define_method(Ripper, "token", ripper_token, 0);
21798 rb_define_method(Ripper, "end_seen?", rb_parser_end_seen_p, 0);
21799 rb_define_method(Ripper, "encoding", rb_parser_encoding, 0);
21800 rb_define_method(Ripper, "yydebug", rb_parser_get_yydebug, 0);
21801 rb_define_method(Ripper, "yydebug=", rb_parser_set_yydebug, 1);
21802 rb_define_method(Ripper, "debug_output", rb_parser_get_debug_output, 0);
21803 rb_define_method(Ripper, "debug_output=", rb_parser_set_debug_output, 1);
21804 rb_define_method(Ripper, "error?", ripper_error_p, 0);
21805#ifdef RIPPER_DEBUG
